name: 3 Leg Chatarunga Pose_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart and feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lift your right leg straight back and up, keeping your hips level.
Step:3 Shift your body forward into a plank position while keeping the right leg lifted.
Step:4 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows close to your sides, maintaining a straight line from head to left heel. Return to the plank position and repeat on the left side.

name: 3 Leg Dog Pose_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in a downward-facing dog position with your hands shoulder-width apart and feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lift your right leg straight back and up, keeping your hips level and ensuring your body forms a straight line from your wrists to your raised foot.
Step:3 Hold the position, keeping your core engaged and your leg extended.
Step:4 Lower your right leg back to the floor and return to the plank position. Repeat with the left leg.

name: 3-4 Sit-up_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head, keeping your elbows wide.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your knees, coming up about three-quarters of the way.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position and repeat.

name: 4 Coners Side Step_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent.
Step:2 Keep your hands close in front of your chest with your fists forming a punch and facing forward.
Step:3 Lift your right foot to the back, straightening it sideways and lightly touching the floor when fully extended. While extending both fists frontwards.
Step:4 Bring your right foot back to starting position and both fists close to your chest at starting position and repeat with alternating legs

name: 4 Corners Curtsy_female
instructions: Step:1 Start with feet shoulder-width apart, hands close to your chest.

Step:2 Step your right foot back and to the left, crossing behind your left leg and bending both knees into a curtsy lunge while extending both arms straight to the oposite side in front of yout torso.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by stepping your right foot forward to meet your left foot.
Step:4 Repeat the curtsy lunge the opposite side while straightening both arms on the opposite side.

name: 4 Punches Side Squat_female
instructions: Step:1 Start with feet shoulder-width apart, hands in fists at chest level.
Step:2 Perform four punches in front of you, alternating between left and right hands.
Step:3 Step your right foot out to the side and lower into a squat position, keeping your back straight and knees aligned with your toes.
Step:4 Return to the standing position by stepping your left foot back in, and repeat the exercise.

name: 4 Reverse Lunge and 4 Side Taps_female
instructions: Step:1 Start with feet shoulder-width apart, arms straight in front of your torso.
Step:2 Step your right foot back into a reverse lunge, bending both knees to 90 degrees. Return to the starting position by stepping your right foot forward and repeat 1 time.
Step:3 Return to standing position and perform four side taps by stepping your right foot out to the side and tapping the floor, then bringing it back to the center. Repeat on the other side.
Step:4 Return to starting position and repeat.

name: 45 degree bicycle twist knee to elbow
instructions: Step:1 Align yourself to 45 degrees to the floor by fixing your left foot into the footrest and supporting your thigh against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your left hand behind your head and your right hand on your waist.
Step:3 Open your upper leg slightly and bend your knee while bringing your opposite elbow towards it.
Step:4 Return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree bicycle twisting crunch
instructions: Step:1 Align yourself to 45 degrees to the floor by fixing your left foot into the footrest and supporting your thigh against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your left hand behind your head and your right hand on your waist.
Step:3 Straighten your upper leg wide and bend your knee while twisting your torso and bringing the opposite elbow towards it.
Step:4 Return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree Bicycle Twisting Crunch_female
instructions: Step:1 Align yourself to 45 degrees to the floor by fixing your left foot into the footrest and supporting your thigh against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your left hand behind your head and your right hand on your waist.
Step:3 Straighten your upper leg wide and bend your knee while twisting your torso and bringing the opposite elbow towards it.
Step:4 Return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 Degree Bicycle Twisting_female
instructions: Step:1 Align yourself to 45 degrees to the floor by fixing your left foot into the footrest and supporting your thigh against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your left hand behind your head and your right hand on your waist.
Step:3 Open your upper leg slightly and bend your knee while bringing your opposite elbow towards it.
Step:4 Return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree hyperextension (arms in front of chest)_female
instructions: Step:1 Fix your feet to the footrests and press your thighs against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your arms across your chest and lean forward.
Step:3 Raise yourself by leaning backward and forming an upright position.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree hyperextension arms to chest
instructions: Step:1 Fix your feet to the footrests and press your thighs against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your arms across your chest and lean forward.
Step:3 Raise yourself by leaning backward and forming an upright position.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree side bend
instructions: Step:1 Place your feet one after the other onto the footrests and support your thigh against the platform.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head and assume an upright position with a straight back.
Step:3 Crunch your torso toward the platform and then to the other side.
Step:4 Repeat while keeping yourself stable.

name: 45 Degree Side Bend_female
instructions: Step:1 Place your feet one after the other onto the footrests and support your thigh against the platform.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head and assume an upright position with a straight back.
Step:3 Crunch your torso toward the platform and then to the other side.
Step:4 Repeat while keeping yourself stable.

name: 45 degree twisting hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Fix your feet to the footrests and press your thighs against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head and lean forward.
Step:3 Raise yourself by leaning backward and twisting your torso to a side.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degree twisting hyperextension_female
instructions: Step:1 Fix your feet to the footrests and press your thighs against the padded platform.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head and lean forward.
Step:3 Raise yourself by leaning backward and twisting your torso to a side.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 45 degrees Step Out_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart keeping them bent to a half squat position.
Step:2 Step your right foot out at a 45-degree angle to the side until your leg is completely straight.
Step:3 Bring your right foot back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left foot, continuing to alternate sides.

name: 5 Sec Fist Against Chin_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit or stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, maintaining good posture. Make a fist with both hands and place them under your chin.
Step:2 Apply gentle upward pressure with your fist against your chin, resisting with your neck muscles. Hold this position for 5 seconds.
Step:3 Keep your neck and head steady, avoiding any movement while maintaining the pressure.
Step:4 Release the pressure after 5 seconds and relax. Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: 90 degree heel touch
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your hips and knees bent to 90 degrees and your arms extended overhead.
Step:2 Raise your upper back and bring your arms forward to touch your heels.
Step:3 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 90 Degree Heels Touch_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your hips and knees bent to 90 degrees and your arms extended overhead.
Step:2 Raise your upper back and bring your arms forward to touch your heels.
Step:3 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: 90 to 90 Stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with both legs bent at 90 degrees. Position one leg in front of your body with your thigh and shin at a 90-degree angle, and the other leg to the side with your thigh and shin at a 90-degree angle with foot extending backwards.
Step:2 Lean lightly forward keeping your arms on the floor and holding the stretch for a few seconds.
Step:3 Switch the position of your legs to perform the stretch on the opposite side.

name: Ab Mat Sit-up_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with a yoga mat placed under your lower back, knees bent facing outwards, and feet  on the floor touching together. Hands behind your head.
Step:2 Lean back to lie down, keeping your arms behind your head.
Step:3 Use your core muscles to sit your torso up, return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Ab Tuck_female
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging on a dip station, holding the parallel bars with your arms extended and your body straight.
Step:2 Lift your knees towards your chest while lightly extending your hips backward, engaging your core muscles.
Step:3 Extend your legs back downwards to starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement.

name: AB Wheel All The Way out
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body into a straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, extending fully and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel All The Way out_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body into a straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, extending fully and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Halfway out
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body halfway while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, extending halfway and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Halfway out_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body halfway while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, extending halfway and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Left out
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward and to the left, extending your body into a partial straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, rolling out to the left and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Left out_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward and to the left, extending your body into a partial straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, rolling out to the left and returning to the starting position each time.

name: Ab Wheel Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward until your body is in a plank position, with your arms extended and your body forming a straight line from head to knees.
Step:3 Hold the plank position, keeping your core engaged and your body stable, as long as required.
Step:4 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position.

name: Ab Wheel Plank_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward until your body is in a plank position, with your arms extended and your body forming a straight line from head to knees.
Step:3 Hold the plank position, keeping your core engaged and your body stable, as long as required.
Step:4 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position.

name: AB Wheel Pulses
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on the floor with your arms extended overhead, holding the ab wheel with both hands.
Step:2 Engage your core by lifting your upper body off the floor slightly, performing a small crunch while keeping your arms extended and the ab wheel overhead.
Step:3 Perform small pulsing crunches, lifting and lowering your upper body slightly while maintaining tension in your core.
Step:4 Continue the pulsing movement for the desired number of repetitions, keeping your arms extended and the ab wheel steady.

name: AB Wheel Pulses_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on the floor with your arms extended overhead, holding the ab wheel with both hands.
Step:2 Engage your core by lifting your upper body off the floor slightly, performing a small crunch while keeping your arms extended and the ab wheel overhead.
Step:3 Perform small pulsing crunches, lifting and lowering your upper body slightly while maintaining tension in your core.
Step:4 Continue the pulsing movement for the desired number of repetitions, keeping your arms extended and the ab wheel steady.

name: AB Wheel Right out
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward and to the right, extending your body into a partial straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, rolling out to the right and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Right out_Female
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on a mat with the ab wheel placed on the floor in front of you, holding it with both hands. Ensure your arms are extended and your back is straight.
Step:2 Roll the ab wheel forward and to the right, extending your body into a partial straight line while keeping your core engaged and your hips slightly extended backward.
Step:3 Roll the ab wheel back to the starting position, using your core muscles to control the movement and maintain stability.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, rolling out to the right and returning to the starting position each time.

name: AB Wheel Take it or Leave It
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs bent at 90 degrees and your feet off the floor, forming a tabletop position. Hold the AB wheel overhead with both hands, keeping your arms straight.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest towards your knees to perform a crunch, bringing the AB wheel towards your shins.
Step:3 Place the AB wheel gently on your shins and lower your upper body back to the floor, keeping your legs in the tabletop position.
Step:4 Perform another crunch, reaching up to grab the AB wheel from your shins, and then lower your upper body back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: AB Wheel Take it or Leave It_Female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs bent at 90 degrees and your feet off the floor, forming a tabletop position. Hold the AB wheel overhead with both hands, keeping your arms straight.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest towards your knees to perform a crunch, bringing the AB wheel towards your shins.
Step:3 Place the AB wheel gently on your shins and lower your upper body back to the floor, keeping your legs in the tabletop position.
Step:4 Perform another crunch, reaching up to grab the AB wheel from your shins, and then lower your upper body back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Abdominal crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with knees slightly bent, feet placed on the floor and arms raised to the shoulder height.
Step:2 Squeeze your abdominals and lift your upper back off the floor, reaching forward with your arms
Step:3 Hold for few seconds and slowly return to the starting position.

name: Abdominal Crunches Machine
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and resistance to your desired settings on the abdominal crunch machine. Sit on the seat and position your feet securely on the footrests.
Step:2 Grab the handles, ensuring your elbows are pointed forward.
Step:3 Engage your core muscles and crunch your abdominals by pulling your upper body forward and curling your chest towards your knees.
Step:4 Hold the crunch for a second, then slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Abdominal crunches with hold
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with knees slightly bent and feet placed on the floor.

Step:2 Inhale and try reaching forward with straight arms while lifting your upper back off the floor.                                                                   3. Hold the end position for few seconds and slowly return to the starting position.

name: Abdominal stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and drawn towards your chest.
Step:2 Wrap your arms around your knees, hugging them tightly.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position, allowing your back to round slightly and your head to relax forward.
Step:4 After holding the stretch for the desired amount of time, release your arms and return to a neutral sitting position.

name: Abdominal Stretch ( Version2 )_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and drawn towards your chest.
Step:2 Place your hands on your knees keeping them set and lean your chest to your knees to stretch.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position, allowing your back to round slightly and your head to relax forward.
Step:4 After holding the stretch for the desired amount of time, release your arms and return to a neutral sitting position.

name: Abdominal Stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and drawn towards your chest.
Step:2 Wrap your arms around your knees, hugging them tightly.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position, allowing your back to round slightly and your head to relax forward.
Step:4 After holding the stretch for the desired amount of time, release your arms and return to a neutral sitting position.

name: Above head chest stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back straight. Raise your arms overhead and clasp your hands together with elbows bent.
Step:2 Keeping your hands clasped, bring your elbows backward to stretch.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:4 After holding the stretch for the desired amount of time, return to the starting position.

name: Above Head Chest Stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back straight. Raise your arms overhead and clasp your hands together with elbows bent.
Step:2 Keeping your hands clasped, bring your elbows backward to stretch.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:4 After holding the stretch for the desired amount of time, return to the starting position.

name: Across chest shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back straight. Raise one arm to shoulder height and bring it across your chest.
Step:2 Use your opposite hand to grasp your upper arm and gently pull it towards your chest, stretching your shoulder.
Step:3 Hold the stretch in this position.
Step:4 Release your arm and repeat the movement on the other side.

name: Adductor dynamic stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a mat with both legs extended upwards.
Step:2 Open your legs wide apart, stretching your inner thighs.
Step:3 Bring your legs back together to the starting position.
Step:4 Continue the movement in a dynamic manner, opening and closing your legs.

name: Adductor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a mat with both legs extended upwards.
Step:2 Open your legs wide apart, stretching your inner thighs.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, or as needed.

name: Adductor stretch side standing
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart while keeping your hands together in front of your chest.
Step:2 Take a step to the left while keeping your right foot in place.
Step:3 Bend the left knee unless your right thigh becomes parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Hold for a few seconds, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: adductor stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a mat with both legs extended upwards.
Step:2 Open your legs wide apart, stretching your inner thighs.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, or as needed.

name: Air Bike (VERSION 2)_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders off the floor, engaging your core.
Step:3 Bring your right elbow towards your left knee while extending your right leg straight.
Step:4 Switch sides, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee while extending your left leg straight. Continue alternating sides in a pedaling motion.

name: Air bike crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders off the floor, engaging your core.
Step:3 Bring your right elbow towards your left knee while extending your right leg lightly.
Step:4 Switch sides, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee while extending your left leg lightly. Continue alternating sides in a pedaling motion.

name: air bike_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Lift your back off the floor, engaging your core.
Step:3 Bring your right elbow towards your left knee while extending your right leg slightly.
Step:4 Lower your back to the floor and repeat, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee while extending your left leg lightly.

name: Air punches march
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Make fists of your hands, fold one arm at your side and extend the other arm overhead.
Step:3 Raise one of your thighs while bending your knee, and lower your arm while extending the other arm overhead.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat by raising your other thigh.

name: Air Swing Side To Side Swing
Air Swing Side To Side Swing Female
Air twisting crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your knees bent and heels on the floor.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head.
Step:3 Raise your chest and twist your torso to one side while bringing the opposite knee close.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat by twisting towards the other side.

name: air twisting crunch_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your knees bent and heels on the floor.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head.
Step:3 Raise your chest and twist your torso to one side while bringing the opposite knee close.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat by twisting towards the other side.

name: All fours quad stretch
instructions: Step:1 Start in an all-fours position on a mat, with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Reach back with your right hand to grasp the ankle of your right leg.
Step:3 Gently pull your ankle towards your glutes, stretching your quadriceps, and hold the stretch in this position for 20-30 seconds.
Step:4 Release your ankle and switch sides, repeating the stretch.

name: ALL FOURS QUAD STRETCH_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in an all-fours position on a mat, with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Reach back with your right hand to grasp the ankle of your right leg.
Step:3 Gently pull your ankle towards your glutes, stretching your quadriceps, and hold the stretch in this position for 20-30 seconds.
Step:4 Release your ankle and switch sides, repeating the stretch.

name: Alternate arm leg plank
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously, extending them straight out while maintaining balance. Hold briefly, then lower back to the plank position.
Step:3 Lift your left arm and right leg simultaneously, extending them straight out and holding briefly before returning to the plank position.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides, lifting opposite arms and legs.

name: Alternate arm leg plank hold
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously, extending them straight out while maintaining balance. Hold this position for a brief period of 1-2 seconds.
Step:3 Lower your right arm and left leg back to the plank position.
Step:4 Lift your left arm and right leg simultaneously, extending them straight out and holding for a brief period of 1-2 seconds before returning to the plank position.

name: Alternate arm leg plank rest pause
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously, extending them straight out while maintaining balance. Then lower back to the plank position and pause for a few seconds.
Step:3 Lift your left arm and right leg simultaneously, extending them straight out and return to the plank position and pause for a few seconds.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides, lifting opposite arms and legs with a brief pause in the plank position.

name: Alternate Bicep Curl Resistance Band
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the center of a resistance band with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Hold the handles of the resistance band with your arms fully extended by your sides, palms facing forward.
Step:3 Raise one of the handles towards your shoulder by bending your arm.
Step:4 As it reaches near the shoulder, return to the initial position and repeat by folding your other arm.

name: Alternate bicep curl standing dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should face forward (supinated grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right dumbbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the forward-facing position of your palms.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: alternate front kick in place_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and arms bent by your sides.
Step:2 Jump lightly and lift your right leg and extend it forward in a kicking motion while simultaneously swing your left arm forward.
Step:3 Lower your right leg and left arm back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement by alternating front kicks with each leg.

name: Alternate hammer curl seated dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should face each other (neutral grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right dumbbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the neutral grip with your palm facing inward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate hammer curl standing dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should face each other (neutral grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right dumbbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the neutral grip with your palm facing inward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate heel touch side kick squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, arms by your side, and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Lower your hips by bending one of your knees while sliding the opposite leg outward on the floor, and touch your heel with your hands.
Step:3 Return to the initial position, and do the same while bending your other knee and sliding the opposite leg.

name: Alternate heel touches
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Lift your shoulders slightly off the floor, engaging your core.
Step:2 Reach your right hand towards your right heel, then return to the center position.
Step:3 Reach your left hand towards your left heel. Continue alternating sides in this manner.

name: Alternate leg pull
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight at 45 degrees off the floor and your arms extended overhead in line with your torso.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders off the mat, engaging your core, and simultaneously bring your right knee towards your chest while swinging both arms in an arc motion until parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Straighten your right leg, and lower your arms and shoulders back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, bringing it towards your chest between your straight arms. Continue alternating sides in this manner.

name: Alternate Leg Pull_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight just off the floor and your arms extended overhead in line with your torso.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders off the mat, engaging your core, and simultaneously bring your right knee towards your chest while swinging both arms in a circular motion until parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Lower your right leg, arms and shoulders back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, bringing it towards your chest between your straight arms. Continue alternating sides in this manner.

name: Alternate leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your arms resting on the floor by your side.
Step:2 Raise your legs straight in the air, making a 90-degree angle with your torso.
Step:3 Lower one of your legs and bring it back just before touching the floor.
Step:4 Do the same with your other leg, and repeat.

name: Alternate leg raise from reverse plank position
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your hips with your arms resting on the floor by your side and your legs extended forward.
Step:2 Raise your upper back, bring your elbows under the shoulders, and bear weight on your forearms with your palms down.
Step:3 Alternately raise and lower your legs to your maximum range while keeping them straight.

name: Alternate Leg Raise from Reverse Plank Position_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your hips with your arms resting on the floor by your side and your legs extended forward.
Step:2 Raise your upper back, bring your elbows under the shoulders, and bear weight on your forearms with your palms down.
Step:3 Alternately raise and lower your legs to your maximum range while keeping them straight.

name: Alternate leg raise with head up
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your arms resting on the floor by your side.
Step:2 Raise your head and upper back off the floor, and lift your legs straight in the air, making a 90-degree angle with your torso.
Step:3 Lower one of your legs and bring it back just before touching the floor.
Step:4 Do the same with your other leg, and repeat.

name: Alternate Leg Raise with Head Up Female
Alternate Leg Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your arms resting on the floor by your side.
Step:2 Raise your head and upper back off the floor, and lift your legs straight in the air, making a 90-degree angle with your torso.
Step:3 Lower one of your legs and bring it back just before touching the floor.
Step:4 Do the same with your other leg, and repeat.

name: Alternate lying floor leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight and your arms resting by your sides.
Step:2 Lift both legs, straight towards the ceiling until they go past your hips.
Step:3 Lower your legs halfway down, then lift them back up towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Lower your legs back down to the initial position. Repeat the movement.

name: Alternate Lying Floor Leg Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight and your arms resting by your sides.
Step:2 Lift both legs, straight towards the ceiling until they go past your hips.
Step:3 Lower your legs halfway down, then lift them back up towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Lower your legs back down to the initial position. Repeat the movement.

name: Alternate oblique crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back and fold your knees while keeping your feet on the floor.
Step:2 Place your right hand behind your head and your left hand on the floor for support.
Step:3 Raise and twist your chest to your left and bring your right elbow towards the left knee.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Alternate Oblique Crunch_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back and fold your knees while keeping your feet on the floor.
Step:2 Place your right hand behind your head.
Step:3 Raise and twist your chest to your left and bring your right elbow towards the left knee.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Alternate punching
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands held up in a guard position near your chest.
Step:2 Punch forward with your right arm, rotating your upper torso slightly.
Step:3 Return your right hand to the guard position and punch forward with your left arm, again rotating your upper torso slightly.
Step:4 Continue alternating punches in a rhythmic manner.

name: Alternate Punching_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands held up in a guard position near your chest.
Step:2 Punch forward with your right arm, rotating your upper torso slightly.
Step:3 Return your right hand to the guard position and punch forward with your left arm, again rotating your upper torso slightly.
Step:4 Continue alternating punches in a rhythmic manner.

name: Alternate Single Leg Raise Plank_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right leg off the floor, extending it straight back while maintaining the plank position. Hold briefly.
Step:3 Lower your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Lift your left leg off the floor, extending it straight back. Hold briefly before lowering it back to the starting position. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternate single leg raises plank
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right leg off the floor, extending it straight back while maintaining the plank position. Hold briefly.
Step:3 Lower your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Lift your left leg off the floor, extending it straight back. Hold briefly before lowering it back to the starting position. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternate sprinter lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lunge back with your right leg, bending both knees to lower your body into a lunge position while reaching your hands towards your left foot.
Step:3 Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Lunge back with your left leg, reaching your hands towards your right foot. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternate Sprinter Lunge_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lunge back with your right leg, bending both knees to lower your body into a lunge position while reaching your hands towards your left foot.
Step:3 Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Lunge back with your left leg, reaching your hands towards your right foot. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternate superman
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your arms extended straight in front of you and your legs extended straight back.
Step:2 Lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously off the floor, engaging your back muscles. Hold briefly.
Step:3 Lower your right arm and left leg back to the mat.
Step:4 Lift your left arm and right leg simultaneously off the floor, holding briefly before lowering them back to the mat. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternate toe tap leg lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your knees bent and feet on the floor.
Step:2 Raise your torso off the floor by placing your elbows on the floor and raise one of your knees toward the chest while keeping your knee bent.
Step:3 Lower your foot back to the floor while raising your other knee towards your chest.
Step:4 Keep repeating by alternately moving your knees towards and away from the chest.

name: Alternate Toe Tap Leg Lift_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your knees bent and feet on the floor.
Step:2 Raise your torso off the floor by placing your elbows on the floor and raise one of your knees toward the chest while keeping your knee bent.
Step:3 Lower your foot back to the floor while raising your other knee towards your chest.
Step:4 Keep repeating by alternately moving your knees towards and away from the chest.

name: Alternating biceps curl seated dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should face forward (supinated grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right dumbbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the supinated grip with your palm facing upward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: alternating biceps hammer curls resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, standing on the middle of a resistance band. Hold the handles of the band with your palms facing each other (neutral grip) and arms fully extended by your sides.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right handle up towards your shoulder, maintaining the neutral grip with your palm facing inward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternating hammer curls seated dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should face each other (neutral grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl the right dumbbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the neutral grip with your palm facing inward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the same motion with your left arm, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternating Hamstring Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping both arms bent by your sides.
Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and bend your right knee, bringing your heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstring at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower your right leg back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg. Alternate between right and left legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternating hamstring curl with punch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle with fists close to your chest.
Step:2 Curl your right leg back, bringing your heel towards your glutes while simultaneously punching forward with your left arm.
Step:3 Lower your right leg and return your left arm to the starting position.
Step:4 Curl your left leg back, bringing your heel towards your glutes while punching forward with your right arm. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating Hamstring Curl with Punch_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle with fists close to your chest.
Step:2 Curl your right leg back, bringing your heel towards your glutes while simultaneously punching forward with your left arm.
Step:3 Lower your right leg and return your left arm to the starting position.
Step:4 Curl your left leg back, bringing your heel towards your glutes while punching forward with your right arm. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating leg downward dog
instructions: Step:1 Start in a downward dog position with your hands and feet on the mat, hips lifted towards the ceiling, and body forming an inverted V shape.
Step:2 Bend your right knee towards your chest, keeping your foot on the floor and maintaining balance on your left foot and both hands.
Step:3 Straighten your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Bend your left knee towards your chest while maintaining balance. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating Leg Downward Dog_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in a downward dog position with your hands and feet on the mat, hips lifted towards the ceiling, and body forming an inverted V shape.
Step:2 Bend your right knee towards your chest, keeping your foot on the floor and maintaining balance on your left foot and both hands.
Step:3 Straighten your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Bend your left knee towards your chest while maintaining balance. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating leg lifts
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your legs straight and hands behind your head.
Step:2 Raise one of your legs straight towards the ceiling without bending your knee.
Step:3 Slowly lower your leg back towards the floor and simultaneously raise the other leg.

name: Alternating Lunge with Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Step your right foot forward, placing it outside your right hand, and rotate your torso to the right, extending your right arm towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Return your right hand and foot to the plank position.

Step:4 Step your left foot forward, placing it outside your left hand, and rotate your torso to the left, extending your left arm towards the ceiling. Return to the plank position. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating oblique sit ups
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your hands lightly behind your head with your elbows pointing outward.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders off the mat and twist your torso to bring your right elbow towards your left knee.
Step:3 Lower your shoulders back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating Plank Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Step your right foot forward outside your right hand, bringing your body into a low lunge position.
Step:3 Return your right foot to the plank position.
Step:4 Step your left foot forward outside your left hand, bringing your body into a low lunge position. Return your left foot to the plank position. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating step out
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and clasp your hands in front of your chest.
Step:3 Lift one of your feet off the floor and step to your side.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and do the same with your other foot. Repeat.

name: Alternating Step Out_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and clasp your hands in front of your chest.
Step:3 Lift one of your feet off the floor and step to your side.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and do the same with your other foot. Repeat.

name: Alternating Superman_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your arms extended straight in front of you and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously off the floor, engaging your core and back muscles. Hold briefly.
Step:3 Lower your right arm and left leg back to the mat.
Step:4 Lift your left arm and right leg simultaneously off the floor, holding briefly before lowering them back to the mat. Continue alternating sides.

name: Alternating toe tap
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight on the floor and your arms resting by your sides.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your right leg and left arm towards the ceiling, trying to touch your toe with your hand.
Step:3 Lower your right leg and left arm back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg and right arm, lifting them towards the ceiling and trying to touch your toe with your hand. Continue alternating sides.

name: Ankle - Dorsal Flexion_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands resting on your hips or at your sides for balance.
Step:2 Flex both feet simultaneously, bringing your toes towards your shins, and then return to the starting position.
Step:3 Repeat the movement, flexing and relaxing both feet simultaneously.

name: Ankle - Plantar Flexion_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands resting on your hips or at your sides for balance..
Step:2 Rise onto your toes, lifting your heels off the floor.
Step:3 Lower your heels back to the starting position. Repeat the movement.

name: Ankle circles
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, hands at your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right foot off the floor slightly and rotate your ankle in a circular motion, making small controlled circles.
Step:3 After a set number of rotations, switch direction and rotate your ankle in the opposite direction.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left ankle, rotating in both directions.

name: Ankle Circles_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, hands at your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right foot off the floor slightly and rotate your ankle in a circular motion, making small controlled circles.
Step:3 After a set number of rotations, switch direction and rotate your ankle in the opposite direction.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left ankle, rotating in both directions.

name: Ankle dorsal flexion
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands resting on your hips or at your sides for balance.
Step:2 Flex both feet simultaneously, bringing your toes towards your shins, and then return to the starting position.
Step:3 Repeat the movement, flexing and relaxing both feet simultaneously.

name: Ankle plantar flexion
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands resting on your hips or at your sides for balance..
Step:2 Rise onto your toes, lifting your heels off the floor.
Step:3 Lower your heels back to the starting position. Repeat the movement.

name: Archer pull up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands positioned wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Pull yourself up towards the bar while simultaneously shifting your body to the right, bringing your chest closer to your right hand.
Step:3 Lower yourself back to the starting position.
Step:4 Pull yourself up again, this time shifting your body to the left, bringing your chest closer to your left hand. Continue alternating sides.

name: Archer push up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bend your right elbow to lower your chest towards your right hand while keeping your left arm extended straight to the side.
Step:3 Push back up to the starting position.
Step:4 Bend your left elbow to lower your chest towards your left hand while keeping your right arm extended straight to the side. Continue alternating sides.

name: Archer Push up_female
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bend your right elbow to lower your chest towards your right hand while keeping your left arm extended straight to the side.
Step:3 Push back up to the starting position.
Step:4 Bend your left elbow to lower your chest towards your left hand while keeping your right arm extended straight to the side. Continue alternating sides.

name: Archer step back
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your arms forward while keeping your palms inward.
Step:3 Take a step backward by extending your left leg behind you while taking your elbow past your back like an archer.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat by taking your right leg backward.

name: Archer Stepback_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your arms forward while keeping your palms inward.
Step:3 Take a step backward by extending your left leg behind you while taking your elbow past your back like an archer.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat by taking your right leg backward.

name: Arm circle
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight to your sides.
Step:2 Begin by making circular motions with your arms, moving them forward in a controlled manner.
Step:3 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Arm circles backward
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight to your sides.
Step:2 Begin by making circular motions with your arms, moving them backward in a controlled manner.
Step:3 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Arm crossover
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder height, palms facing the floor.
Step:2 Bring your arms forward and cross them in front of your chest.
Step:3 Return your arms to the starting position, extending them out to the sides.
Step:4 Continue crossing your arms in front of your chest and extending them back out to the sides in a controlled, rhythmic manner.

name: Arm crossover chest out
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended out to the sides at shoulder height, elbows bent and palms facing the floor.
Step:2 Bring your arms forward while straightening them and cross them in front of your chest twice.
Step:3 Return your arms to the starting position, extending them out to the sides and bringing your chest forward.
Step:4 Continue crossing your arms in front of your chest and extending them back out to the sides in a controlled, rhythmic manner.

name: Arm double crossover
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended out to the sides at shoulder height, elbows bent and palms facing the floor.
Step:2 Bring your arms forward while keeping them bent and cross them in front of your chest twice.
Step:3 Return your arms to the starting position, extending them out to the sides.
Step:4 Continue crossing your arms in front of your chest and extending them back out to the sides in a controlled, rhythmic manner.

name: Arm pulses
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend your arms to make a 90-degree angle with the elbows while keeping your palms facing inward.
Step:3 Tighten your upper arms and move your arms forward and backward in a pulse-like fashion.
Step:4 Keep doing this activity for a suitable time.

name: Arm pulses cross
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bring your forearms forward with your palms facing the floor and make a 90-degree angle with your upper arms.
Step:3 Tighten your upper arms and move your hands towards each other.
Step:4 As your one hand comes over the other one, return to the initial position and repeat.

name: Arm pulses palms downwards
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms bent at the elbows, with your forearms parallel to the floor and palms facing upwards.
Step:2 Perform small, quick pulses by moving your forearms forward and backward, maintaining the position and height.
Step:3 Continue pulsing in a controlled, rhythmic manner for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Arm pulses palms upwards
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms bent at the elbows, with your forearms parallel to the floor and palms facing downwards.
Step:2 Perform small, quick pulses by moving your forearms forward and backward, maintaining the position and height.
Step:3 Continue pulsing in a controlled, rhythmic manner for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Arm rotation knee lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Fold your arms at your sides and make fists with your hands near your chest.
Step:3 Raise your right knee while rotating your torso to the left side and back to the right side.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat by raising your other knee.

name: Arm swing side to side
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder level, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Swing your arms forward until they meet and cross together in front of you in a hugging motion.
Step:3 Swing your arms back to the starting position.
Step:4 Continue swinging your arms forward and back in a controlled, rhythmic manner.

name: Arm Tuck Side Bend_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with your right arm extended straight out to the side at shoulder height and palm facing upwards and your left hand resting on your hip.
Step:2 Bend your right arm at the elbow, bringing your hand down towards your lower back.
Step:3 Return your right arm to the extended position.
Step:4 Continue the movement with the same arm for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Armless Prayer Stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Begin on your knees, spread wide and feet touching, with your elbows on the floor, directly under your shoulders.
Step:2 Place your hands on your shoulders, with your head positioned between your elbows close to the floor.
Step:3 Gently lower your chest towards the floor, keeping your hips over your knees and your back straight.
Step:4 Hold the stretch briefly, then return to the starting position. Repeat the movement.

name: arms behind back shoulder flexor stretch
Arms behind back shoulder flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms at your sides.
Step:2 Bring both arms behind your back. Set your forearms parallel to the floor, crossing one over the other to stretch your shoulders.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your shoulders. Return to the starting position and repeat as needed.

name: Arms Lateral Raise And Rotation Up
Arms Lateral Raise And Rotation Up_Female
Arms up and down
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Extend your right arm straight up overhead and your left arm straight down by your side.
Step:2 Simultaneously lower your right arm while raising your left arm, keeping both arms straight, until your right arm is down by your side and your left arm is overhead.
Step:3 Continue alternating the arms in a controlled, rhythmic swinging motion, moving one arm up while the other moves down.

name: Arnold press cable Resistance band standing
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart, in the middle of a resistance band.
Step:2 Hold the band handles with your arms bent close to your chest and palms facing back.
Step:3 Push the handles up, while rotating your arms and hands to look forward, and extending your arms overhead.
Step:4 Return to the initial position by reversing the movement and repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Arnold press dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Start with your arms bent, palms facing your shoulders, and elbows close to your torso.
Step:2 Press your back against the bench. Begin to press the dumbbells overhead. As you press, rotate your palms so they face forward at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms at the top, ensuring your biceps are near your ears.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position by rotating your palms back towards your shoulders. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Around the world superman hold
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your arms extended straight to your sides and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor, holding the Superman position.
Step:3 Move your arms in a circular motion, starting from the initial position, sweeping them around straight forward, and back to the starting position.
Step:4 Continue moving your arms in a controlled, rhythmic manner while maintaining the Superman hold.

name: around the world superman hold_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat with your arms extended straight to your sides and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor, holding the Superman position.
Step:3 Move your arms in a circular motion, starting from the initial position, sweeping them around straight forward, and back to the starting position.
Step:4 Continue moving your arms in a controlled, rhythmic manner while maintaining the Superman hold.

instructions: Step:1 Sit on the Assault AirBike's seat and adjust it to a comfortable height. Place your feet on the pedals and your hands on the handles.
Step:2 Begin pedaling at a moderate pace. Simultaneously, push and pull the handles back and forth in a coordinated motion with your legs.
Step:3 Gradually increase your pedaling speed and the intensity of your arm movements to achieve a fast pace.
Step:4 Continue pedaling and moving the handles at a fast pace for the desired duration or number of intervals.

name: Assisted Bulgarian Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from an elevated box and place your right foot on it. Hold onto a stable bar or support in front of you with your right hand. Keep your chest upright and your front foot flat on the floor.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip until your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:3 Pause for a second at the bottom and push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Assisted chin up normal width reverse grip
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the platform pad of an assisted chin-up machine and grasp the handles with a reverse grip (palms facing you) at shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Begin the movement by pulling your body upward until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Slowly lower your body back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout the exercise.

name: Assisted chin up reverse close grip
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the platform pad of an assisted chin-up machine and grasp the handles with a reverse grip (palms facing you) positioned close together.
Step:2 Begin the movement by pulling your body upward until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Slowly lower your body back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout the exercise.

name: Assisted chin up reverse wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the platform pad of an assisted chin-up machine and grasp the handles with a reverse grip (palms facing you) positioned wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Begin the movement by pulling your body upward until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Slowly lower your body back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout the exercise.

name: Assisted Chin-up on a bench_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a bench with your hands gripping a pull-up bar, palms facing towards you (supinated grip).
Step:2 Use your legs to assist in pulling your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Lower your body back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Continue the movement in a controlled, rhythmic manner, using the bench for assistance.

name: Assisted close grip underhand chin up

name: Assisted weighted push up
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself in a high plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, your feet together, and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Have your partner place a weight plate on your upper back.

name: back and shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a block with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart and raise your right arm overhead.
Step:2 Bend your right elbow and reach down your back. Use your left hand to gently pull on your right elbow, enhancing the stretch.

instructions: Step:1 Sit on a block with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart and raise your right arm overhead.

name: Back extension machine
instructions: Step:1 Fix your feet to the footrests and press your thighs against the padded platform.

name: Back extension on exercise ball
instructions: Step:1 Position your lower abdomen, face down on an exercise ball , with your feet planted firmly on the floor and your legs extended straight.

name: Back Extension on Exercise Ball_female
instructions: Step:1 Position your lower abdomen, face down on an exercise ball , with your feet planted firmly on the floor and your legs extended straight.

instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and use a nearby support (such as a squat cage, wall or a chair) for balance.

name: Back lever

name: Back lever_female
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging on a bar with your arms extended overhead, hands placed shoulder-width apart, and your palms facing forward.

name: Back Slaps Wrap Arround Stretch_female

name: Backhand raise

name: Band Decline Sit up_female

name: Band front Face Pull_female
