Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions

name: Band Incline Alternate Hammer Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with your feet flat on the floor. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand using a hammer grip (palms facing each other), letting your arms hang straight down.
Step:2 Curl the right handle towards your shoulder, keeping your elbow stationary and close to your body until your hand is near your shoulder.
Step:3 Slowly lower your right hand back to the starting position with control and repeat the movement with your left hand.
Step:4 Continue alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Bench Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle. Lie back on the bench with your feet on the floor, holding the band handles at shoulder height with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the handles upward until your arms are fully extended, keeping the band aligned over your chest.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to shoulder height with control, maintaining tension in the band.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Biceps Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle. Sit back on the bench with your feet on the floor. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand with your arms hanging straight down and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl the handles upward towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows stationary and close to your body until your hands are near shoulder level.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Fly_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle. Sit back on the bench with your feet flat on the floor. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand, extending your arms out to the sides with a slight bend in your elbows, palms facing up.
Step:2 Engage your chest and bring the handles up in an arc motion towards each other until your hands meet above your chest.
Step:3 Slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Hammer Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand using a hammer grip (palms facing each other), letting your arms hang straight down.
Step:2 Curl the handles upward towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows stationary and close to your body until your hands are near shoulder level.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Hammer Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand with your palms facing each other, positioning your hands at chest height.
Step:2 Press the handles upward until your arms are fully extended, keeping the band aligned over your chest.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to shoulder height with control, maintaining tension in the band.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Palms Back Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle with feet on the floor, holding one handle of the resistance band in each hand with your palms facing your chest, positioned at shoulder height.
Step:2 Press the handles upward until your arms are fully extended, squeezing your chest muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to shoulder height with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Band Incline Row_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding one handle of the resistance band in each hand with your arms fully extended down, palms facing back. Your feet should be firm on the floor, and the resistance band should be secured under the bench.
Step:2 Pull the handles towards your chest, bending your elbows and keeping them away from your body until your hands are near by your chest sides.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the rowing motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline T Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding one handle of the resistance band in each hand with your arms fully extended down, palms facing forward. Keep your feet firm on the floor and the resistance band secured under the bench.
Step:2 Lift your arms out to the sides until they reach shoulder height, forming a "T" shape with your body.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are parallel and your torso is stable against the bench.
Step:4 Lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Triceps Extension_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended straight above your head, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the handles behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, ensuring your forearms are parallel to the floor and your upper arms remain still.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Incline Y Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding one handle of the resistance band in each hand with your arms hanging down and palms facing back. Ensure the resistance band is secured under the bench.
Step:2 Lift your arms diagonally in a "Y" shape until they are in line with your body, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band kneeling crunch_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above head height. Kneel on the floor facing away of the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your hands positioned at the sides of your head.
Step:2 Engage your core and bend at the waist, bringing your elbows towards your knees in a controlled crunch motion.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, ensuring a full contraction of your abdominal muscles.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band kneeling lat pulldown_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above head height. Kneel on the floor facing the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended overhead and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Pull the handles down towards your shoulders, bending your elbows and keeping them close to your body until your hands are near shoulder height.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the bottom of the movement, ensuring a full contraction of your back muscles.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band kneeling preacher curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point low to the floor. Squat fully on the floor facing the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended in front of you, resting on your knees, and palms facing up.
Step:2 Curl the handles towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary until your hands are near shoulder level.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring a full contraction.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band kneeling rear kick_female
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on all fours, on your knees and elbows, with your hands holding the handles of the band and the band looped around your right foot.
Step:2 Extend your right leg straight back, keeping your foot flexed and your leg in level with your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, ensuring a full contraction.
Step:4 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Kneeling Single Arm High Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a loop resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above head height. Kneel on your right knee, with the opposite foot flat on the ground for balance. Hold one end of the band with your right arm and keep it fully extended.
Step:2 Pull the band down towards your torso by bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blade.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arm fully while maintaining control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Kneeling Single Arm High Row_Female
Band Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band at a low-mid point on sturdy equipment. Lie on your back facing the extended cable passing over your torso, and attach your right ankle to the band using a cuff.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and pull it toward your chest, while the other leg stays extended and relaxed on the floor.
Step:3 Press your foot forward against the resistance, straightening your leg fully without locking the knee.
Step:4 Return slowly to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: band low alternate chest press_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above head height. Step one foot in front and the other back, with both knees slightly bent, facing away of the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your palms facing down, positioning your hands near to your shoulders.
Step:2 Press the right handle forward until your arm is fully extended, keeping your left hand stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly return the right handle to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the pressing motion with your left hand, alternating between right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band low chest fly_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a high anchor point above you. Step one foot in front and the other back, with both knees slightly bent, facing away from the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended at your sides at shoulder level, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Bring your arms down in a wide arc motion until your hands meet opposite your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly raise your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the fly motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: band low chest press_female
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above head height. Step one foot in front and the other back, with both knees slightly bent, facing away of the anchor point, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your palms facing down, positioning your hands near to your shoulders.
Step:2 Press both handles forward until your arm is fully extended. Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly return the handles to the starting position with control.
Step:3 Repeat the pressing motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Lying Reverse Grip Pressdown_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your feet flat on the floor, knees bent, and a resistance band anchored behind your head. Hold the ends of the band with your palms facing forward with your elbows bent and forearms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Extend your arms straight up to the ceiling, keeping your elbows stationary.
Step:3 Slowly return your hands to the starting position, controlling the resistance.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Lying Reverse Grip Row_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet firmly planted on the floor for stability. Hold the handles of a resistance band anchored below the bench with a reverse grip (palms forward) and allow them to hang down.
Step:2 Pull the handles of the band upwards towards your torso by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body, and squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back down towards the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Palloff Press_Female
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. Stand perpendicular to the anchor point, holding the handle of the band with both hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Push the band straight out in front of you, extending your arms fully and squeezing your chest muscles at the peak of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return your hands to your chest, maintaining control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Prone Incline Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet firmly planted on the floor for stability. Hold the handles of a resistance band anchored below the bench, with your arms fully extended down and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl the handles of the band upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back down towards the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Prone Incline Hammer Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet firmly planted on the floor for stability. Hold the handles of a resistance band anchored below the bench, with your arms fully extended down and palms facing each other (neutral grip).
Step:2 Curl the handles of the band upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and your palms facing each other throughout the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back down towards the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Securely loop a resistance band around a pull-up bar. Place one or both feet into the bottom of the loop band. Grip the pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Start in a dead hang position with your arms fully extended.
Step:3 Pull yourself upward by bending your elbows and driving them down towards your sides, bringing your chin above the bar.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Band Pullthrough
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart and the resistance band passing between your legs, held securely with both hands in front of you. Keep your knees slightly bent and your spine neutral.
Step:2 Push your hips back while hinging at the hips, allowing your hands to move between your legs as the band stretches. Maintain a flat back and keep your arms extended.
Step:3 Drive your hips forward by squeezing your glutes and return to a fully upright position while keeping your arms straight and the band under tension.
Step:4 Pause briefly at the top with your glutes fully contracted, then repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Push-up_female
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with the resistance band crossed around your upper back and each end secured under your hands, which should be placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your feet should be together.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at about a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Fly_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold the ends of a resistance band anchored below the bench with your arms extended downward and slightly bent at the elbows, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides in a wide arc motion until they are in line with your shoulders, squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, controlling the resistance band as you lower your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Spider Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold the ends of a resistance band anchored below the bench, with your arms extended downward and palms facing back (pronated grip).
Step:2 Curl the handles of the band upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back down towards the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Rotating Hammer Grip Incline Bench Row_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie face down on the bench with your forefeet firmly on the floor. Place the resistance band under the bench and hold one handle of the band in each hand using an underhand grip (palms facing up), letting your arms hang straight down.
Step:2 Pull the handles towards your torso by bending your elbows, rotating them to a hammer grip (palms facing you), and keeping them close to your body until your hands are near your sides.
Step:3 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Band Seated Lateral Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding the ends of a resistance band anchored under the bench with your arms hanging at your sides, palms facing inward, and a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent and leading with your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, controlling the resistance band as you lower your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Seated Neutral Grip Shoulders Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding the ends of a resistance band anchored under the bench, with your arms bent, hands at shoulder level, and palms facing each other (neutral grip).
Step:2 Press the handles of the band upwards until your arms are fully extended above your head, keeping your palms facing each other.
Step:3 Slowly lower your hands back to shoulder level, controlling the resistance band as you lower your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Seated Shoulder Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding the ends of a resistance band anchored under the bench, with your arms bent, hands at shoulder level, and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the handles of the band upwards until your arms are fully extended above your head, keeping your palms facing forward.
Step:3 Slowly lower your hands back to shoulder level, controlling the resistance band as you lower your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band side bend_female
instructions: Step:1 Anchor one end of the band at a low point of the equipment. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, your right side leaning to the anchor point, holding the other end of the resistance band in your right hand. Allow your left hand to hang by your side for counterbalance.
Step:2 Contract your left obliques to bend at the waist to your left side until you are upright.
Step:3 Return to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Single Arm Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place one end of the resistance band securely under your foot of the working side. Hold the other end of the band in your working hand at shoulder height, palm facing inward.
Step:2 Press the band overhead by fully extending your arm, keeping your wrist straight and elbow slightly bent at the top.
Step:3 Slowly lower the band back to the starting position, maintaining control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Single Arm Pec Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding the handle of the band in your working hand with your arm extended out to the side, palm facing forward.
Step:2 Keep your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and your chest engaged.
Step:3 Pull the band in an arc motion, bringing your hand towards the center of your chest.
Step:4 Slowly return your arm to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band single leg split squat_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the ends of a resistance band anchored under your front foot. Place your back foot on a bench behind you.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee until your front thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, straightening your front leg.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs to work the other side.

name: Band Spanish Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a split stance with your left leg forward and the other leg behind you, facing sturdy equipment. Loop a resistance band around your left leg, just under the knee, and anchor it in front of you at knee level.
Step:2 Hold your hands together in front of your chest and keep your torso upright.
Step:3 Lower your body straight down by bending both knees until your left thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through the heel of your left foot to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Band Standing Leg Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding to a weight cage for balance. Attach a resistance band to a low anchor point and loop the other end around your right ankle. Shift your weight onto your left leg.
Step:2 Curl your right leg by bending your knee, bringing your heel towards your glutes while keeping your upper leg stationary.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, straightening your leg and controlling the resistance band.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Band standing rear delt row_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the ends of a resistance band anchored at head height in front of you. Keep your arms extended straight forward just higher than shoulder height with palms facing down.
Step:2 Pull the band towards your chin by bending your elbows out to the sides, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back to shoulder height.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Two Legs Calf Raise - (Band under both legs) VERSION 2_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart on the resistance band, holding the ends in each hand with the band securely anchored under both feet.
Step:2 Rise up onto your forefeet, lifting your heels as high as possible while keeping the tension in the band.
Step:3 Slowly lower your heels back to the floor, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Warm up Shoulder Stretch_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the resistance band with both hands in front of you. Your arms should be straight, and hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Slowly lift the band overhead while slightly spreading your hands to stretch the band.
Step:3 Hold this position for a few seconds and slowly return to the starting position with the band in front of you.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Wrist Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding the end of a resistance band, with your right hand, anchored under your right foot. Rest your forearm on your thigh with your palm facing up.
Step:2 Start with your wrist extended down towards the floor, keeping your forearm stationary.
Step:3 Curl your wrist upward, bringing your knuckles towards your forearm, squeezing your forearm muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your wrist downwards. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Y Raise_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the ends of two crossed resistance bands anchored at a low point on a sturdy equipment. Start with your arms hanging in front of your torso, palms facing your hips.
Step:2 Raise your arms upward and outward to form a "Y" shape until your arms are in line with your shoulders.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position, controlling the resistance band as you lower your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Banded Feet Elevated Hip Thrusters Female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your arms by your sides and your heels placed on an elevated surface such as a bench or box. Wrap a resistance band just above your knees to add extra glute activation.
Step:2 Bend your knees at approximately 90 degrees and keep your feet hip-width apart. Brace your core and maintain a neutral spine.
Step:3 Drive through your heels and lift your hips off the ground by contracting your glutes, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your knees at the top.
Step:4 Pause at the top while pushing your knees slightly outward against the band, then lower your hips back to the ground in a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell  squat back POV
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under a barbell resting on a squat rack. Place the barbell across your upper back and grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Lift the bar off the rack and take a step back, standing with your feet shoulder-width apart.

Step:3 Keep your chest up, and maintain a neutral spine. Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor or slightly below.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees until you are fully upright. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Alternate Biceps Curl_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with one hand, your palm facing forward (supinated grip). Keep your arm fully extended by your side.
Step:2 Keep your elbow close to your torso. Slowly curl the barbell up towards your shoulder, maintaining the supinated grip with your palm facing upward.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, ensuring your elbow stays stationary and close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Back Wide Shrug_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands behind your back. Your palms should face away from your body with a wide grip.
Step:2 Keep your shoulders back and chest up. Slowly lift your shoulders towards your ears in a shrugging motion.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, holding the contraction for a moment.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell back wide shrugs
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands behind your back. Your palms should face away from your body with a wide grip.
Step:2 Keep your shoulders back and chest up. Slowly lift your shoulders towards your ears in a shrugging motion.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, holding the contraction for a moment.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell behind neck military press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench without back support, holding a barbell with both hands. Your hands should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, and the barbell should rest on your upper back and shoulders.
Step:2 Sit up straight. Start with your elbows bent and the barbell behind your neck.
Step:3 Press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended, keeping the bar slightly behind your head.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position behind your neck with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell behind neck push press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands behind your neck. Your hands should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with the barbell resting on your upper back and shoulders.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, preparing to use your legs to generate power.

Step:3 Push through your heels and extend your knees and hips explosively, pressing the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended. Keep the bar slightly behind your head at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position behind your neck with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Behind the Back Push Press Single Arm Balance_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with one hand behind your back. Your hand should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with the barbell resting on your upper back and shoulder.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, preparing to use your legs to generate power.

Step:3 Push through your heels and extend your knees and hips explosively, pressing the barbell overhead with one arm until your arm is fully extended. Keep the bar slightly behind your head at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position behind your shoulder with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Bench Lateral Step-up_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand beside a bench with a barbell across your upper back. Your hands should grip the bar slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step laterally onto the bench with your closest foot, pushing through your heel to lift your body up onto the bench.
Step:3 Bring your trailing leg up to meet the stepping leg by the bench, maintaining balance and control.
Step:4 Step down off the bench with your trailing leg first, then the stepping leg. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, and position the bar directly above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and unrack the barbell by extending your arms fully. Lower the barbell slowly and with control to your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Press the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully, focusing on using your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then carefully rack the barbell back onto the bench press rack.

name: Barbell bench press decline
instructions: Step:1 Set a decline bench at a suitable angle and lie down on it with your feet secured under the foot pads. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your core and unrack the barbell by extending your arms fully. Lower the barbell slowly and with control to your lower chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Press the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully, focusing on using your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then carefully rack the barbell back onto the bench press rack.

name: Barbell bench press incline
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45 degree angle and lie down on it with your feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your core and unrack the barbell by extending your arms fully. Lower the barbell slowly and with control to your upper chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Press the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully, focusing on using your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then carefully rack the barbell back onto the bench press rack.

name: Barbell Bench Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, and position the bar directly above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and unrack the barbell by extending your arms fully. Lower the barbell slowly and with control to your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Press the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully, focusing on using your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then carefully rack the barbell back onto the bench press rack.

Clean the barbell to your shoulders by explosively lifting it from the floor, shrugging your shoulders, and rotating your wrists so the bar rests on your shoulders with your elbows pointing forward.

Step:3 Step into a split squat position by moving one leg forward and the other leg back, lowering your body until your back knee nearly touches the floor. Ensure your front knee tracks over your toes and your back knee is bent.

Step:4 Lower your hips back to the starting position with control, stopping just before your glutes touch the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: barbell overhead lunge_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell overhead with both hands, using a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width. Keep your arms fully extended and your core engaged.

Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position by bending both knees. Your back knee should hover just above the floor, and your front thigh should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement with your left leg, continuing to alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell overhead lunges
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell overhead with both hands, using a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width. Keep your arms fully extended and your core engaged.

Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position by bending both knees. Your back knee should hover just above the floor, and your front thigh should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement with your left leg, continuing to alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell overhead shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell overhead with both hands, using a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width. Keep your arms fully extended and your core engaged.
Step:2 Raise your shoulders towards your ears in a shrugging motion while keeping your arms extended and the barbell stable overhead.
Step:3 Hold the shrugged position briefly, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Step:4 Lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell overhead squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell overhead with both hands, using a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width. Keep your arms fully extended and your core engaged.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees fully while keeping the barbell overhead. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: barbell overhead squat_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell overhead with both hands, using a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width. Keep your arms fully extended and your core engaged.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees fully while keeping the barbell overhead. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: barbell palm down wrist curl over a bench_female
instructions: Step:1 Kneel in front of a flat bench, holding a barbell with both hands, palms facing down (overhand grip). Rest your forearms on the bench with your wrists hanging over the edge and allow them to hang down.
Step:2 Curl your wrists upward, lifting the barbell as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pause Incline Bench Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the bench. Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Unrack the barbell and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. Engage your core and keep your shoulders retracted.
Step:3 Slowly and with control, lower the barbell to your upper chest, pausing for 1-3 seconds when it lightly touches your chest.
Step:4 Press the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pause Lunge_female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip.

Step:2 Step forward with your right leg into a lunge position, lowering your body until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee is nearly touching the floor. Pause for 1-3 seconds in this position.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right leg back to meet your left.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise with your left leg, alternating between right and left legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell pendlay row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Begin the row by pulling the barbell towards your abdomen, driving your elbows up and back.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell lightly touches your abdomen.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the floor with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell power clean
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squatted position with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing your body), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be resting on the floor.

Step:2 Explosively extend your hips and knees while pulling the barbell up towards your chest, keeping it close to your body. As the barbell passes your knees, shrug your shoulders and continue to pull the barbell upward.
Step:3 Quickly rotate your elbows under the bar and catch it in a front rack position with your elbows pointing forward. Stand up straight to complete the lift.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell power clean from blocks
instructions: Step:1 Position the barbell on blocks set just below knee height. Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing your body), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.

Step:2 Begin the lift by explosively extending your hips and knees while pulling the barbell up towards your chest, keeping it close to your body. As the barbell passes your knees, shrug your shoulders and continue to pull the barbell upward.
Step:3 Quickly rotate your elbows under the bar and catch it in a front rack position with your elbows pointing forward. Stand up straight to complete the lift.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the blocks with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell power jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should rest on your front deltoids and clavicles.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees to dip into a quarter squat position while keeping your chest up and maintaining a neutral spine.
Step:3 Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles to drive the barbell overhead.
Step:4 Stand up fully to complete the lift. Lower the barbell back to shoulder height with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell power snatch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squatted position with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell with a wide grip (palms facing your body), hands wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be resting on the floor.

Step:2 Explosively extend your hips and knees while pulling the barbell up towards your chest, keeping it close to your body. As the barbell passes your knees, shrug your shoulders and continue to pull the barbell upward.
Step:3 Quickly rotate your elbows under the bar and catch it in a wide overhead position with your elbows fully extended and your body in a partial squat. Stand up straight to complete the lift.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell preacher curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor. Position your upper arms on the preacher pad, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. Curl the barbell upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell pullover to triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing the barbell), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms so the barbell is directly above your chest.
Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head. Lower the barbell until you feel a stretch in your chest and lats.
Step:3 Reverse the motion by pulling the barbell back over your chest, then extend the barbell straight up by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell push bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with palms facing the barbell, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is nearly parallel to the floor.

Step:2 Pull the barbell towards your abdomen by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. At the peak of the movement, perform a small push of the barbell downwards and pull it up again.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, extending your arms fully while keeping your back straight.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell quarter squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body into a quarter squat position where your thighs are above parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell rack pull
instructions: Step:1 Position a barbell on a rack set to just below knee height. Stand with your feet hip-width apart, and grip the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing your body), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Begin the lift by driving through your heels, extending your hips and knees to lift the barbell.
Step:3 Pull the barbell up your legs until you reach a standing position with your shoulders back and hips fully extended. Keep the barbell close to your body throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the rack with control by hinging at your hips and bending your knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell rear delt raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell behind your glutes with an overhand grip (palms facing back), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Engage your rear deltoids and lift the barbell upward behind your back by raising your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell rear lunge on box
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a sturdy box with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step one foot backward off the box, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your front knee should be directly over your ankle, and your back knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position on the box, bringing your back foot forward to meet your front foot.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with the opposite leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell rear lunges
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step one foot backward, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your front knee should be directly over your ankle, and your back knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, bringing your back foot forward to meet your front foot.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with the opposite leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell reverse biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Let the barbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your forearms and biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell reverse close grip bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing back) and hands placed shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell directly above your chest with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest by bending your elbows. Keep your elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Step:3 Lower the barbell just before touching your chest, then push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell reverse grip bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing back) and hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell directly above your chest with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest by bending your elbows. Keep your elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Step:3 Allow the barbell to lightly touch your chest, then push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell reverse grip bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing forward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is nearly parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:2 Pull the barbell towards your abdomen by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell reverse spider curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on an incline bench with your chest and stomach supported. Hold a barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms fully so the barbell hangs down towards the floor.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your forearms and biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your forearms and biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell rollout
instructions: Step:1 Begin by kneeling on a mat with a barbell placed in front of you. Grip the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Slowly roll the barbell forward, extending your arms and allowing your body to move forward.
Step:3 Roll out as far as you can while maintaining control and a neutral spine. Your arms should be fully extended, and your body should be in a straight line from your head to your knees.
Step:4 Engage your core and use your abdominal muscles to pull the barbell back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell romanian deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squat position with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand up by driving through your heels and extending your hips and knees until you are standing straight with the barbell hanging in front of your thighs.

Step:3 From this standing position, hinge at your hips and push them back, lowering the barbell down the front of your legs while keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. Lower the barbell until it passes your knees.
Step:4 Drive your hips forward to return to the standing position, lifting the barbell back up while keeping it close to your legs. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated behind neck military press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell behind your neck at shoulder height.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position behind your neck with control, bending your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated concentration biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart. Lean forward slightly and rest your elbows on the inside of your thighs.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated good morning
instructions: Step:1 Sit parallel on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and lean your torso forward, lowering it towards your thighs while keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Lower your torso until it is nearly parallel to the floor, while keeping your back straight and your elbows slightly bent.
Step:4 Lift your torso back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated military press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with feet flat on the floor, back first in front of a rack. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell in front of your shoulders, just below chin level.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position with control by bending your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated on knee calve raises
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and a barbell resting across your thighs, just above your knees. Position your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lift your heels off the floor by pressing through your forefeet, raising your knees towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Squeeze your calf muscles at the top of the movement, ensuring your heels are as high as possible.
Step:4 Lower your heels back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated overhead press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell at shoulder height in front of you.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position with control, bending your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated overhead triceps press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, maintaining an upright posture. Hold a barbell with a close grip (palms facing up), hands positioned slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Position the barbell behind your head with your elbows bent and pointing upwards. Press the barbell overhead by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position with control, bending your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Begin by rotating your torso to the right, keeping your hips and lower body stationary. Rotate until you feel a stretch in your obliques.
Step:3 Reverse the movement, rotating your torso to the left, again keeping your hips and lower body stationary.
Step:4 Repeat the rotation to both sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell seated twist on exercise ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Begin by rotating your torso to the right, keeping your hips and lower body stationary. Rotate until you feel a stretch in your obliques.
Step:3 Reverse the movement, rotating your torso to the left, again keeping your hips and lower body stationary.
Step:4 Repeat the rotation to both sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell shrugs
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders straight up towards your ears as high as you can, keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Squeeze your upper back muscles (trapezius) at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell side bends
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Lean to the right side by bending at the waist, lowering your torso as far as is comfortable.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by engaging your oblique muscles and straightening your torso.
Step:4 Repeat the movement to the left side. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell side split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg and bend your right knee, lowering your body into a side lunge while keeping your left leg straight.
Step:3 Lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the floor, ensuring your right knee is aligned with your right foot.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement on the left side. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Step Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand beside a sturdy elevated surface such as a box or bench, and position a barbell securely across your upper back and shoulders. Place the foot closest to the box on top of it, ensuring your entire foot is flat and stable.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles, press firmly through the heel of your elevated foot, and drive your body upward until your working leg is fully extended and both feet are on top of the box.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top while maintaining an upright posture with your shoulders pulled back and your spine neutral.
Step:4 Lower your trailing foot back to the floor with control to return to the starting position. Complete the desired number of repetitions before switching sides.

name: Barbell Silverback Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands using an overhand grip (palms down). Your hands should be shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your torso at 45 degrees to the ground.
Step:2 Start with your arms fully extended, letting the barbell hang directly below your shoulders.
Step:3 Shrug your shoulders upward to your ears. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions.

name: Barbell Silverback Shrug_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands using an overhand grip (palms down). Your hands should be shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your torso at 45 degrees to the ground.
Step:2 Start with your arms fully extended, letting the barbell hang directly below your shoulders.
Step:3 Shrug your shoulders upward to your ears. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions.

name: Barbell single arm biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with one hand using an underhand grip (palm facing up). Let the barbell hang at arm's length by your side.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell single leg deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands using an overhand grip (palms facing down). Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg and lift your left leg behind you, keeping it straight. Allow the barbell to hang down, keeping your arms straight naturally.
Step:3 Lower the barbell until your torso is almost parallel to the floor and your left leg is extended behind you in a straight line. Keep your right knee slightly bent.
Step:4 Lift your torso back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Barbell single leg split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position one foot behind you on a bench, and the other foot firmly planted on the floor.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee, allowing your back knee to drop towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the floor and your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Barbell Smith Chest Press_Female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench positioned under the smith machine barbell, with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the bench. Grip the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Unrack the barbell by extending your arms straight up. Having the barbell over your chest with your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Lower the barbell towards your chest by bending your elbows, ensuring the barbell follows a straight path and your elbows are at a 45-degree angle to your torso.
Step:4 Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your elbows, fully engaging your chest muscles. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold the barbell with a wide overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be on the floor, close to your shins.
Step:2 Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell upward in one smooth motion. Keeping the barbell close to your body as you lift.
Step:3 As the barbell reaches chest height, quickly drop into a squat position and catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended.
Step:4 Stand up by extending your hips and knees, keeping the barbell overhead. Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch balance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Your feet should be in a slight squat stance.
Step:2 Dip slightly by bending your knees and hips, then quickly drive upwards, extending your knees and hips.
Step:3 As you extend, use the upward momentum to press the barbell overhead while simultaneously dropping into a deep squat position, catching the barbell with your arms fully extended overhead.
Step:4 Stand up by extending your hips and knees, keeping the barbell overhead. Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch deadlift close grip
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be on the floor, close to your shins.
Step:2 Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees simultaneously, keeping the barbell close to your body.
Step:3 Continue lifting until you are standing upright with the barbell at hip level.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, bending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch deadlift wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed about 2 fists wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be on the floor, close to your shins.
Step:2 Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees simultaneously, keeping the barbell close to your body.
Step:3 Continue lifting until you are standing upright with the barbell at hip level.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, bending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch from blocks
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Place the barbell on blocks positioned at knee height. Hold the barbell with a wide overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Lift the barbell off the blocks by extending your hips and knees simultaneously, keeping the barbell close to your body.

Step:3 As the barbell reaches hip level, explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell upward in one smooth motion. Quickly drop into a squat position and catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended.
Step:4 Stand up by extending your hips and knees, keeping the barbell overhead. Lower the barbell back to the blocks with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell snatch pull
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold the barbell with a wide overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be on the floor, close to your shins.
Step:2 Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees simultaneously, keeping the barbell close to your body.

Step:3 As the barbell reaches hip level, explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell upward. Focusing on pulling the barbell up to abdomen height by driving your elbows upward and outward.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, bending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell split clean
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold the barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be on the floor, close to your shins.
Step:2 Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees simultaneously, keeping the barbell close to your body.

Step:3 As the barbell reaches hip level, explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while pulling the barbell upward. Quickly drop into a split stance, with one foot forward and the other foot back, catching the barbell at shoulder height with your elbows pointing forward.

Step:4 Stand up by bringing your feet back together, keeping the barbell at shoulder height. Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell split jerk
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your elbows should be pointing slightly forward, and your chest should be up.
Step:2 Engage your core, dip slightly by bending your knees and hips, then explosively extend your knees and hips to drive the barbell overhead.

Step:3 As you drive the barbell up, quickly split your feet into a lunge position with one foot forward and the other foot back, catching the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended and your torso upright.
Step:4 Stand up by bringing your feet back together, keeping the barbell overhead. Lower the barbell back to shoulder height with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with a barbell placed across your upper back and your feet positioned in a split stance, one foot forward and the other extended behind.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending both knees until your back knee nearly touches the floor and your front thigh is parallel to the floor. Keep your front knee aligned with your front foot.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, extending both knees fully.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Barbell squat to grass
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your feet should be pointed slightly outward.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body as far down as possible, aiming to get your hips below your knees.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell squat with 2 sec hold
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your feet should be pointed slightly outward.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body as far down as possible, aiming to get your hips below your knees and pause for 2 seconds.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Staggered Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with a barbell in front of your thighs and adopt a staggered stance, placing one foot slightly behind the other with your toes aligned and both feet flat on the ground.
Step:2 Grip the barbell with both hands just outside your thighs and keep your arms straight, chest lifted, and spine neutral.
Step:3 Hinge at the hips and lower the barbell down along your front leg, keeping your back straight and shoulders pulled back.
Step:4 Once you reach just below your knees or mid-shin, push through your front heel and engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position.

name: Barbell standing back wrist curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell behind your back with an overhand grip (palms facing backward), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your glutes.
Step:2 Flex your wrists to curl the barbell upward, bringing the barbell toward your forearms.
Step:3 Hold the contraction at the top for a moment, squeezing your forearm muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing close grip curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed slightly closer  than shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward by bending your elbows, bringing the barbell toward your shoulders. Keep your elbows close to your torso throughout the movement.
Step:3 Hold the contraction at the top for a moment, squeezing your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing close grip military press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed at shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be at chest height.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, making sure to keep the bar path straight and close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the barbell overhead for a moment and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at chest height. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing concentration curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed about shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Engage your core, keep your chest up, and maintain a neutral spine. Slightly bend forward from your hips and allow your elbows to hang close to your knees.
Step:3 Curl the barbell upward by bending your elbows, bringing the barbell toward your shoulders. Keep your elbows stationary against your thighs to isolate your biceps.

Step:4 Hold the contraction at the top for a moment, squeezing your biceps. Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing leg calf raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a step with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your forefeet should be on the edge of the step, and your heels should hang off.
Step:2 Raise your heels as high as possible by extending your ankles, lifting your body upward.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, feeling the contraction in your calf muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back down below the level of the step, stretching your calves. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing military press
secondaryMuscles: Upper Chest (Clavicular Head of Pectoralis Major)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be at chest height.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, making sure to keep the bar path straight and close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the barbell overhead for a moment, ensuring your arms are fully extended and your shoulders are engaged.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at chest height. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing overhead triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed closer than shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. Your elbows should be close to your head.
Step:2 Slowly lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Lower the barbell until your forearms are parallel to the floor, feeling the stretch in your triceps.
Step:4 Press the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing shoulder press
secondaryMuscles: Upper Chest (Clavicular Head of Pectoralis Major)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be at chest height.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, keeping your elbows outwards.
Step:3 Hold the barbell overhead for a moment, ensuring your arms are fully extended and your shoulders are engaged.
