Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at chest height. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Rotate your torso to the right, keeping your hips and knees aligned with the movement.
Step:3 Rotate back to the center position with control, then twist your torso to the left.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides, repeating for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing wide grip biceps curls
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward by bending your elbows, bringing the barbell toward your shoulders. Keep your elbows close to your torso throughout the movement.
Step:3 Hold the contraction at the top for a moment, squeezing your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell standing wide grip military press
secondaryMuscles: Upper Chest (Clavicular Head of Pectoralis Major)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed  2 fists wider than shoulder-width apart. The barbell should be at chest height.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, making sure to keep the bar path straight and close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the barbell overhead for a moment, ensuring your arms are fully extended and your shoulders are engaged.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at chest height. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Step Up Balance On Box
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a box with a barbell resting on your upper back and your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Step up onto the box with one foot, driving through the heel and extending your leg to lift your body up.
Step:3 As you rise, bring the opposite knee up until your thigh is parallel to the ground, balancing momentarily at the top.
Step:4 Lower the raised leg back down with control, then step off the box to return to the starting position.

name: Barbell Step Up Balance On Box_Female
Barbell step up on bench
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pressing through your heel to lift your body up.
Step:3 Bring your left foot up to meet your right foot on the bench, standing fully upright.
Step:4 Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position. Repeat the movement, alternating the leading leg, for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell stiff leg deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees and hinge at your hips to lower the barbell toward your feet. Keep your legs mostly straight but not locked.
Step:3 Lower the barbell down the front of your legs until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Your back should remain straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lift the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your hips, squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell straight leg deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Keep your legs straight but not locked as you hinge at your hips to lower the barbell toward your feet.
Step:3 Lower the barbell down the front of your legs until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Your back should remain straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lift the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your hips, squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell sumo deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. Position a barbell on the floor in front of you, and squat down to grip the barbell with both hands inside your legs, using an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Step:2 Drive through your heels and extend your hips and knees simultaneously to lift the barbell off the floor. Keep the barbell close to your body and your arms straight as you stand up.

Step:3 Once you reach the top position, squeeze your glutes and stand tall. Slowly lower the barbell back to the floor by bending at the hips and knees, maintaining a straight back. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell sumo romanian deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed inside your legs. Your arms should be fully extended, and the barbell should rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees and hinge at your hips to lower the barbell toward your feet. Keep your legs mostly straight but not locked.
Step:3 Lower the barbell down the front of your legs until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. Your back should remain straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lift the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your hips, squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell thruster
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell at shoulder height.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hips, ensuring your thighs are just lower than your knees.
Step:3 Push through your heels to extend your legs and return to a standing position. As you rise, simultaneously press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height and immediately descend into the next squat. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell underhand bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.

Step:2 Slightly bend your knees and hinge at your hips, keeping your back straight and torso slightly above parallel to the floor. Allow the barbell to hang directly in front of you with your arms fully extended.
Step:3 Pull the barbell toward your lower ribcage by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell upright row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Allow the barbell to rest against your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Pull the barbell upward along the front of your body by bending your elbows and lifting your upper arms.
Step:3 Continue lifting the barbell until it reaches chest height, keeping your elbows higher than your wrists throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wide bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Position the barbell directly above your chest with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Slowly lower the barbell to your chest by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Once the barbell lightly touches your chest, push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wide grip biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart, arms hanging straight.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows. Keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Continue lifting the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wide grip upright row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Allow the barbell to rest against your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Pull the barbell upward along the front of your body by bending your elbows and lifting your upper arms.
Step:3 Continue lifting the barbell until it reaches chest height, keeping your elbows higher than your wrists throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wide shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Allow the barbell to rest against your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Raise your shoulders towards your ears as high as possible, keeping your arms straight and the barbell close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the contraction at the top for a moment, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wrist curl on knees
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang over the edge.
Step:2 Start with your wrists extended so the barbell is lowered as much as possible while maintaining control.
Step:3 Curl the barbell upward by flexing your wrists, lifting the barbell as high as possible while keeping your forearms stationary on your thighs.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wrist curl wide legs
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet spread wide apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Rest your forearms on the edge of the bench, allowing your wrists to hang over the edge.
Step:2 Start with your wrists extended so the barbell is lowered as much as possible.
Step:3 Curl the barbell upward by flexing your wrists, lifting the barbell as high as possible while keeping your forearms stationary on your thighs.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell wrist extension on knees
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang over the edge.
Step:2 Start with your wrists relaxed so the barbell hangs as much as possible.
Step:3 Extend the barbell upward by extending your wrists, raising the barbell as far as possible while keeping your forearms stationary on your thighs.
Step:4 Slowly bring the barbell back to the starting position by relaxing your wrists. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Barbell Z Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended and your feet slightly apart. Hold the barbell at shoulder height using an overhand grip (palms facing forward), slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Keep your back straight, engage your core, and ensure your chest is upright.
Step:3 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, keeping your head neutral and looking forward.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to shoulder height. Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions.

name: Barbell Z Press_female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended and your feet slightly apart. Hold the barbell at shoulder height using an overhand grip (palms facing forward), slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Keep your back straight, engage your core, and ensure your chest is upright.
Step:3 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, keeping your head neutral and looking forward.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to shoulder height. Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions.

name: Basic toe touch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend at the hips and reach down towards your toes, keeping your legs as straight as possible.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, feeling the stretch in your hamstrings and lower back.
Step:4 Return to the standing position and repeat the movement.

name: Basketball shot jump
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands mimicking holding a basketball.
Step:2 Thrust upwards explosively from the squat position to jump, extending your legs and arms as if shooting a basketball.
Step:3 Land softly with your feet flat on the floor, bending your knees to absorb the impact.
Step:4 Return to the squat position and repeat the movement.

name: Behind neck lat pull down machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor. Grasp the bar with a wide overhand grip (palms facing forward).
Step:2 Lean slightly forward and pull the bar down behind your neck, keeping your elbows pointed down.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together as you bring the bar down to the back of your neck.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position, extending your arms fully without locking your elbows. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Behind neck press Resistance band cable
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart, and a resistance band under your feet.
Step:2 Hold the ends of the band near your shoulders with your arms folded at the sides.
Step:3 Stretch the band by extending your arms overhead.
Step:4 As your arms become straight, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: Bench alternating step ups
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step up onto the bench with your right foot, then bring your left foot up to meet your right foot, standing fully on the bench.
Step:3 Step down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, and then repeat the movement with your left foot stepping up first.
Step:4 Continue alternating step ups on bench in a controlled, rhythmic manner.

name: Bench Bulgarian Split Squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench with your back to the bench.
Step:2 Extend one of your legs back and place the top of your foot on the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body into a squat by bending your other knee, keeping your torso upright.
Step:4 Push through your floored heel to return to the starting position, and repeat the movement.

name: Bench Bulgarian Split Squats left
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench with your back to the bench.
Step:2 Extend your left leg back and place the top of your foot on the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body into a squat by bending your right knee, keeping your torso upright.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, and repeat the movement.

name: Bench Bulgarian Split Squats Right
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench with your back to the bench.
Step:2 Extend your right leg back and place the top of your foot on the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body into a squat by bending your left knee, keeping your torso upright.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, and repeat the movement.

name: Bench decline ab sit-ups
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured under the foot pads.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your knees, performing a crunch.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement.

name: Bench dip (knees bent)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands placed on the bench beside your hips.
Step:2 Slide your hips off the bench, supporting your body with your hands, and bend your knees at a 90-degree angle with your feet flat on the floor.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your palms to raise your body back to the starting position.

name: Bench dip on floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench and place your hands on its edge near your hips.
Step:2 Walk your feet out, extend your legs, shift your weight on heels, and take your hips off the bench while holding the bench with straight arms.
Step:3 Lower your hips down by folding your arms and legs.
Step:4 As your arms form a 90-degree angle, raise your hips and repeat.

name: Bench knee tucks
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands placed beside your hips for support.
Step:2 Lean back slightly and lift your feet off the floor with your legs extended straight out.
Step:3 Pull your knees towards your chest, tucking them in while engaging your core.
Step:4 Extend your legs back out to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement.

name: Bench pull-ups
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under a pull-up bar with one foot placed on a bench for support.
Step:2 Grip the pull-up bar with both hands, using an overhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Pull your chest towards the bar, engaging your back and arm muscles.
Step:4 Lower yourself back down to the starting position in a controlled manner, keeping your core engaged.

name: Bench Reverse Plank Hold
instructions: Step:1 Place your feet on a bench with your legs extended and your hands on the floor directly under your shoulders, arms straight.
Step:2 Lift  your hips straight until torso comes parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Hold this position, keeping your core engaged and maintaining a straight line from head to heels.
Step:4 Maintain the hold for the designated period, focusing on stability and muscle engagement.

name: Bench triceps dip leg curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on a bench and place your hands on its edge near your hips.
Step:2 Walk your feet out, extend your legs, and lift your hips off the bench while holding the bench.
Step:3 Lower your hips down by folding your arms and bending your knees.
Step:4 As your arms form a 90-degree angle, raise your hips while extending your legs, and repeat.

name: Bench triceps dip straight legs
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on a bench and place your hands on the edge near your hips.
Step:2 Walk your feet out, straighten your legs, and lift your hips off the bench while holding the bench.
Step:3 Lower your hips down by folding your arms.
Step:4 As your arms form a 90-degree angle, raise your hips, and repeat.

name: Bent arm chest stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand beside a wall and place your bent arm (elbow at a 90-degree angle) against the wall, with your forearm and hand flat against the wall.
Step:2 Gently rotate your torso away from the wall to feel a stretch in your chest.
Step:3 Hold this position for 15-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Bent knee back to side kick
instructions: Step:1 Start on your hands and knees in a tabletop position, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right knee off the floor and extend it backward while keeping it bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Bring your right knee back down to the starting position.

Step:4 Lift your right knee out to the side until it is parallel to the floor, then return it to the starting position. Repeat the movement on the left side after completing the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent knee lying twist
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your arms extended out to the sides, forming a T shape.
Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the floor, bringing your upper legs vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Lower your bent knees to one side, keeping your torso and arms flat on the floor.
Step:4 Then bring your knees back to the center and lower them to the opposite side. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent knee lying twist (on stability ball)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on the floor with your arms extended out to the sides to form a T shape.
Step:2 Place your bent legs on top of an exercise ball.
Step:3 Lower your bent knees to one side, keeping your torso and arms flat on the floor.
Step:4 Then bring your knees back to the center and lower them to the opposite side. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent leg side kick (kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Start on your hands and knees in a tabletop position, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right knee off the floor in a swift motion and raise it sideways until it is level with your hip, keeping your leg bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Lower your right knee back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Bent over barbell row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips until your torso is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Let the barbell hang directly in front of you with your arms fully extended. Pull the barbell towards your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent over rear delt fly dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips until your torso is almost parallel to the floor. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang directly below you with your arms fully extended. Maintain a neutral spine throughout the movement.

Step:3 Lift the dumbbells out to the sides by raising your arms until they are in line with your shoulders. Keep a slight bend in your elbows and focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position by bringing your arms back down. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent over rear deltoid fly Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the ends of the resistance band anchored under your feet. Hinge at the hips with a slight bend in your knees to bring your torso almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Start with your arms hanging down towards the floor, palms facing back, and a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, forming a "T" shape, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and leading with your elbows. Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent over row Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles of a resistance band anchored under your feet. Hinge at the hips with a slight bend in your knees to bring your torso almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Start with your arms extended towards the floor, holding the band with your palms facing each other.
Step:3 Pull the handles of the band towards your hips by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position, extending your arms back towards the floor. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bent over twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a straight bar behind your neck with both hands.
Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent, until your torso is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Twist your torso to one side, bringing one end of the bar towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the other side.

name: Bent-over Row with bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips until your torso is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Let the bar hang directly in front of you with your arms fully extended. Pull the bar towards your abdomen by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:3 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bicep curl low cable machine normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a low cable crossover machine. Hold the handle attached to the low pulley with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands at shoulder-width apart, arms fully extended and elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Curl the handle upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps curl cable
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a low cable pulley. Hold the handle attached to the low pulley with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands at shoulder-width apart, arms fully extended and elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Curl the handle upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps curl cable wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a low cable pulley. Hold the handle attached to the low pulley with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands just wider than shoulder-width apart, arms fully extended and elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Curl the handle upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps curl cable wide grip crossover machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a low cable crossover machine. Hold the handle attached to the low pulley with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands just wider than shoulder-width apart, arms fully extended and elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Curl the handle upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps curl front step
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and extend both arms forward parallel to the floor with palms facing upwards.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and touch the floor lightly, while performing a biceps curl with both arms bending your elbows to bring your hands towards your shoulders.
Step:3 Bring your right foot back to the starting position while extending both arms and repeat alternating legs.

name: Biceps curl Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the middle of the resistance band under your feet. Hold the handles of the band with your palms facing forward and arms fully extended down by your sides.
Step:2 Keeping your elbows close to your torso, slowly curl the handles of the band towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the curl, holding for a brief moment to maximize contraction.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles of the band back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps curl to shoulder press Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the middle of the resistance band under your feet. Hold the handles of the band with your palms facing forward and arms fully extended down by your sides.
Step:2 Perform a biceps curl by bending your elbows and bringing the handles of the band towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your torso.
Step:3 From the biceps curl position, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward, and press the handles of the band overhead by extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Lower the handles back to the starting position by reversing the steps. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps leg concentration curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs apart and feet flat on the floor.
Step:2 Lean forward slightly and grab your hamstring with one hand, using your arm to support your leg.
Step:3 Perform a biceps curl by bending your elbow and lifting your leg towards your shoulder, using your biceps to curl your leg.
Step:4 Lower your leg back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Biceps stretch behind the back
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and clasp your hands together behind your back.
Step:2 Straighten your arms and pull your shoulders back to feel a stretch in your biceps.
Step:3 Keep your arms straight and maintain the stretch.
Step:4 Hold this position for 15-30 seconds, then return to the starting position.

name: Bicycle air legs
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back and lift your hips off the floor, supporting them with your hands while keeping your elbows on the floor.
Step:2 Perform a bicycle motion with your legs by extending your right leg straight forward while bending your left knee towards the floor.
Step:3 Switch legs by extending your left leg straight forward and bending your right knee towards the floor, continuing the bicycle motion.
Step:4 Maintain a controlled and steady pace throughout the exercise.

name: Bicycle twisting crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your legs raised at 45 degrees off the floor, keeping them straight.
Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your chest while twisting your torso, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee.
Step:3 Alternate sides, bringing your left knee towards your chest and your right elbow towards your left knee, continuing in a controlled, bicycle-like motion.

name: Bicycles
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs bent and lifted off the floor, and both arms straight to the floor.
Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your chest while straightening your left leg towards the floor without letting it touch the floor.
Step:3 Alternate sides by bringing your left knee towards your chest and straightening your right leg towards the floor, continuing in a controlled, bicycle-like motion.

name: Bicycles crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your legs lifted off the floor.
Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your chest while extending your left leg out.
Step:3 Simultaneously twist your torso, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee.
Step:4 Alternate sides, bringing your left knee towards your chest and your right elbow towards your left knee, continuing in a controlled, bicycle-like motion.

name: Bird dog
instructions: Step:1 Start in a tabletop position on your hands and knees, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Extend your left leg backward, toes extended back, and right arm forward simultaneously, keeping your extending arm straight, until both are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Hold this position briefly, maintaining balance and stability.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg.

name: Bird dog (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a tabletop position on your hands and knees, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Extend your left leg backward, and right arm forward simultaneously, keeping your extending arm straight, until both are slightly higher than torso level.
Step:3 Hold this position briefly, maintaining balance and stability.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg.

name: Boat stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and lift your legs off the floor, balancing on your buttocks.
Step:3 Extend your arms forward, parallel to the floor, to grab your legs and lean back slightly while keeping your back straight.
Step:4 Hold this position, maintaining balance.

name: Body saw plank
instructions: Step:1 Start in a forearm plank position, with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Rock your body back by pushing through your forearms, moving your shoulders behind your elbows level.
Step:3 Rock your body forward by pulling with your forearms, moving your shoulders in front of your elbows level.
Step:4 Repeat this controlled forward and backward motion.

name: Body slide
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and extend your arms straight out at shoulder level.
Step:2 Slide your hips to the left, keeping your upper body and arms steady.
Step:3 Slide your hips to the right, maintaining control and keeping your arms extended.
Step:4 Continue sliding your hips left and right in a controlled motion.

name: Body throw
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight and feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips to knee level, and extend your arms back at your sides.
Step:2 Push through your feet and raise yourself upright while raising your heels and extending your arms overhead.
Step:3 Return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Body-up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands placed directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your torso.
Step:3 Push through your palms to lift your body back up to the starting plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight bent over rear delt fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent, until your torso is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Allow your arms to hang straight down from your shoulders.
Step:3 Lift your arms out to the sides until they are in line with your shoulders, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Lower your arms back down in a controlled manner and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight calf raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides for balance.
Step:2 Lift your heels off the floor, rising onto your toes.
Step:3 Hold the top position briefly, squeezing your calf muscles.
Step:4 Lower your heels back to the floor in a controlled manner and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended by your sides for support. Place one foot on a box and cross the opposite ankle over the thigh of your working leg, forming a figure-four shape.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and squeeze them to lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from shoulders to knee.
Step:3 Pause at the peak of the movement for a second and slowly lower your hips back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge_Female
Bodyweight Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended by your sides for support. Place both feet on an elevated surface, with one foot flat and the other slightly forward so only the heel rests on the edge.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and squeeze them to lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from shoulders to knee.
Step:3 Pause at the peak of the movement for a second and slowly lower your hips back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge_Female
Bodyweight forward lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and lower your body by bending both knees, ensuring your front knee is aligned over your ankle and your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left foot stepping forward, alternating legs.

name: Bodyweight front slam
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and extend your hands overhead.
Step:2 Swing your arms down forcefully in front of your body, as if slamming a medicine ball to the floor, while simultaneously bending your knees into a squat position.
Step:3 Return to the starting position with hands extended overhead.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: bodyweight full squat with overhead front raise
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, your torso leaning slightly forward, and both arms extended between your thighs.
Step:2 Begin to straighten your legs to rise into a standing position while simultaneously raising both arms straight overhead.
Step:3 Fully extend your legs and arms, standing tall with your arms overhead.
Step:4 Lower your body back into the squat position, bringing your arms back down between your thighs. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight full squat with overhead front raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in close to your knees.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, while simultaneously raising your arms overhead.
Step:3 Stand back up to the starting position, lowering your arms back close to your knees.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight full squat with overhead press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended just in front of your knees.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Stand up from the squat while pressing your hands overhead, extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Lower your hands back down as you descend into the next squat. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight full squat with overhead press (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, your torso leaning slightly forward, and both hands just in front of your knees.
Step:2 Straighten your legs to rise into a standing position while simultaneously pressing your hands upwards until they are extended overhead.
Step:3 Fully extend your legs and arms, standing tall with your arms overhead.
Step:4 Lower your body back into the squat position, bringing your hands back down in front of your knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Hip Thrust
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your upper back resting against a bench and your knees bent, feet flat on the floor and shoulder-width apart. Cross your arms over your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and press through your heels to lift your hips upward until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, keeping your chin tucked slightly and your ribs down.
Step:4 Slowly lower your hips back down to the ground under control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight knee thrust
instructions: Step:1 Start in a partial lunge position with your left foot forward and right foot back, hands in front of your hips.
Step:2 Thrust your right knee forward and up to hip level, bringing your hands to meet your knee.
Step:3 Return to the partial lunge position, lowering your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Bodyweight kneeling hold to stand
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the floor with both knees, hands placed on your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right foot and place it flat on the floor in front of you, transitioning into a half-kneeling position.
Step:3 Push through your right foot to stand up fully, bringing your left foot to meet your right.
Step:4 Lower back down into the half-kneeling position, then return to the original kneeling position. Repeat with the other leg.

name: Bodyweight kneeling push-up row
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body on the floor.
Step:2 Push up by extending both arms, keeping your knees on the floor. Lift your right hand off the floor, performing a rowing motion by bringing your elbow up towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Return your right hand to the floor and lower your body to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight kneeling sissy squat
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling position with your knees on the floor and your torso upright.
Step:2 Lean back slowly, keeping your body straight from your knees to your head, engaging your quadriceps.
Step:3 Return to the upright kneeling position, repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions

name: Bodyweight kneeling to hand tap
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands just in front of your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards the middle of your hips while lightly rotating your torso to bring your left hand to touch the right knee.
Step:3 Lower your right leg back to the floor and return your hands to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left knee, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight kneeling triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling position with your knees on the floor. Place your hands on the floor in front of you opposite your head, close together, and lean forward.
Step:2 Bend your elbows to lower your forearms and head towards the floor, engaging your triceps.
Step:3 Push through your hands to extend your arms back to the starting position, straightening your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight lying leg curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your stomach while curling your arms at your chest and extend your legs on the floor.
Step:2 Bend your knees to lift your lower legs towards your glutes, engaging your hamstrings.
Step:3 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight muscle-up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight.
Step:2 Pull yourself up explosively, transitioning from a pull-up to a dip position above the bar.
Step:3 Push your body up until your arms are fully extended above the bar.
Step:4 Lower yourself back down to the starting hanging position in a controlled manner. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight overhead squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended overhead.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your arms extended overhead.
Step:3 Stand back up to the starting position, maintaining the arm position throughout.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Overhead Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended overhead with hands holding together, elbows slightly bent.
Step:2 Bend your elbows to lower your hands behind your head, engaging your triceps.
Step:3 Extend your arms back to the starting overhead position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight pulse forward lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position, ensuring your front knee is aligned over your ankle and your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:3 Perform small pulsing movements by slightly raising and lowering your body in the lunge position.
Step:4 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement on the other side.

name: Bodyweight pulse squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or extended in front of you.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, ensuring your thighs are parallel to the floor and your back is straight.
Step:3 Perform a small pulsing movement by slightly raising and lowering your body in the squat position.
Step:4 Return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight pulse squat arms to chest
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on crossed at your chest
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, ensuring your thighs are parallel to the floor and your back is straight.
Step:3 Perform a small pulsing movement by slightly raising and lowering your body in the squat position.
Step:4 Return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight rear lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides.
Step:2 Step backward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position, ensuring your front knee is aligned over your ankle and your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left foot stepping backward, alternating legs.

name: Bodyweight rear lunge front raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides.
Step:2 Step backward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position while simultaneously raising your arms in front of you to shoulder level.
Step:3 Ensure your front knee is aligned over your ankle and your back knee is close to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, lowering your arms back to your sides. Repeat the movement with your left foot stepping backward, alternating legs.

name: Bodyweight single leg deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your hands by your sides or on your hips.
Step:2 Lift your right leg straight back and lean forward at the hips, keeping your back straight, until your torso is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by lowering your right leg and raising your torso back to upright.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg

name: Bodyweight squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands extended in front of you for balance.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Stand back up to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight squat to front leg
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands extended down by your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Stand up from the squat and raise your right leg straight in front of you to hip level mimicking a kick, lower it down and immidiately raise your left leg to hip level.
Step:4 Lower your left leg back to the floor and repeat.

name: Bodyweight squat to side leg
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands extended by your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Stand up from the squat and raise your right leg as high as possible, kicking it to the side until straight.
Step:4 Lower your right leg back to the floor and immediately transition into the next squat, alternating legs with each repetition.

name: Bodyweight Squat to Side to Front Leg
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands at your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Stand up from the squat and raise your right leg straight to the side, then lower it back to the floor.
Step:4 Perform another squat, then stand up and raise your right leg straight to the front. Lower it back to the floor and repeat the movement, alternating legs with each repetition.

name: Bodyweight squats hold
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands crossed to your chest.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back.
Step:3 Hold the squat position for the desired duration, maintaining proper form throughout.
Step:4 Stand back up to the starting position by pressing through your heels and straightening your legs.

name: Bodyweight standing around world wall supported
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back against a wall for support.
Step:2 Extend your arms to the sides of your torso with palms facing forward.
Step:3 Move your arms in a circular motion, bringing them overhead, and back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing back stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and bring both arms straight behind your back, holding your hands together.
Step:2 Gently arch your back, pushing your hips forward and looking towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Hold the stretched position for a few seconds, maintaining a gentle and controlled stretch.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing calf raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides for balance.
Step:2 Rise up onto your toes, lifting your heels off the floor.
Step:3 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.
Step:4 Lower your heels back to the floor to return to the starting position.

name: Bodyweight standing fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended out to the sides, bent at 90 degrees, elbows at shoulder height.
Step:2 Bring your arms together in front of your body until your forearms meet.
Step:3 Open your arms back out to the sides to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing military press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, upper arms parallel to the floor, and arms bent at 90 degrees, fingers pointing at the ceiling.
Step:2 Press your hands upward, extending your arms fully overhead.
Step:3 Lower your hands back to shoulder level to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing military press wall supported
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back against a wall for support, upper arms parallel to the floor, and arms bent at 90 degrees, fingers pointing at the ceiling.
Step:2 Press your hands upward, extending your arms fully overhead.
Step:3 Lower your hands back to shoulder level to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place your hands on your hips.
Step:2 Raise your shoulders up towards your ears.
Step:3 Lower your shoulders back to the starting position and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight standing triangle fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place your hands behind your head, forming a triangle with your bent elbows, elbows facing outwards.
Step:2 Close your elbows together in front of you, bringing them towards each other.
Step:3 Open your elbows back out to the sides to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight step-up on step box
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart in front of a step box.
Step:2 Step up onto the box with your right foot, then bring your left foot up to meet your right, standing fully on the box.
Step:3 Step back down to the floor with your left foot, followed by your right foot.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating the lead foot.

name: Bodyweight svend press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands pressed together close to your chest, elbows bent.
Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping your hands pressed together.
Step:3 Bring your hands back to your chest, bending your elbows to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position on your toes and elbows, with your hands positioned at shoulder-width apart, palms on the floor.
Step:2 Push through your palms to extend your arms straight, keeping your palms in place.
Step:3 Lower your forearms to the floor back to the starting plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight wall squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and your feet shoulder-width apart, positioned a few inches away from the wall.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and hips, allowing your buttocks to touch the wall first, then your entire torso.
Step:3 Immediately push through your heels to stand back up, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder height.
Step:2 Bend at the waist, rotating your torso to touch your right hand to your left foot, while keeping your left arm extended upward.
Step:3 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the opposite side, touching your left hand to your right foot.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating sides.

name: Bodyweight windmill cut
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder height.
Step:2 Bend at the waist, rotating your torso to touch your right hand to your left foot 3-4 times in a pulsing motion, while keeping your left arm extended upward.
Step:3 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the opposite side, touching your left hand to your right foot.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating sides.

name: Both Arms Behind On Wall Biceps Stretch
Both Arms Behind On Wall Biceps Stretch_Female
Bottoms-up half rep
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended just off the floor and your arms resting on the floor by your sides.
Step:2 Bend your knees towards your chest, stopping when your upper legs are vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Lower your legs back down without letting them touch the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bouncing circle draw
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, legs slightly bent, and your hands lightly bent in front of your hips.
Step:2 Slowly straighten your legs while simultaneously drawing circles with your hands, moving them outward and upward.
Step:3 Encircle your hands inward, bringing them close together and downward as you bend your knees back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Bouncing inner thigh tap
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended by your sides at shoulder level.
Step:2 Rotate your torso to touch the inside of your right thigh with your left hand, slightly bending your knees as you do so.
Step:3 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the opposite side, rotating your torso to touch the inside of your left thigh with your right hand, slightly bending your knees.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Box jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart in front of a box.
Step:2 Bend your knees and hips, swinging your arms back to prepare for the jump.
Step:3 Explosively jump onto the box, landing softly with both feet.
Step:4 Stand up fully on the box before stepping or jumping back down to the starting position.

name: Box jump squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart in front of a box.
Step:2 Bend your knees and hips, swinging your arms back to prepare for the jump.
Step:3 Explosively jump onto the box, landing softly in a squat position.
Step:4 Jump back down to the floor, returning to the starting position and repeat.

name: Boxing jab
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Extend your left arm forward in a quick, snapping motion to throw a jab.
Step:3 Quickly retract your left arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Boxing left hook
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Rotate your hips and shoulders, bringing your left arm in a horizontal arc to throw a hook.
Step:3 Quickly retract your left arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Boxing left uppercut
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and rotate your hips and shoulders, bringing your left fist upward in a rising arc to throw an uppercut.
Step:3 Quickly retract your left arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Boxing right cross
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Rotate your hips and shoulders, extending your right arm forward in a straight line to throw a cross.
Step:3 Quickly retract your right arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Boxing right hook
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Rotate your hips and shoulders, bringing your right arm in a horizontal arc to throw a hook.
Step:3 Quickly retract your right arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Boxing right uppercut
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a boxing stance with your feet shoulder-width apart, left foot forward, and hands up in a guard position near your chin.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and rotate your hips and shoulders, bringing your right fist upward in a rising arc to throw an uppercut.
Step:3 Quickly retract your right arm back to the guard position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Brazilian crunches
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position on your toes and hands, arms straight in line with shoulders, with your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your left elbow while lightly rotating your hips. Return your leg to starting position.

Step:3 Repeat the movement on the opposite side, bending your left knee and bringing it towards your right elbow while lightly rotating your hips. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bridge - Mountain Climber (Cross Body)
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position on your toes and hands, with your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your left elbow while lightly rotating your hips, stop when your knee passes the elbow.
Step:3 Return to the starting plank position, then repeat the movement on the opposite side.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bridge hip abduction
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your knees bent, feet flat on the floor at shoulder width, and arms extended by your sides.
Step:2 Lift your hips off the floor to form a straight line from your shoulders to your knees, engaging your glutes and core.
Step:3 While keeping your hips elevated, move your knees outwards in a controlled manner and back.
Step:4 Repeat the movement  for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bridge pose setu bandhasana
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back with your knees bent, feet together on the floor, and arms resting at your sides.
Step:2 Raise your hips and straighten your thighs with your back while your knees are closed.
Step:3 Maintain this position, raise your arms and then land them overhead with your palms facing upward.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat.

name: Bridge with alternating leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your knees bent, feet flat on the floor, and arms resting by your sides.
Step:2 Lift your hips off the floor to form a straight line from your shoulders to your knees, engaging your glutes and core.
Step:3 While keeping your hips elevated, extend your right leg straight keeping it in level with torso, then lower it back to the starting position.

Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, extending it straight keeping it in level with torso, then lowering it back to the starting position. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Briskly walking
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Begin walking at a brisk pace, ensuring that you take quick, short steps.
Step:3 Swing your arms naturally with each step, allowing them to move opposite to your legs for balance.
Step:4 Maintain this brisk pace for the desired duration or distance.

name: Briskly Walking (360 degrees)
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Begin walking at a brisk pace, ensuring that you take quick, short steps.
Step:3 Swing your arms naturally with each step, allowing them to move opposite to your legs for balance.
Step:4 Maintain this brisk pace for the desired duration or distance.

name: Bulgarian split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your left foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your right foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Bulgarian split squat bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your left foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your right foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: bulgarian split squat bodyweight left
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your right foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your left foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your left knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your left thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: bulgarian split squat bodyweight right
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your left foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your right foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Bulgarian split squat cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Place one foot behind you on a bench or step, with your other foot forward. Secure the resistance band under your front foot.
Step:2 Hold the handles of the resistance band with your palms facing forward, elbows bent, and hands raised near your shoulders. Keep your arms folded by your sides.
Step:3 Lower your body towards the floor by bending the front knee, stopping just before your back knee touches the floor
Step:4 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions before switching legs.

name: Bulgarian split squat left bodyweight side view
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your right foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your left foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your left knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your left thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: bulgarian split squat right bodyweight side view
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a bench or elevated surface, facing away from it. Place your left foot behind you on the bench, with the top of your foot resting on the surface.
Step:2 Position your right foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the bench.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Burpee
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position and place your hands on the floor in front of you.
Step:3 Jump your feet back to land in a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:4 Perform a push-up, then jump your feet back towards your hands.
Step:5 Explode into a jump straight up, reaching your arms overhead. Land softly and immediately lower back into the squat position to begin the next repetition.

name: Burpee squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides, ready to begin the movement.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position and place your hands on the floor in front of you.
Step:3 Step your right foot back, then your left foot, to land in a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:4 Step your right foot forward, then your left foot, to return to the squat position, then stand up and repeat.

name: Butt kick with row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you, palms facing down.
Step:2 Bend your right knee to bring your heel towards your buttocks while simultaneously pulling your elbows back to perform a rowing motion.
Step:3 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left leg, bringing your left heel towards your buttocks while pulling your elbows back.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Butt kicks
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Begin by jogging in place, lifting your heels towards your buttocks with each step.

Step:3 Alternate lifting your right and left heels in a quick, continuous motion, keeping your knees pointing down. Swing your arms naturally with each step, allowing them to move opposite to your legs for balance.
Step:4 Maintain a steady pace for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Butt kicks slow
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Begin by jogging in place, lifting your heels towards your buttocks with each step.

Step:3 Alternate lifting your right and left heels in a quick, continuous motion, keeping your knees pointing down. Swing your arms naturally with each step, allowing them to move opposite to your legs for balance.
Step:4 Maintain a steady pace for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Butterfly yoga flaps
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs bent and the soles of your feet pressed together, allowing your knees to fall out to the sides.
Step:2 Hold your feet with both hands and sit up tall, lengthening your spine.
Step:3 Gently flap your knees up and down like the wings of a butterfly, keeping your movements smooth and controlled.
Step:4 Continue the flapping motion for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Butterfly yoga pose
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs bent and the soles of your feet pressed together, allowing your knees to fall out to the sides.
Step:2 Hold your feet with both hands and sit up tall, then lean forward slightly towards the floor, creating a gentle arch in your back.
Step:3 Press your knees gently towards the floor to deepen the stretch in your hips.
Step:4 Hold the position for the desired duration, breathing deeply and evenly throughout.

name: Cable alternate triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back facing the low pulley, holding the handle behind your head with your arm bent, elbow pointing up and palm facing the ceiling. Use your other hand to support the active arm by holding it just above the elbow.
Step:2 Extend your active arm up overhead, straightening your elbow to push the handle upward.
Step:3 Slowly return your arm to the starting position behind your head. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable assisted inverse leg curl
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the seat of a cable pulldown machine with both legs secured under the thigh pads. Face away from the machine and hold the cable bar behind your neck with both hands.
Step:2 Lean forward to straighten your legs until your torso is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position by bringing your upper body back up, bending at the knees.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable bar lateral pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a cable pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar with a wide overhand grip, your arms fully extended overhead.
Step:2 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:3 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, bringing your elbows down and back.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position with your arms fully extended overhead. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable bench fly press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench positioned between two cable machines, with the cables set at a low position. Grasp the handles with your arms bent and hands close to your chest sides.
Step:2 Press the handles upward in an arc motion over your chest, extending your arms upward.
Step:3 Lower the handles back down to the starting position, stopping when your hands are close to your chest sides.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench positioned between two pulley cables, with the cables set at a low position.
Step:2 Grasp the handles with your arms bent and hands close to your chest sides.
Step:3 Press the handles upward in a straight line over your chest, extending your arms fully.
Step:4 Lower the handles back down to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions

name: Cable bent over one arm lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand to the side of the machine with your right side facing it, and grasp the handle with the left hand, allowing the cable to cross in front of your body.
Step:2 Bend at the hips until your upper body is nearly parallel to the floor, keeping your knees slightly bent and your back flat. Let the arm holding the handle hang straight down.
Step:3 Raise the handle out to the side until your hand is at shoulder level, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable bent over reverse grip row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing the machine and grasp the bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend at the hips to form a 90 degree angle with your upper body, keeping your knees slightly bent. Let your arms extend with the cable, holding the bar.
Step:3 Pull the bar towards your lower abdomen, bringing your elbows backwards.
Step:4 Slowly extend the bar back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing the machine and grasp the bar with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend at the hips to form a 90 degree angle with your upper body, keeping your knees slightly bent. Let your arms extend with the cable, holding the bar.
Step:3 Pull the bar towards your lower abdomen, bringing your elbows backwards.
Step:4 Slowly extend the bar back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable biceps curl (EZ bar)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the pulley machine and grasp the EZ-bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and core engaged. Hold the bar extending in front of your thighs.
Step:3 Curl the bar upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows. Keeping your upper arms stationary and focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with your arms fully extended. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Calve Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a low cable pulley with a straight bar attachment, with your feet hip-width apart, holding the bar in front of your hips with both hands.
Step:2 Push through your forefeet to raise your heels as high as possible.
Step:3 Pause for a second at the peak of the movement and then slowly lower your heels back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Cable close grip curl
