instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the pulley machine and grasp the bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands closer than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and core engaged. Hold the bar extending in front of your thighs.
Step:3 Curl the bar upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows. Keeping your upper arms stationary and focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with your arms fully extended. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable close grip front lat pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar attached to the machine with your arms fully extended above you, hands closer than shoulder-width and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, bringing your elbows down and back while slightly leaning back.
Step:3 Slowly return the handle to the starting position with your arms fully extended overhead.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable front raises straight bar
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing away from the machine, with your feet shoulder-width apart and the bar held with an overhand grip, palms facing down.
Step:2 Stand upright with your back straight and core engaged. Let the bar hang down in front of your thighs with your arms fully extended and the cable passing between your legs.
Step:3 Raise the bar in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your arms straight but with a slight bend in the elbows.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a bar attachment with both hands at chest level with elbows facing the floor.
Step:2 Begin squatting by bending your hips and knees, descend into a deep squat until your thighs are parallel to the ground or lower.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Cable Hamstring Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach an ankle strap to a low pulley and secure it around your working ankle, then stand upright facing the machine and hold onto a stable surface or clasp your hands together for balance.
Step:2 Keep your upper body stationary and your knees aligned as you slowly bend your working knee, curling your foot up toward your glutes.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, focusing on squeezing your hamstring.
Step:4 Lower your foot back down to the starting position with control and repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching legs.

name: Cable Individual Glute Kickbacks
instructions: Step:1 Attach an ankle strap to a low pulley on a cable machine and secure it around one ankle. Stand facing the machine and hold onto the handles or frame for support while keeping your torso leaning slightly forward.
Step:2 Engage your core and shift your weight onto the stationary leg while slightly bending the knee of the supporting leg.
Step:3 Extend the strapped leg straight back in a controlled motion, squeezing your glute at the top without hyperextending your lower back.
Step:4 Slowly return your leg to the starting position without letting the weight stack touch, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching sides.

name: Cable lateral raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a cable machine with the handles attached to the low pulleys on either side, with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the left handle with your right hand and the right handle with your left hand, with the cables crossing in front of you. Stand
Step:2 Stand upright with your back straight. Let the handles hang down in front of your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:3 Raise the handles out to your sides until your arms are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable leaning lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand next to the machine on your left side, holding the handle with your right hand. Lean away from the machine, using your left hand to hold onto the machine for support.
Step:2 Position your feet together, with your outside foot slightly in front for better stability. Let the handle hang down at your side with your arm fully extended.
Step:3 Raise the handle out to the side until your arm is parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable low fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable machine with the pulleys set at a low position. Grasp the handles with your palms facing forward and arms extended down out to your sides. Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly staggered for stability.
Step:2 Stand upright with your back straight. Bring the handles together in front of your body in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and palms should face upwards.
Step:3 Slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable low seated row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the pulldown machine with your feet placed securely under the knee pads. Grasp the bar with both hands, hands at shoulder-width apart and palms facing down.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight and core engaged, extending your arms fully in front of you.
Step:3 Pull the bar towards your lower abdomen, bringing your elbows back and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: cable lying extension pullover (with cables attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach both cable handles to a single low pulley. Lie on a flat bench with your head positioned near the pulley. Grasp the handles with your palms facing up and your arms extended in line with your body.
Step:2 Keep your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed against the bench. Engage your core to maintain stability.
Step:3 Raise the handles in an arc motion over your head, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Lower the handles back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable lying fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench between a dual crossover machine and your feet flat on the floor. Grasp the handles with your palms facing up and arms extended to the sides at chest level.
Step:2 Raise the handles over your chest in a wide arc motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by lowering the handles out to your sides in a wide arc motion.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable lying triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the middle pulley of a cable machine. Lie on a flat bench with your head positioned near the pulley. Grasp the bar or rope with an overhand grip, your arms extended straight up above your chest.
Step:2 Lower the bar towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Just before touching your forehead, extend your arms back to the starting position, focusing on contracting your triceps.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable lying triceps extension (low)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the low pulley of a cable machine. Lie on a flat bench with your head positioned near the pulley. Grasp the bar or rope with an overhand grip, your arms extended straight up above your chest.
Step:2 Lower the bar towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Just before touching your forehead, extend your arms back to the starting position, focusing on contracting your triceps.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable machine high to low
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable machine with the pulleys set at a high position. Grasp the handles with your palms facing forward and arms extended down out to your sides. Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly staggered for stability.
Step:2 Stand upright with your back straight. Bring the handles together in front of your body in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and palms should face upwards.
Step:3 Slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable middle fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable fly machine with the pulleys set at mid-chest height, with one foot in front of the other and knees slightly bent. Hold the handles with both hands, arms extended out to the sides at shoulder height, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Keep your back straight and maintain a slight bend at the hips and knees for stability.
Step:3 Pull the handles together in front of your chest in a wide arc, keeping your arms slightly bent, until your hands meet in the centerline of your chest.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable narrow chair stand-up
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to the low pulley on the machine. Grasp the end of the rope in each hand and bring it close to your chest.Feet close together, flat on the floor, knees bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Push through your heels and extend your legs to stand up, keeping the handles close to your chest.
Step:3 Slowly lower yourself back down to the seated position, controlling the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable neutral grip kickback
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a middle pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing the machine and grasp the handle with your left hand, using a neutral grip (palm facing your body). Step back to create tension in the cable.

Step:2 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and bend slightly at the hips, keeping your back straight and core engaged. Your upper arm should be parallel to the floor and close to your body with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Extend your left arm straight back by straightening your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary and focusing on contracting your triceps.
Step:4 Slowly return your arm to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your right hand.

name: Cable one arm bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing the machine, holding the handle with your left hand. Step back with one foot to create tension in the cable.
Step:2 Bend at the hips slightly to the floor, keeping your knees bent and your back flat. Place your right hand on your right knee for support.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your lower abdomen, bringing your elbow back. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your right hand.

name: Cable One Arm Chest Fly Bent
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable fly machine with the pulleys set at mid-chest height, with feet just wider than shoulder-width and bend at the hips and knees and lean towards the floor. Place your left hand to your knee for support.

Step:2 Hold the handle with your right hand, arm extended out to the side at shoulder height, palm facing forward. Bring the handle opposite your chest in a wide arc motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly return the handles to the starting position, maintaining control and the bend in your elbow.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable one arm curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing the machine, holding the handle with your right hand, palm facing forward.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight. Let your arm fully extend down by your side.
Step:3 Curl the handle upwards towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary and close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable one arm front raise
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a low pulley on a cable machine. Stand facing away from the machine, holding the handle with your right hand, palm facing back. Step forward to create tension in the cable.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight. Let your arm fully extend down by your side.
Step:3 Raise the handle straight in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your arm straight but with a slight bend in the elbow.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable one arm inner biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight, with your right side facing the machine, holding the handle with your right hand, arm extended at shoulder height parallel to the floor, palm facing up.
Step:2 Curl the handle towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary and parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable one arm lat pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the handle attached to the high pulley with your right hand, arm fully extended above you, palm facing forward.
Step:2 Pull the handle down towards your right shoulder, bringing your elbow down while slightly leaning back.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable overhead curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable machine with the pulleys set at the highest position. Grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing upward. Extend your arms out to the sides at shoulder height, almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Curl the handles towards your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable overhead extension rope
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to the high pulley on a cable machine. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, back to the machine, and grasp the rope handle with both hands, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Step forward to create tension in the cable. Extend your arms straight in level with your torso, keeping your elbows close to your head.
Step:3 Lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable palm rotational row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. Attach a single handle to a middle pulley and hold it with your right hand, palm facing downwards.
Step:2 Bend slightly at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight, and extend your right arm forward.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your palm to face upwards as you bring your elbow back, keeping it close to your torso.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position, rotating your palm back to face inwards. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable preacher curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor. Attach a straight bar to the low pulley of a cable machine and grasp the bar with both hands, shoulder-width apart, palms facing upwards.
Step:2 Position your upper arms on the preacher bench pad and extend your arms fully, holding the bar.
Step:3 Curl the bar towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable pull through
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a cable pulley machine with a rope attached at a low position. Hold the handles between your thighs with your back facing the machine, and the cables extending back.
Step:2 Spread your feet just wider than shoulder-width, lean forward, bending at the hips and knees into a semi-squat position, while keeping your back straight and your arms extended.
Step:3 Extend your hips forward to straighten your body, pushing the handles with your thighs.
Step:4 Return to the starting semi-squat position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the cable pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar attached to the high pulley with an overhand grip, hands placed at shoulder-width, arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, bringing your elbows down and back while keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable pulldown (pro lat bar)
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the cable pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the Pro Lat Bar attached to the high pulley with an overhand grip, hands placed wider than shoulder-width, arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, bringing your elbows down and back while keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and lean slightly forward, keeping your back straight and elbows close to your body. Your forearms should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable pushdown (straight arm)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms slightly bent throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable rear delt fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable machine with the pulleys set at chest height. Cross the cable ends and hold the left cable end with your right hand and the right cable end with your left hand, arms extended in front of you.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Pull the handles apart and out to the sides, keeping your arms straight but with a slight bend in the elbows, until your arms are extended out to your sides.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, bringing the handles back in front of you. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable rear drive
instructions: Step:1 Stand straight with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. Set the pulley at shoulder height and grasp the handle of the cable with your right hand, palm facing down. Set your arm parallel to the floor in front of you and bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Drive your elbow sideways while slowly straightening your arm, pulling the cable across your chest.
Step:3 Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable rear drive bent arm
instructions: Step:1 Stand straight with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. Set the pulley at shoulder height and grasp the handle of the cable with your right hand, palm facing down. Set your arm parallel to the floor in front of you and bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Drive your elbow sideways, keeping your arm bent at 90 degrees, pulling the cable across your chest.
Step:3 Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable rear pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the cable pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Attach a straight bar to the high pulley and grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing forward, hands wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Lean your head slightly forward, keeping your back straight and core tight. Extend your arms fully above your head.
Step:3 Pull the bar down behind your neck by bending your elbows and bringing them down to the sides.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms up to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and arms fully extended down in front of you.
Step:3 Curl the bar upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable crossover machine with the pulleys set at shoulder height. Cross the cable ends and hold the left cable end with your right hand and the right cable end with your left hand, arms extended in front of you.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Pull the handles apart and out to the sides, keeping your arms straight but with a slight bend in the elbows, until your arms are extended out to your sides.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, bringing the handles back in front of you. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse grip pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and elbows close to your body. Your forearms should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, allowing your forearms to become parallel to the floor again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse grip straight back seated high row
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Attach a straight bar to the high pulley and grasp the bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing back), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight and arms fully extended above your head.
Step:3 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by bending your elbows and bringing them down and back, keeping your upper arms close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse grip triceps push down straight bar on crossover
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and elbows close to your body. Your forearms should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, allowing your forearms to become parallel to the floor again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse grip triceps pushdown (EZ bar)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight an EZ bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the EZ bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and elbows close to your body. Your forearms should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the EZ bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, allowing your forearms to become parallel to the floor again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable reverse grip triceps pushdown back side POV
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and elbows close to your body. Your forearms should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, allowing your forearms to become parallel to the floor again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable seated on floor row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor facing a cable machine with your legs extended straight out in front of you. Attach a straight bar to the low pulley and grasp the bar with both hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing down.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight and arms fully extended towards the machine. Bend your knees slightly for comfort.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your lower abdomen by bending your elbows and bringing them backwards, keeping your upper arms close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable seated one arm alternate row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seated cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and knees slightly bent. Attach a single handle to the low pulley and grasp the handle with your right hand, arm fully extended towards the machine.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight, keeping your left hand on your left knee for support.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your lower abdomen by bending your elbow and bringing it back, keeping your upper arm close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Cable seated rear lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench in the middle of a cable machine with the pulleys set at the lowest position. Attach single handles to each pulley and grasp the left handle with your right hand and the right handle with your left hand, allowing the cables to cross under your thighs.
Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight, so your chest is close to your knees.
Step:3 Raise both handles out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable seated row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seated pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor. Attach a V-bar handle to the low pulley and grasp the handle with both hands, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight and arms fully extended towards the machine.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your lower abdomen by bending your elbows and bringing them backwards, keeping your upper arms close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Row With V Bar
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seated cable machine with your feet flat on the floor. Attach a V handle to the pulley and grasp the handle with both hands, arms fully extended towards the machine.
Step:2 Lean slightly forward, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your abdomen by bending your elbows and bringing it back while raising your torso to a seated position, keeping your arms close to your body.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions

name: Cable seated supine grip row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seated pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor. Attach a straight bar to the middle pulley and grasp the bar with both hands using a supine grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight and arms fully extended towards the machine.
Step:3 Pull the bar towards your lower abdomen by bending your elbows and bringing them back, keeping your upper arms close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley and stand facing the cable while holding the bar with both hands. Shift your weight onto your right leg, keeping it bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Slightly bend your standing knee and hinge at the hips to lower your torso to the floor.
Step:3 Once your torso is nearly parallel to the floor. Drive through your standing leg to return to the starting position
Step:4 Lower your foot to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Cable Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a low pulley cable machine with a bar attached and grab it with both hands using an overhand grip. Take a step back into a split stance with one foot forward and one foot behind.
Step:2 Hold the bar extended along the cable and keep your torso upright.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending both knees until your thigh is parallel to the floor. Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Leg Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach an ankle strap to a high pulley and secure it around your right ankle. Stand facing away from the machine and hold onto a stable surface for balance.
Step:2 Bend the knee of the strapped leg so your heel is close to your glutes.
Step:3 Slowly extend your leg by straightening the knee and then return it to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Cable standing up straight crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable crossover machine with the pulleys set at the highest point. Grasp the handles with each hand, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart with one foot forward and the other back and knees slightly bent. Keep your back straight and arms extended out to your sides.
Step:3 Pull the handles down and forward until they meet in front of your hips. Keep a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly return your arms to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable straight arm pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands shoulder-width apart.

Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, lean your torso slightly forward and keep your back straight and a slight bend in your knees. Extend your arms fully in front of you at shoulder height.
Step:3 Pull the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, bringing it back to shoulder height. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps overhead extension (ez bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach an EZ bar to the high pulley of a cable machine. Stand with your back facing the machine, feet shoulder-width apart, and grasp the EZ bar with both hands, palms facing up.

Step:2 Step forward slightly to create tension in the cable and position your feet in a staggered stance for stability. Extend your arms straight up above your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears.
Step:3 Lower the EZ bar behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down elbow out (v bar)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight, knees slightly bent and lean slightly forward.

Step:2 Grasp the V-bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing each other, and place your hands shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, with your elbows flared out to the sides.
Step:3 Push the V-bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms close to your torso.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down ez bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent.

Step:2 Grasp the EZ bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Push the EZ bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down ez bar close grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent.

Step:2 Grasp the EZ bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands closer than shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Push the EZ bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down ez bar wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent.

Step:2 Grasp the EZ bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Push the EZ bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down straight bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent.

Step:2 Grasp the straight bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Push the bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable triceps push down v bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent.

Step:2 Grasp the v bar attached to the high pulley with both hands, palms facing down, and place your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Push the v bar down towards your thighs by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable twin handle parallel grip lat pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Sit upright on a bench positioned between two cable pulley machines with the pulleys set at a high position. Hold a handle in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the handles down towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and bringing them downwards, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand sideways to the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Attach a handle to the pulley at shoulder height and grasp it with both hands, arms extended in front of you.
Step:2 Twist your torso away from the machine, pulling the handle across your body while keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable twist (up-down)
instructions: Step:1 Stand sideways to the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Attach a handle to the high pulley and grasp it with both hands, arms extended diagonally along the cable.
Step:2 Twist your torso down and across your body, pulling the handle down towards your opposite hip while keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable twisting overhead press
instructions: Step:1 Stand sideways to the cable machine with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, knees bent at almost 90 degrees and hips pushed back.
Step:2 Grasp the handle, attached at hip height, with the hand closest to the machine, keeping it close to your shoulder. Place your other hand on your hip.
Step:3 Twist your torso away from the machine while pushing the handle sideways and straight across your torso, straightening your legs to a standing position as you press the handle.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting semi-squat position with control, bringing the handle back to your shoulder. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable twisting pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with the left foot forward and the right foot back, knees bent. Attach a handle to the low pulley and grasp it with the right hand, palm facing down. Lean forward so your upper body is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Extend your arm fully towards the pulley, keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your torso, rotating your wrist as you pull until your palm faces the ceiling.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Underhand Pulldown Wide Grips
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Attach a wide grip bar to the high pulley and grasp it with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing back), hands wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by bending your elbows and bringing them down and back.
Step:3 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upper Chest Crossover
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable crossover machine with the pulleys set at the lowest point. Grasp the handles with each hand, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent.
Step:3 Pull the handles up and forward until they meet over your chest.
Step:4 Slowly return your arms to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Cable upright row with EZ bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine with an EZ bar attached to the low pulley. Grasp the EZ bar with both hands using an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Pull the EZ bar upwards towards your chin by bending your elbows and raising your upper arms, leading with your elbows, keeping the bar close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable upright row with straight bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Pull the bar upwards towards your chin by bending your elbows and raising your upper arms, leading with your elbows, keeping the bar close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable wrist curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing the cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley. Grasp the bar with both hands using an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs with your wrists just beyond your knees, allowing the bar to hang down.
Step:3 Curl the bar upwards by flexing your wrists, bringing the bar towards your forearms.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Y raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with the pulleys set at the lowest position. Grasp a handle in each hand, holding the left handle with your right hand and the right handle with your left hand, so the cables cross in front of you.
Step:2 Take a step back and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and arms extended down in front of you.
Step:3 Raise the handles up and out to form a "Y" shape, keeping your arms straight but with a slight bend in the elbows. Lift until your arms are overhead.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf push stretch with hands against wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height and shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step your right foot back and keep on your toes, keeping your leg straight and bring your left leg close to the wall, touching it with your forefoot.
Step:3 Press your back heel flat to the floor, pushing with your left forefoot against the wall to deepen the stretch in your calf.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Calf raise clap
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended out to the sides at shoulder level.
Step:2 Lift your heels off the floor as high as possible while simultaneously bringing your arms forward to clap, keeping them straight.
Step:3 Lower your heels back to the floor and return your arms to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf raise from deficit with chair supported
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a raised platform or step, with your heels hanging off the edge, and hold onto a chair for support.
Step:2 Position your feet hip-width apart, ensuring your toes are firmly on the platform.
Step:3 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, engaging your calf muscles and lifting your body.
Step:4 Lower your heels back down past the edge of the platform to feel a stretch in your calves. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf raise leg press machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet shoulder-width apart on the higher portion of the footplate with your toes pointing up.
Step:2 Press the footplate by extending your legs and keeping a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Push through your forefeet to raise the footplate as much as possible, squeezing your calf muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your forefeet down to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Calf raise leg press machine_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet shoulder-width apart on the higher portion of the footplate with your toes pointing up.
Step:2 Press the footplate by extending your legs and keeping a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Push through your forefeet to raise the footplate as much as possible, squeezing your calf muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your forefeet down to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Calf raise on hack squat machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the hack squat machine with your shoulders under the pads and your feet hips-width apart on the foot platform, with your toes pointing forward and your heels hanging off the edge.
Step:2 Extend your legs to release the safety handles, keeping a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Push through your forefeet to raise your heels as high as possible, squeezing your calf muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf raise on hack squat machine_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the hack squat machine with your shoulders under the pads and your feet hips-width apart on the foot platform, with your toes pointing forward and your heels hanging off the edge.
Step:2 Extend your legs to release the safety handles, keeping a slight bend in your knees.
Step:3 Push through your forefeet to raise your heels as high as possible, squeezing your calf muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf raise with wall support
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height for support.
Step:2 Position your feet flat on the floor, ensuring they are parallel to each other.
Step:3 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body and engaging your calf muscles.
Step:4 Lower your heels back to the floor in a controlled manner. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf stretch with hands against wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. Place your hands on the wall at shoulder height and shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Step one foot back, keeping your back leg straight and your front leg slightly bent. Press your back heel into the floor.
Step:3 Lean forward slightly, pushing against the wall to deepen the stretch in your calf.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Calf stretch with rope
instructions: Step:1 Lie on the floor with your legs extended straight on the floor. Pass a rope with handles under your right forefoot, holding the handles with both hands.
Step:2 Keep your back flat against the floor and gently pull the rope towards you, flexing your foot and bringing your toes towards your shin.
Step:3 Straighten your leg fully to deepen the stretch in your calf muscle.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release the rope and switch to the other foot, repeating the stretch.

name: Calve Stretch From Wall To Floor
Calve Stretch From Wall To Floor_Female
Calves stretch on stairs
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a step or stair with one foot on a higher step and the other foot on a lower step, ensuring the lower foot's heel is hanging off the edge.
Step:2 Hold onto the railing or wall for support to maintain balance.
Step:3 Slowly lower the heel of the lower foot below the level of the step until you feel a stretch in your calf muscle.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for the desired duration, then slowly raise your heel back to the starting position. Repeat as needed for both legs.

name: Captains chair leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the captain's chair and place your forearms on the arm pads, gripping the handles for stability. Allow your legs to hang straight down.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back pressed against the back pad.
Step:3 Raise your legs, knees first, up in front of you until your thighs are parallel to the floor and your feet are slightly forward.
Step:4 Slowly lower your knees back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Captains chair straight leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the captain's chair and place your forearms on the arm pads, gripping the handles for stability. Allow your legs to hang straight down.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back pressed against the back pad.
Step:3 Raise your legs straight up in front of you until they are parallel to the floor, keeping them as straight as possible.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cardio lunge
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a lunge position with your right leg forward and left leg back, ensuring your right knee is aligned over your ankle and your left knee is just above the floor. Bend both arms at your sides.
Step:2 Explosively push off your left foot, bringing it forward in a small step while pushing  your right leg slightly backwards.
Step:3 Immediately return your left foot back to the starting lunge position.
Step:4 Continue the explosive movement, maintaining a steady, rhythmic pace. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions or duration, then switch legs.

name: Cat stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin on your hands and knees in a tabletop position, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees aligned under your hips.
Step:2 Inhale deeply, then slowly arch your back upwards towards the ceiling, tucking your chin towards your chest and drawing your navel in towards your spine.
Step:3 Hold the arched position for a few seconds, feeling the stretch along your spine and back muscles.
Step:4 Exhale and slowly return to the starting tabletop position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ceiling look stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a tabletop position on all fours, with your wrists aligned under your shoulders and your knees aligned under your hips.
Step:2 Slowly lift your torso upwards, arching your back gently and leaning backward.
Step:3 Allow your hands to slide down to your legs, supporting your upper body as you look up towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration and slowly return to the starting tabletop position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Celebratory hip thrust
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight up in the air.
Step:2 Simultaneously bend your elbows and thrust your arms downwards to your hips while thrusting your hips forward.
Step:3 Return to the initial position with your arms extended overhead and your hips back in the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair back lunge left Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach one end of a resistance band to a sturdy chair or similar support and the other end to your left ankle. Stand facing the chair with your right foot firmly planted on the floor.

Step:2 Step back with your left foot, keeping your right foot in place, and lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees, ensuring your right knee is directly above your right ankle and your left knee is hovering just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: chair back lunge right Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach one end of a resistance band to a sturdy chair or similar support and the other end to your right ankle. Stand facing the chair with your left foot firmly planted on the floor.

Step:2 Step back with your right foot, keeping your left foot in place, and lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees, ensuring your left knee is directly above your left ankle and your right knee is hovering just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Chair Bulgarian split squats bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a chair, facing away from it. Place your one foot on the chair behind you, with the top of your foot resting on the seat.
Step:2 Position your other foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the chair.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your back knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your thigh is parallel to the floor and your knee is close to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your floored heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Chair Bulgarian Split Squats bodyweight left
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a chair, facing away from it. Place your left foot on the chair behind you, with the top of your foot resting on the seat.
Step:2 Position your right foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the chair.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee is close to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: chair Bulgarian Split Squats bodyweight right
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet in front of a chair, facing away from it. Place your right foot on the chair behind you, with the top of your foot resting on the seat.
Step:2 Position your left foot firmly on the floor, a comfortable distance in front of the chair.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your left knee and hip, keeping your torso upright, until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee is close to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Chair elevated single leg glute bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your left heel placed on the edge of a chair, your right leg extended bent up towards the ceiling.
Step:2 Position your arms by your sides with your palms facing down for stability.
Step:3 Engage your core and glutes to lift your hips off the floor.
Step:4 Hold the position briefly at the top, squeezing your glutes, then slowly lower your hips back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Chair feet elevated glute bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with both heels placed on the edge of a chair, legs bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Position your arms by your sides with your palms facing down for stability.
Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then lift your hips off the floor.
Step:4 Hold the position briefly at the top, squeezing your glutes, then slowly lower your hips back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair frog feet elevated glute bridge bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your heels placed on the edge of a chair, legs bent, and the soles of your feet touching each other in a frog position.
Step:2 Position your arms by your sides with your palms facing down for stability.
Step:3 Engage your core and glutes to lift your hips off the floor until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:4 Hold the position briefly at the top, squeezing your glutes, then slowly lower your hips back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair triceps dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your hands placed next to your hips, gripping the edge of the chair.
Step:2 Extend your legs out in front of you with your heels on the floor and your legs straight.
Step:3 Slide your hips off the chair and lower your body by bending your elbows until they form a 90-degree angle.
Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back up to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest bench press correct stance
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor, positioned so that your eyes are directly under the barbell. Grip the barbell with a slightly wider than shoulder-width grip, palms facing away from you, ensuring your hands are evenly spaced on the bar.
Step:2 Place your feet flat on the floor, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Engage your legs and glutes, pushing your feet into the floor to create a strong foundation.
Step:3 Maintain a natural arch in your lower back, keeping your shoulders and glutes in contact with the bench. Retract your shoulder blades and tuck them firmly into the bench for stability.

name: Chest dip
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping the parallel bars with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Lift your body off the floor and lean slightly forward, crossing your ankles behind you.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor, keeping your chest leaning forward to engage your chest muscles.
Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest dip (on dip station)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping the parallel bars of the dip pull-up cage with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Lift your body off the floor and lean slightly forward, crossing your ankles behind you for balance.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor, keeping your chest leaning forward to engage your chest muscles.
Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest dip machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the seated chest dip machine and firmly grasp the handles with both hands.
Step:2 Position your feet flat on the floor, keeping your chest up and shoulders back.
Step:3 Push the handles downwards by extending your elbows, until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest dip on bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands placed next to your hips, gripping the edge of the bench.
Step:2 Extend your legs out in front of you with your heels on the floor and your legs straight.
Step:3 Slide your hips off the bench and lower your body by bending your elbows until they form a 90-degree angle, leaning your chest slightly forward to engage your chest muscles.
Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back up to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest dip weighted
instructions: Step:1 Grip the dip bars firmly with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended. Position your body slightly forward, with your legs bent and crossed at the ankles, holding weights.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows, allowing them to flare out slightly to the sides. Lower yourself until your upper arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Maintain the forward lean throughout the movement to keep the focus on your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest dip weighted slow
instructions: Step:1 Grip the dip bars firmly with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended. Position your body slightly forward, with your legs bent and crossed at the ankles, holding weights.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body by bending your elbows, allowing them to flare out slightly to the sides. Lower yourself in a controlled manner until your upper arms are parallel to the floor.

Step:3 Push through your palms to slowly extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Maintain the forward lean throughout the movement to keep the focus on your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a slow and controlled pace throughout the exercise.

name: Chest dip with pause bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping the parallel bars with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended to lift your body off the floor and lean slightly forward, crossing your ankles behind you for balance.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor, keeping your chest leaning forward to engage your chest muscles.

Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Pause in the upper position for a few seconds, allowing for a couple seconds of rest. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest fly high to low Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a low anchor point behind you. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing up.
Step:2 Position one leg forward and the other back, with both knees slightly bent, keeping your back straight and your arms extended down and slightly behind you.
Step:3 Raise the handles up and together in a wide arc, bringing them to meet at head level while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest fly low to high Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a high anchor point behind you. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Position one leg forward and the other back, with both knees slightly bent. Keep your back straight and your arms extended out to the sides at head height.
Step:3 Bring the handles down and together in a wide arc, meeting in front of your lower abdomen while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly raise your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest fly side step
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms bent at 90 degrees, and your elbows open wide at shoulder height.
Step:2 Step your right foot out to the side, bending your right knee slightly as you bring your elbows together in front of you until they are close together and back.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by stepping your left foot out to the side while repeating the fly motion with your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest lift with rotation
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows wide.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body into a crunch position, holding the contraction at the top.
Step:3 While holding the crunch, rotate your torso to the right. Return to the center.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the floor, then repeat the movement, this time rotating to the left. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest out hands behind (hold)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and shoulders relaxed.
Step:2 Interlace your fingers behind your back, extending your arms straight.
Step:3 Lift your arms slightly while pushing your chest out and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, maintaining a steady and controlled breath throughout the stretch.

name: Chest press front Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point behind you at chest height. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing down.
Step:2 Position one leg forward and the other back, with both knees slightly bent. Start with your elbows bent at 90 degrees, your hands at chest level, and your arms parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest press high to low cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a high anchor point behind you. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing down.
Step:2 Position one leg forward and the other back, with both knees slightly bent.Start with your elbows bent at 90 degrees and your hands at your chest sides.
Step:3 Push the handles forward and down in a diagonal motion until your arms are fully extended and hands facing your hips.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest press low to high Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a low anchor point behind you. Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing down.
Step:2 Position one leg forward and the other back, with both knees slightly bent. Start with your elbows bent and your hands close to your chest sides.
Step:3 Push the handles forward and up in a diagonal motion until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Press Machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the chest press machine with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the backrest. Grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing forward, and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Push the handles forward and extend your arms fully, keeping a slight bend in your elbows to avoid locking them.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows and bringing the handles back towards your chest.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Press Machine_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the chest press machine with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the backrest. Grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing forward, and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Push the handles forward and extend your arms fully, keeping a slight bend in your elbows to avoid locking them.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows and bringing the handles back towards your chest.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest pull back
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and leaning slightly forward at the hips. Bend your arms in front of your chest with your palms facing each other, lightly squeezing to activate your chest.
Step:2 Perform a rowing motion with your right arm by pulling it back, bending your elbow, and squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine.
Step:3 Return your right arm to the starting position, keeping your left arm steady and engaged in front of your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the rowing motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest raise and rotate
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms bent at 90 degrees, with forearms parallel to the floor, elbows squeezed to the sides.
Step:2 Perform a semi-circular motion by rotating your arms upwards and outwards until your forearms are vertical to the floor and your upper arms are at shoulder level.
Step:3 Reverse the motion, bringing your arms back to the starting position with your forearms parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest stretch with exercise ball
instructions: Step:1 Begin on all fours, with your knees directly under your hips and your hands directly under your shoulders.
Step:2 Place your right forearm on an exercise ball positioned to your side, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Slowly lower your chest towards the floor to deepen the stretch in your chest.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, then return to the starting position and switch arms to repeat the stretch on the other side.

name: Chest tap push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the floor, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Explosively push through your palms to lift your body back up, lifting both hands off the floor at the top of the movement.
Step:4 While in the air, tap your chest with both hands, then quickly place your hands back on the floor and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Child pose
instructions: Step:1 Begin by kneeling on the floor with your knees together or slightly apart, and your big toes touching.
Step:2 Sit back on your heels, extending your arms forward on the floor, lowering your torso down between your thighs.
Step:3 Rest your forehead on the floor, keeping your arms extended out in front of you with palms facing down.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, breathing deeply and allowing your body to relax into the stretch.

name: Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right
Child Pose Arms Extended Left Right_Female
Child pose up
instructions: Step:1 Begin on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips. Keep your elbows bent close to your body with chest close to the floor.
Step:2 Push through your hands to lift your upper body slightly while simultaneously pushing your hips backwards towards your heels. Straighten your arms as you move your hips back.
Step:3 Continue to push your hips back until they are close to your heels, extending your arms fully in front of you on the floor.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, breathing deeply and allowing your body to relax into the stretch.

name: Chin up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back to start the movement.
Step:3 Pull your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin up (isometric and negative)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back to start the movement.
Step:3 Pull your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar. Hold this top position (isometric hold) for a specified duration.
Step:4 After the hold, slowly lower yourself back to the starting position (negative phase), taking about 3-5 seconds to fully extend your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin up reverse close grip
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with a close underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands placed closer than shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your back and start pulling your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin up reverse normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back to start the movement.
Step:3 Pull your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin up reverse wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands placed wider than your shoulder-width. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back to start the movement.
Step:3 Pull your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin ups (narrow parallel grip)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with a narrow parallel grip (palms facing each other) and your hands close together. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and start pulling your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin-up (isometric and negative)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back to start the movement.
Step:3 Pull your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar. Hold this top position (isometric hold) for a specified duration.
Step:4 After the hold, slowly lower yourself back to the starting position (negative phase), taking about 3-5 seconds to fully extend your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Circle elbow arm
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms out to the sides at shoulder level, keeping them straight.
Step:2 Bend your arms at the elbows, bringing your fingers to touch your shoulders on the same side, keeping your elbows pointing outwards.
Step:3 Begin to make small circular motions with your elbows, moving them forward, up, back, and down in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Continue circling your elbows for the desired number of repetitions, then reverse the direction of the circles and repeat.

name: Circles knee stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet together and knees slightly bent. Place your hands on your hips for support.
Step:2 Keeping your knees together, bend them together and slowly rotate them in a circular motion to the right, making small controlled circles.
Step:3 Continue circling your knees for the desired number of repetitions, then reverse the direction of the circles and rotate to the left.
Step:4 Maintain a steady pace and keep your upper body relaxed throughout the exercise.

name: Clamshell
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs stacked, knees bent at about 90 degrees, and your hips aligned. Rest your head on your bottom arm and place your top hand on your hip for support.
Step:2 Keep your feet together and your core engaged.
Step:3 Raise your top knee upward as far as possible without rotating your hips or lifting your feet off each other. Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower your knee back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Clap curtsy squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight overhead, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Step your right foot behind and across your left leg, bending both knees to lower into a curtsy squat while simultaneously lower your hands in circular motion to your sides.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, extending your right leg back to shoulder-width apart and bringing your arms back overhead and clap them together.
