Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Clap jack
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet together and your arms extended by your sides at shoulder level.
Step:2 Simultaneously jump your feet out to the sides to a wide stance while bringing your arms straight in front of you and clapping your hands together at chest level.
Step:3 Jump your feet back together and bring your arms back to your sides to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement continuously for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Clap push ups
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the floor, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Explosively push through your palms to lift your body off the floor. While in the air, quickly clap your hands together in front of your chest.
Step:4 Place your hands back on the floor to catch yourself and immediately lower into the next push-up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Climber a padded stool supported
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position on the floor with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. The padded stool should be in front of you.
Step:2 Engage your core and place your right hand on the stool, followed by your left hand, lifting your upper body onto the stool.
Step:3 Reverse the movement by placing your right hand back on the floor, followed by your left hand, lowering your body back into the plank position.
Step:4 Continue climbing up and down the stool, alternating which hand leads the movement for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Clock push ups
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standard push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Perform a push-up by lowering your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, then push back up to the starting position.
Step:3 Move your right hand and left hand a few inches to the left (clockwise) and perform another push-up.

Step:4 Return both hands to the starting position and perform another push-up. Repeat this sequence, alternating between the starting position and the clockwise position for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Close grip barbell bench press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Position yourself so that your eyes are directly under the barbell. Grip the barbell with a close grip, placing your hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart, with palms facing away from you.
Step:2 Lower the barbell slowly to your mid-chest by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body throughout the movement.
Step:3 Push the barbell back up to the starting position by fully extending your arms without locking your elbows. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close grip push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed under your shoulders, with straight arms. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides.
Step:3 Push through your palms to lift your body back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close-reverse Grip Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with a close underhand grip (palms facing you) and your hands placed closer than shoulder-width apart. 2. Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly bent or crossed behind you.
Step:2 Engage your back and start pulling your body upward by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps, continuing until your chin is above the bar.
Step:3 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cluster
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squatted position with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.

Step:2 Lift the barbell to a front rack position by performing a clean movement, explosively extending your hips and knees, shrugging your shoulders, and then catching the barbell at your shoulders with your elbows pointing forward. As you catch the barbell, simultaneously lower into a squat by bending your knees and hips until your thighs are lower than your knees.
Step:3 From the bottom of the squat, stand up straight by extending your knees.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the floor. Repeat the sequence for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cobra full push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed under your shoulders, your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Perform a push-up by lowering your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides.
Step:3 As your chest reaches the floor, leave your hips on the floor and press through your palms to lift your chest up, straightening your arms and arching your back into the cobra position.
Step:4 Bend your arms to lower your chest back to the floor, then press through your palms to lift your body back to the starting plank position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cobra push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor with your legs extended straight behind you and your hands placed at shoulder level, palms flat on the floor and elbows close to your sides.

Step:2 Engage your core and press through your palms to lift your chest off the floor, straightening your arms to come into the cobra position. 3. Keep your hips on the floor. Hold the cobra position for a moment, feeling the stretch in your lower back and abdomen.
Step:3 . Slowly lower your chest back to the floor by bending your elbows, returning to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cobra side Ab stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor with your legs extended straight behind you and your hands placed at shoulder level, palms flat on the floor.
Step:2 Press through your palms to lift your chest off the floor, straightening your arms to come into the cobra position, keeping your hips on the floor.

Step:3 From the cobra position, slowly rotate your torso to the right, looking over your right shoulder, and hold the stretch for a moment, feeling the stretch along the left side of your abdomen. Return to the center cobra position.

Step:4 Slowly rotate your torso to the left, looking over your left shoulder, and hold the stretch, feeling the stretch along the right side of your abdomen. Return to the center cobra position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cobra yoga pose hold
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor with your legs extended straight behind you and your hands placed at shoulder level, palms flat on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and press through your palms to lift your chest off the floor, straightening your arms to come into the cobra position, keeping your hips on the floor.
Step:3 Hold the cobra position, keeping your arms straight and your chest lifted, while breathing steadily.

name: Cocoons
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your legs extended straight and your arms extended overhead on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and simultaneously lift your legs off the floor while bringing your arms forward to meet your knees, curling your body into a "cocoon" position.
Step:3 Hold the cocoon position for a moment, squeezing your core muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs and arms back to the starting position, maintaining control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Commando pull-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by grasping a pull-up bar with both hands placed close together, palms facing each other in a neutral grip.
Step:2 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight.
Step:3 Engage your back and pull your body up towards the bar, leaning your head to one side of the bar as you lift.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with a controlled movement. Repeat the pull-up, alternating the side of your head relative to the bar for each repetition.

name: Concentration curls dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand and rest your right elbow on the inside of your right thigh.
Step:2 Let the dumbbell hang down towards the floor with your arm fully extended.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps, keeping your elbow stationary and close to your thigh. Squeeze the biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Control balance
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on your back, raise your legs towards the head, and hold your feet by extending your arms overhead.
Step:2 Release your right leg and take it upward until it becomes vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Place your free hand on your left calf and maintain balance.
Step:4 Hold for a while, return to the starting position, and repeat.

name: Corner touch
instructions: Step:1 Begin standing with your body turned to the left side in a semi-lunge position, your left leg bent, and your right leg extended behind you lightly bent. Extend your right arm upward and your left arm downward to your side.

Step:2 Engage your core and rotate your body on your feet, turning to face the opposite side. As you rotate, lower your right arm and raise your left arm, so that your left arm is now upward and your right arm is downward to your side.
Step:3 Repeat the movement, alternating sides, and performing the desired number of repetitions.

name: Corner wall chest stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing in front of a corner of a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. Place your palms flat against the walls at your sides, with your elbows slightly below shoulder height.
Step:2 Lean forward into the corner, keeping your legs in place, to lean into the stretch.
Step:3 Push your chest forward towards the corner, feeling the stretch across your chest and shoulders. Hold this position for the desired duration.
Step:4 Slowly step back to return to the starting position and repeat the stretch as needed.

name: Cossack squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg, bending your right knee while keeping your left leg straight. Lower your hips towards the floor, ensuring your right knee tracks over your right toes.

Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, then repeat the movement on the left side by shifting your weight to your left leg and bending your left knee. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Counterbalanced skater squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall on your right foot, curl your left leg to 90 degrees, and extend your arms forward.
Step:2 Lower your hips while bending your right knee, lean forward, and maintain balance by moving your left thigh backward.
Step:3 Hold this position for a while, return to the initial position, and repeat.

name: Crab pose
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on the floor with your legs bent, feet flat on the floor, and hands placed behind you with your fingers pointing towards your body.
Step:2 Engage your core and press through your palms and feet to lift your hips off the floor, creating a tabletop position with your body.
Step:3 Hold this position, ensuring your hips are lifted high and your torso is parallel to the floor, while keeping your head in line with your spine.
Step:4 After holding the position for the desired duration, slowly lower your hips back to the floor and return to the starting position.

name: Crab twist toe touch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on the floor with your legs bent, feet flat on the floor, and hands placed behind you with your fingers pointing towards your body.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and press through your palms and feet to lift your hips off the floor, creating a tabletop position with your body.
Step:3 Simultaneously lift your right hand and left foot off the floor and twist your torso to reach your right hand towards your left foot, attempting to touch your left toe.

Step:4 Return your hand  and leg to the floor and repeat the movement on the opposite side by lifting your left hand and reaching towards your right foot. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block_Female
Criss cross arms lift
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight in front of you at your hip height, palms facing inwards.
Step:2 Cross your right arm over your left arm at the wrists and then cross your left arm over your right arm.
Step:3 Repeat the crossing movement until your hands are opposite your head.
Step:4 Lower your arms back to your hip level by crossing them down.

name: Criss cross elbow to knee
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your hands placed behind your head, elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:2 Engage your quadriceps and perform a light jump, crossing your legs in mid-air, and land with your feet crossed and immediately lightly jump back to the starting position.
Step:3 Lift your right knee towards your left elbow while twisting your torso to bring your left elbow towards your right knee.

Step:4 Return to the starting position, perform another light jump crossing your legs, and repeat the movement on the opposite side by lifting your left knee towards your right elbow. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Criss cross jack
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet wide apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides at shoulder level.
Step:2 Engage your quadriceps and perform a light jump, crossing your legs in mid-air while simultaneously bringing both arms straight in front of your chest.
Step:3 Land with your legs crossed and your arms in front of your chest.

Step:4 Immediately jump again to return to the starting position with your feet wide apart and your arms extended to the sides at shoulder level. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Criss cross jump
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet wide apart and your arms bent out to the sides at shoulder level and hands facing each other.
Step:2 Engage your quadriceps and perform a light jump, crossing your legs in mid-air while simultaneously crossing both arms in front of your chest.
Step:3 Land with your legs crossed and your arms in front of your chest.

Step:4 Immediately jump again to return to the starting position with your feet wide apart and your arms bent out to the sides at shoulder level and hands facing each other. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Criss cross leg raises
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your legs extended straight out and your arms resting by your sides or under your lower back for support. Engage your core and lift both legs slightly off the floor.
Step:2 Start crisscrossing your legs in a scissor motion, crossing your right leg over your left and then your left leg over your right.

Step:3 Gradually move your legs upward while continuing to crisscross until they form a 45-degree angle with your torso. Then, lower them back down to just above the floor, maintaining the crisscross motion throughout.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cross Body Elbow Pull Shoulder Stretch_Female
Cross over shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lean forward at your hips with a slight arch in your back.
Step:2 Cross your arms and place your hands on your knees.
Step:3 Engage your core and gently press your chest downward to feel the stretch in your shoulders and upper back.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for the desired duration, then slowly return to a standing position.

name: Crossed arms front leg kick
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms crossed in front of your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your right leg straight in front of you to perform a front kick, keeping your leg as straight as possible.
Step:3 Lower your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Immediately lift your left leg to perform a front kick, keeping your arms crossed and your core engaged. Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crossover kneeling hip flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a lunge position with your right foot on the floor and your left knee on the floor, ensuring both legs are bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Engage your core and rotate your torso towards your right leg, placing both arms straight and pulling on the outside of your right thigh.
Step:3 Gently push your hips forward while keeping your back straight to stretch.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Crouching heel back calf stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin standing with your legs wide in a semi-lunge position, turned to the right side, with your left leg extended back and your right knee bent.
Step:2 Bend forward at the hips and place your hands on the floor in front of you for balance, keeping your back as straight as possible.
Step:3 Push your left heel down towards the floor, feeling a stretch in your left calf muscle.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for the desired duration, then switch sides and repeat the stretch on the right side.

name: Crunch (arms straight)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your arms straight above your head, keeping them in line with your ears.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, reaching your arms straight up towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back to the floor with control, keeping your arms extended. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (hands overhead)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your arms straight overhead with hands close together, keeping them in line with your ears.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, reaching your arms straight up towards the ceiling.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back to the floor with control, keeping your arms extended. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (legs on stability ball)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent at a 90-degree angle and your lower legs resting on a stability ball.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Lift your shoulder blades off the floor, curling your upper body towards your knees while keeping your legs stable on the ball.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back to the floor with control, maintaining your legs' position on the ball. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (on bosu ball)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on a BOSU ball with your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent.
Step:2 Lean back to position your lower back against the BOSU ball, ensuring your upper body is supported. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades upwards, curling your upper body towards your knees.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back down with control, maintaining your core engagement. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (on stability ball)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on a stability ball with your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle.

Step:2 Walk your feet forward and lean back to position your lower and mid-back on the stability ball. Your upper body should be supported by the ball. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades upwards, curling your upper body towards your knees.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back down with control, maintaining your core engagement. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (straight leg up)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your legs extended straight up towards the ceiling. Keep your feet together, and your arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, reaching your arms towards your toes.
Step:3 Hold the crunch position briefly, squeezing your abdominal muscles at the top.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back to the floor with control, keeping your legs extended upward. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch floor
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, curling your upper body towards your knees.
Step:4 Lower your shoulder blades back to the floor with control, maintaining your core engagement. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch frog on floor
instructions: Step:1 Begin seated on the floor, leaning back slightly. Your arms should be extended out to the sides at shoulder level, and your legs should be extended straight and parallel just above the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core to simultaneously bring both knees towards your chest while lightly crunching your upper body towards your knees.
Step:3 As you crunch, bring your arms together towards the sides of your knees.
Step:4 Extend your legs back out and open your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet just off the floor.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor while simultaneously lifting your legs slightly to bring your knees towards your head.
Step:4 Lower your back to the floor and your legs back to the starting position, keeping your feet just off the floor. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch with medicine ball
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Hold a medicine ball with both hands, keeping your arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Lift your upper back off the floor by contracting your abdominal muscles.
Step:3 Raise the medicine ball towards the ceiling as you perform the crunch, keeping your arms straight. Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your abs.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position, keeping control of the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Curtsy lunge bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides.
Step:2 Step your right leg behind and across your left leg, bending both knees to lower into a curtsy lunge. Your front knee should be aligned with your front ankle.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side, stepping your left leg behind and across your right leg. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Curtsy lunge slide with towel
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and place a towel under your right foot.
Step:2 Slide your right foot behind and across your left leg, bending both knees to lower into a curtsy lunge. Your front knee should be aligned with your front ankle.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, sliding your right foot back to the original position.
Step:4 Complete the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch the towel to the other foot and repeat the movement with the opposite leg.

name: Curtsy lunges Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a resistance band under your left foot. Hold the handles of the band with both hands either at shoulder height or by your abdomane sides.
Step:2 Step your right leg behind and across your left leg, while bending both knees to lower into a lunge.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right leg back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to work the other leg.

name: Curtsy squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips or by your sides.

Step:2 Step your right leg behind and across your left leg, bending both knees to lower into a curtsy squat. Your front knee should be aligned with your front ankle, and your back knee should point towards the floor.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side, stepping your left leg behind and across your right leg. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dead bug
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your arms extended straight up towards the ceiling and your legs lifted with your knees bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Engage your core and slowly lower your right arm and left leg towards the floor, keeping your back flat on the floor and not allowing it to arch.
Step:3 Return your right arm and left leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dead bug extended arms
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back, right arm extended overhead on the floor in line with your torso and left arm extended by your side. Right knee bent close to your chest, while the left leg is bent and lightly extended away from your hips level, keeping both lower legs parallel to the floor.

Step:2 In a semi circular motion bring your right arm to your side while slowly extending your right leg to pass your hip level and simultaneously bring your left arm in a semi circular motion extended overhead on the floor in line with your torso and your left knee closer to your chest.
Step:3 Repeat the movement with the opposite arm and leg, lowering the arm extended by your side and the opposite leg. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dead hang stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing under a pull-up bar or a similar overhead bar.
Step:2 Reach up and grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing forward (overhand grip), and your hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Allow your body to hang freely with your feet off the floor, keeping your arms fully extended and your shoulders relaxed.
Step:4 Hold this position for the desired duration, focusing on deep breathing and maintaining a relaxed grip.

name: Decline bench full sit up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured under the footpads.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your knees and stop until a few inches away.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline bench oblique crunches
instructions: Step:1 Secure your feet at the end of a decline bench, lie back with your knees slightly bent, and cross your hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the bench while twisting your torso to the right.
Step:3 Squeeze your obliques at the top of the movement, ensuring that the contraction is felt along the side of your abdomen.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position and repeat the movement, this time twisting your torso to the left. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline bench oblique crunches dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Secure your feet at the end of a decline bench and lie back with your knees slightly bent. Hold a dumbbell in each hand close to your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the bench by contracting your abdominal muscles, while simultaneously twisting your torso to the right.
Step:3 Squeeze your obliques at the top of the movement, ensuring that the contraction is felt along the side of your abdomen.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position and repeat the movement, this time twisting your torso to the left. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline bent leg reverse crunch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your head at the higher end and place your hands on the side edges of the bench for stability. Bend your knees at 90 degrees and lift your legs so your thighs are perpendicular to the bench and your lower legs are parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the bench, curling your knees towards your chest while keeping both legs bent.
Step:3 Lower your hips back to the starting position with control, keeping your knees bent at 90 degrees. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline chair push up diamond
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your feet on a chair and positioning your hands on the floor close together, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards your hands by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline diamond pike push-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your feet on a bench and positioning your hands on the floor close together, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers. Hips raised towards the ceiling.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms an inverted V shape with your legs and torso.
Step:3 Lower your head towards your hands by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline kneeling push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your knees on a step up and position your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your chest and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your knees.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline kneeling push up on box
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your knees on a box and position your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your chest and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your knees.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline levitating sit ups bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured under the footpads. Position your torso so it is parallel to the floor, 'levitating' off the bench.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your knees, keeping your back straight and avoiding pulling on your neck.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the starting position with control, maintaining the parallel position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your feet on a bench and position your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline push up against wall
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your feet against a wall and positioning your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart. Your body should be in a decline position with your feet elevated on the wall.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your feet.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline shoulder tap
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing your feet on a bench and positioning your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart. Your body should be in a decline position with your feet elevated.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lift your right hand off the floor and tap your left shoulder, lightly rotate your hips according to the tap side.
Step:4 Return your right hand to the floor and repeat the movement with your left hand, tapping your right shoulder. Continue alternating for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline sit up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured under the footpads. Position yourself so that your hips are at the edge of the bench.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your knees until your torso forms a 90 degree angle with your thighs, keeping your back as straight as possible.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline sit ups dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Secure your feet at the end of a decline bench and lie back with your knees slightly bent. Hold a dumbbell in each hand close to your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the bench by contracting your abdominal muscles.
Step:3 Continue to lift your upper body until you are in a seated position, ensuring that the contraction is felt in your abs.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position with control, keeping your core engaged. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Deep push-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands holding dumbbells on the floor, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Your feet should be on the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, allowing your chest to go deeper than your hands.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, straightening your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Diagonal chop cable
instructions: Step:1 Anchor one end of the band at chest height. Stand with your right side facing the anchor point, with your feet shoulder-width apart, and grasp the handle with both hands. Extend your arms to hold the handle opposite your chest.
Step:2 Pull the handle down and diagonally across your body, twisting your torso and pivoting your back foot to follow through. Bring the handle down towards the left side.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to work in the opposite direction

name: Diagonal chop left
instructions: Step:1 Start standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, clasping your hands together and holding them extended opposite your chest.
Step:2 Rotate your torso and simultaneously bring your hands diagonally across your body towards your left hip, bending your knees slightly as you turn.
Step:3 Keep your arms extended and pivot your right foot as you rotate to protect your knee from strain.
Step:4 Return to the starting position in a controlled manner, bringing your hands back opposite your chest.

name: Diagonal chop right
instructions: Step:1 Start standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, clasping your hands together and holding them extended oposite your chest.
Step:2 Rotate your torso and simultaneously bring your hands diagonally across your body towards your right hip, bending your knees slightly as you turn.
Step:3 Keep your arms extended and pivot your right foot as you rotate to protect your knee from strain.
Step:4 Return to the starting position in a controlled manner, bringing your hands back opposite your chest.

name: Diagonal lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together, arms extended outwards at shoulder level.

Step:2 Step diagonally forward with your right foot, planting it at a 45-degree angle. As you lower into a lunge, rotate your torso to the right and lean down to touch your right foot with your left hand, keeping your left leg straight.
Step:3 Press through your right heel and rotate back to center as you return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, stepping diagonally forward, rotating left, and touching your left foot with your right hand.

name: Diagonal opens
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms bent at the elbows, elbows facing outwards, and hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Slide your right hand over your left forearm, both arms in an opposite diagonal direction while keeping the elbows bent.
Step:3 Return your hands to the starting position and repeat the movement by sliding your left hand over your right forearm, extending in the opposite diagonal direction.

name: Diagonal punch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hands in a guard position near your face.
Step:2 Rotate your torso to the right, and extend your right arm in a diagonal punch across your body.
Step:3 Return your right hand to the starting position as you rotate your torso back to center.
Step:4 Repeat the motion with your left arm, rotating your torso to the left to execute a diagonal punch across your body.

name: Diamond push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands close together under your chest, fingers forming a diamond shape (thumbs and index fingers touching).
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor, keeping your elbows close to your body and your back straight.
Step:3 Pause briefly as your chest nearly touches your hands.
Step:4 Push back up to the starting plank position, maintaining a straight line from your head to your heels throughout the movement.

name: Diamond push-up (on knees)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by kneeling on a mat with your hands close together under your chest on the floor, fingers forming a diamond shape (thumbs and index fingers touching).
Step:2 Lean forward to shift your weight onto your hands while keeping your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:4 Press through your hands to lift your body back up to the starting position, maintaining the alignment of your spine throughout the movement.

name: Dip leg raise on couch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a couch with your hands placed next to your hips, gripping the edge for support.
Step:2 Lift your hips off the couch by pressing down into your hands and straightening your arms, while keeping your feet flat on the floor and both knees bent.
Step:3 As you bend your elbows to lower your body into a dip, simultaneously lift one leg, bent at the knee, towards your chest.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back up, straightening your arms and simultaneously lowering your lifted leg back to the starting position.

name: Dip on floor with chair
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your back facing a chair and place your hands on the edge of the chair seat, fingers pointing towards your body.
Step:2 Bend your knees in front of you with your heels resting on the floor.
Step:3 Press down into the chair with your hands to lift your hips off the floor, straightening your arms.
Step:4 Bend your elbows to lower your body towards the floor until your elbows form about a 90-degree angle and push through your hands to lift your body back up to the starting position.

name: Dips between chairs
instructions: Step:1 Position two chairs parallel to each other, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with the seats facing away from you.
Step:2 Stand between the chairs and grasp the top of each chair back with your hands.
Step:3 Lift your body off the floor by straightening your arms, supporting your weight through your hands.

Step:4 Slowly lower your body by bending your elbows until they form about a 90-degree angle, keeping your body upright and close to the chair backs. Press through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, extending your arms fully.

name: Donkey calf raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step with your heels hanging off, placing your forefeet securely on the step.
Step:2 Lean forward and reach down to hold onto a bench in front of you for stability, keeping your back straight and hips aligned with your feet.
Step:3 Press down through your forefeet to elevate your heels as high as possible, fully contracting your calf muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels below the level of the step to maximize the stretch in your calves before the next lift.

name: Donkey kicks bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin on all fours in a tabletop position with your knees hip-width apart on the floor, hands under your shoulders, and your back flat.
Step:2 Keeping your knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift your right leg up towards the ceiling, driving your heel upward as if pushing against the sky.
Step:3 Push your leg up until your thigh is in line with your body and your foot is above your knee.
Step:4 Lower your leg slowly back to the starting position without letting your knee touch the floor. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions before switching to the left leg.

name: Doorway biceps curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand in a doorway and grip the sides of the door frame at about hip height, palms facing forward or slightly inward depending on comfort and doorway design.
Step:2 Step forward with one foot to create tension in your arms and lean slightly back, so your body weight helps create resistance.
Step:3 Curl your elbows to raise your body slowly towards the door frame, keeping your elbows pinned at your sides.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position, repeat the movement.

name: Double jump squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands close together in front of your torso. Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and hips, keeping your chest up and your weight in your heels. Stand back up to the starting position.
Step:2 Immediately lower into a squat again and then explosively jump up from the squat.
Step:3 Land softly on your feet after the jump, repeat the sequence.

name: Double knee drive
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, both arms bent and raised by your sides.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards your chest while rotating your torso to the right, bringing your left elbow to touch your right knee twice.
Step:3 Lower your right leg back to the starting position and return your torso to face forward.

Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side by lifting your left knee towards your chest, rotating your torso to the left, and bringing your right elbow to touch your left knee twice. Continue alternating sides.

name: Double punch front leg lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands in fists near your sides with cloesd fists.
Step:2 Simultaneously punch forward with both arms while lifting your right leg slightly bent at the knee to about waist height.
Step:3 Return your arms and right leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Immediately repeat the movement, this time lifting your left leg while simultaneously punching forward with both arms. Continue alternating leg lifts with each set of punches.

name: Downward dog sprint
instructions: Step:1 Get down on your fours and raise your hips while keeping your arms and legs straight to form an inverted V-shape.
Step:2 Raise and lower your feet alternately as if you are sprinting.
Step:3 Continue for a suitable duration.

name: Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet_Female
Drag curl dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up). Let your arms hang straight down by your sides.
Step:2 Begin by dragging the dumbbells upward along your torso by bending your elbows and pulling them back, as if you are zipping up your jacket.
Step:3 Continue lifting the dumbbells until they reach chest height, focusing on squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the descent. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Drag curl Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a resistance band under your feet. Hold the handles of the band with both hands, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your body and your back straight. Start with your arms fully extended down at your sides.
Step:3 Curl the handles up by dragging your elbows along your torso, keeping them close to your torso, until your hands reach chest level.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell ab crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Hold a dumbbell with both hands striaght over your chest.
Step:2 Lift your head, shoulders, and upper back off the floor by contracting your abdominal muscles.
Step:3 Raise the dumbbell towards the ceiling as you perform the crunch, keeping your arms straight. Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your abs.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position, keeping control of the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Bench Press (high start)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor and a dumbbell in each hand. Start with both arms extended straight up over your chest, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the right dumbbell towards your chest by bending your elbow while keeping the left arm extended and stable.
Step:3 Press the right dumbbell back to the starting position by extending your elbow and contracting your chest muscles.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with the left arm while keeping the right arm extended and stable. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides and palms facing inwards.

Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the right dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. Rotate your forearm as you lift the dumbbell so that your palm faces your shoulder at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm while keeping the right arm extended. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl (VERSION 2)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides and palms facing inwards.

Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the right dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. Rotate your forearm as you lift the dumbbell so that your palm faces your shoulder at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm while keeping the right arm extended. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. Let your arms hang straight down by your sides.
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your body and curl the right dumbbell towards your shoulder by bending your elbow. Keep your palm facing inward throughout the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm while keeping the right arm extended. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Your palms should be facing forward, and your elbows should be bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Engage your core and press the right dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended. Keep your left dumbbell in the starting position.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Repeat, alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Side Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Your palms should be facing each other, and your elbows should be bent at a 60-degree angle and facing downward.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell overhead and slightly lean to the opposite side until your arm is fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner and press the left dumbbell overhead and slightly to the side.
Step:4 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and controlled movement.

name: Dumbbell armpit row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing your body.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells up towards your armpits by bending your elbows. Your elbows should be pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Arnold Press (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing each other and your elbows bent.
Step:2 Engage your shoulders and rotate your palms to face forward as you press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Reverse the motion by lowering the dumbbells back to shoulder height while rotating your palms to face each other again.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and controlled motion throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Arnold Press Seated
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing your body and your elbows bent. Your feet should be flat on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your shoulders and rotate your palms to face forward as you press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Reverse the motion by lowering the dumbbells back to shoulder height while rotating your palms to face your body again.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and controlled motion throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Around Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended straight on your sides, palms facing down.
Step:2 Slowly raise the dumbbells in an arc over your torso and behind your head, keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Return your arms back to the starting position in an arc motion, this time from your sides.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and controlled motion throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Bar Grip Sumo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Hold a dumbbell vertically with both hands, like holding a bar, in front of your hips.
Step:2 Push your hips back and bend your knees to lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping the dumbbell in line with your chest.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, straightening your legs and squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended above your chest and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your feet flat on the floor, maintaining a natural arch in your lower back.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells to your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms at a 45-degree angle to your torso.
Step:4 Push the dumbbells back to the starting position by straightening your arms, ensuring a controlled motion throughout. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Seated Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended, ensuring your wrists remain straight and aligned with your forearms.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back facing a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides.
Step:2 Lower yourself into a squat by bending your knees and hips, keeping your chest up and back straight, until your thighs are parallel to the floor and your buttocks lightly touch the bench.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position, fully extending your hips and knees.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.

name: Dumbbell bent arm lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand, elbows bent at a 90-degree angle and palms facing your body.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. Raise your upper arms to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping your elbows bent at 90 degrees throughout the movement.
Step:3 Lower your arms back to the starting position with a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent Arm Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie perpendicular on a bench with only your upper back supported and your hips slightly lowered. Hold a dumbbell with both hands above your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your feet flat on the floor for stability. Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell until your upper arms are in line with your torso or as far as comfortable, feeling a stretch in your chest and lats.
Step:4 Pull the dumbbell back to the starting position with a controlled motion, keeping your elbows slightly bent. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent Over Face Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing back). Bend at your hips and knees to lower your torso until it is parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang directly below your shoulders, elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbells upward to the ceiling, bending your elbows and bringing them as high as possible and facing outward. Make sure to lead the dumbbells at face level.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent-Over Reverse Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing towards you). Bend at your hips and knees to lower your torso until it is nearly parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang directly below your shoulders, arms fully extended.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbells towards your torso, leading with your elbows and keeping them close to your body. Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent-Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). Bend at your hips and knees to lower your torso until it is nearly parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang directly below your shoulders, arms fully extended.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbells towards your torso, leading with your elbows and keeping them close to your body. Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with a controlled motion. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell bicep curl to shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing forward). Keep your elbows close to your torso.
Step:2 Perform bicep curls by bending your elbows to lift the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 As you reach the top of the curl, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward and press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully.

Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists back to the starting position and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl with Overhead Extension on Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on a stability ball with your forefeet on the floor for support. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with one arm extended overhead and the other arm hanging by your side.

Step:2 Simultaneously perform a bicep curl with the arm hanging by your side, bending your elbow to lift the dumbbell towards your shoulder and an overhead triceps extension with the other arm, bending your elbow to lower the dumbbell behind your head.
Step:3 Slowly return both arms to the starting position, ensuring control and stability throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell bulgarian box split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet, back first in front of a box, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides. Place the top of one foot on the box behind you.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee until your front thigh is parallel to the floor and your back knee is hovering just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat the movement on the other side.

name: Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand a few feet, back first in front of a bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides. Place the top of one foot on the bench behind you.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee until your front thigh is parallel to the floor and your back knee is hovering just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat the movement on the other side.

name: Dumbbell chest press decline
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet securely placed under the footpads. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended above your chest, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbells slowly towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Push the dumbbells back to the starting position by straightening your arms, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell chest press flat
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended above your chest, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbells slowly towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Push the dumbbells back to the starting position by straightening your arms, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell chest press incline bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench with your feet firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended above your chest, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbells slowly towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Push the dumbbells back to the starting position by straightening your arms, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell chest pull over
instructions: Step:1 Lie crosswise on a bench, with your upper back and shoulders supported, feet firmly planted on the floor and hips slightly lowered. Hold a dumbbell with both hands above your chest, arms slightly bent.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head and down towards the floor, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position by reversing the arc motion, focusing on engaging your chest and lats.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Chest Supported Lateral Raises
instructions: Step:1 Lie face-down on an incline bench with your chest and stomach supported by the bench, and your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, arms extended straight down.
Step:2 Slowly raise the dumbbells in an arc over your head and towards your back, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbell back to the starting position by reversing the arc motion, focusing on engaging your back and shoulder muscles.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell close grip shoulder press sit up
instructions: Step:1 Lie on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a close grip, elbows bent at 90 degrees resting on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and perform a sit-up by raising your torso towards your knees while simultaneously pressing the dumbbells overhead.
Step:3 Lower your torso back to the starting position while bringing the dumbbells back to shoulder height.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell close Legs Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet close together, holding a dumbbell with both hands from the bar, allowing it to hang in front of you.
Step:2 Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips, lowering the dumbbell towards your feet while keeping it close to your legs.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, ensuring your knees are slightly bent.
Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Close-Grip Simultaneous Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a close grip, palms facing front.
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the dumbbells simultaneously towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps.
Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cossack Squats (VERSION 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell close to your chest between your palms, with your elbows bent facing down.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg and bend your right knee, lowering your body into a squat position while keeping your left leg straight and your left foot flat on the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the other side. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cross Body Hammer Curl (Version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing your body.
Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the right dumbbell across your body towards your left shoulder, squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm, curling the dumbbell towards your right shoulder. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Crunch Hold with Legs Off
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees straight and your legs lifted off the floor almost parallel to the floor, holding a dumbbell with both hands extended just over your hips.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, performing a crunch while pushing the dumbbell over your thighs.
Step:3 Hold the crunch position for a few seconds, ensuring your abs are fully engaged and your lower back remains pressed into the floor.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the floor, maintaining control of the dumbbell throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cuban Press (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. Let your arms hang straight down in front of your thighs.
Step:2 Raise your elbows to shoulder height, keeping your arms bent at a 90-degree angle, forming a "goalpost" position with your forearms perpendicular to your body.
Step:3 Rotate your shoulders to lift the dumbbells upward until your forearms are vertical.
Step:4 Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. Reverse the movement to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Curl Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging down by your sides. Your palms should face forward.

Step:2 Curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. From the top of the curl position, press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. Your palms should be facing backward at the top of the press.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells behind your head, bending at the elbows until forearms are parallel to the floor. Extend your arms to bring the dumbbells back overhead.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height, then reverse the curl movement to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell curls
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards (neutral grip).
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, rotating your wrists so your palms face upward at the top of the curl.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a brief moment, ensuring you squeeze your biceps.

Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the neutral grip, maintaining control throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell curls alternating
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards (neutral grip).
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl one dumbbell up towards your shoulder, rotating your wrist so your palm faces upward (supinated grip) at the top of the curl.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a brief moment, ensuring you squeeze your biceps, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, rotating your wrist back to the neutral grip.
Step:4 Repeat the curl with the other arm, alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell curtsy lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, arms bent at 90 degrees, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your chest.

Step:2 Step your right leg behind and to the left of your left leg, lowering your hips into a curtsy lunge position. Your front knee should be aligned with your front ankle, and your back knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right leg back to starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the lunge with your left leg stepping behind and to the right of your right leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Alternate Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured and a dumbbell in each hand, arms lowered and elbows bent at a 90-degree angle, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the left dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended while keeping the right arm lowered.
Step:3 Lower the left dumbbell back to the starting position, and press the right dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended.
Step:4 Alternate the press with each arm, maintaining control and stability throughout the exercise, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured and a dumbbell in each hand, arms lowered and elbows bent at a 90-degree angle, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press both dumbbells upward simultaneously until your arms are fully extended, keeping the motion controlled.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with controlled motion until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle.
Step:4 Repeat the press and lowering motion for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining stability throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Decline Close Neutral Grip Press_Female
Dumbbell decline fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured and holding a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended straight out to your sides at chest level with palms facing up.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells up in a wide arc until your arms are straight above your chest, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly lower your arms back out to the sides in a controlled motion, keeping the slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are level with your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the steps for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Decline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured and holding a dumbbell in each hand, arms bent and dumbbells by your sides with palms facing each other.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells up over your chest, extending your arms fully without locking your elbows, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position by your sides in a controlled motion.
Step:4 Repeat the steps for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Decline One Arm Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your arm bent and the dumbbell by your side, palm facing inward. Place your other hand on the bench for stability.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbell up over your chest, extending your arm fully without locking your elbow, keeping your elbow close to your body.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position by your side in a controlled motion.
Step:4 Repeat the steps for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Decline Overhead Sit-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured, holding a dumbbell in each hand extended overhead.
Step:2 Slowly lift your shoulders, and upper back off the bench while simultaneously bringing the dumbbells up and over your head.
Step:3 Continue to lift your torso until you are in an upright position with the dumbbell directly above your head.
Step:4 Slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position, keeping the dumbbells extended overhead.

name: Dumbbell Decline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying chest first on an incline bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight down toward the floor, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Allow your shoulders to relax downward, feeling a stretch in your upper traps.
Step:3 Lift your shoulders upward towards your ears, squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Decline Sit-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet securely positioned under the footpads. Hold a dumbbell with both hands against your chest.
Step:2 Lift your upper body towards your knees, keeping the dumbbell close to your chest.
Step:3 Sit up fully until your back is straight, then slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline triceps pull-over extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and hold a dumbbell with both hands, extending your arms straight above your chest.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head, keeping your arms slightly bent at the elbows.
Step:3 Once your arms are almost parallel to the floor, bend your elbows to lower the dumbbells down to your head sides, and immediately straighten your elbows.
Step:4 Raise both dumbbells in an arc over your head to starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Twist Fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured and holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms straight out to your sides at chest level with palms facing each up.
Step:2 As you raise the dumbbells up in a wide arc, twist your wrists so that your palms face backward, bringing the dumbbells to meet above your chest while maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly lower your arms back out to the sides in a controlled motion, twisting your wrists back so that your palms face up, until your arms are level with your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the raising and lowering motion for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell diagonal chop
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands extended opposite your chest.
Step:2 Rotate your torso and lower the dumbbell diagonally across your body to the left side, extending your arms fully as you reach downward, while pivoting your feet towards your left side.
Step:3 In a controlled motion, bring the dumbbell back up to the starting position, reversing the diagonal path.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Drag Over Shoulder Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended down by your sides.
Step:2 Begin the movement by curling the dumbbells up towards your shoulders while dragging your elbows backward, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Once the dumbbells are close to your shoulders, push them up slowly to pass the shoulders.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: dumbbell external rotatio
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. Keep your opposite hand behind your back for support.
Step:2 Start with your working arm bent at a 90-degree angle, elbow close to your side, forearm parallel to the floor facing forward with the dumbbell held in a neutral position.
