Step:3 Rotate your forearm outward, keeping your elbow fixed in place, until your palm faces forward.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position, bringing your forearm back to starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell external rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. Keep your opposite hand behind your back for support.
Step:2 Start with your working arm bent at a 90-degree angle, elbow close to your side, forearm parallel to the floor facing forward with the dumbbell held in a neutral position.
Step:3 Rotate your forearm outward, keeping your elbow fixed in place, until your palm faces forward.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position, bringing your forearm back to starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: dumbbell face down lying shoulder pres
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with your legs bent at 90 degrees and crossed together. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms bent and elbows pointing outwards at shoulder height.
Step:2 Begin with the dumbbells at shoulder level, palms facing the floor. Press the dumbbells forward by extending your arms until your arms are fully extended but not locked out.
Step:3 Slowly bring the dumbbells back to the starting position at shoulder level, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell face down lying shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with your legs bent at 90 degrees and crossed together. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms bent and elbows pointing outwards at shoulder height.
Step:2 Begin with the dumbbells at shoulder level, palms facing the floor. Press the dumbbells forward by extending your arms until your arms are fully extended but not locked out.
Step:3 Slowly bring the dumbbells back to the starting position at shoulder level, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell farmer walks
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing upright with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended at your sides, and palms facing inward. Ensure your feet are hip-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your chest up and shoulders back to maintain proper posture.
Step:3 Start walking forward, taking controlled, even steps, while maintaining a tight grip on the dumbbells.
Step:4 Walk for the desired distance or time, keeping your torso upright and your core engaged. Once you reach the end of the distance, turn around and walk back to the starting point.

name: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge_Female
Dumbbell Feet Elevated Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your feet elevated on a box, with your knees bent at 90 degrees. Place a dumbbell on your hips and hold it securely with both hands for support.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and press through your heels to lift your hips toward the ceiling, extending your hips until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 At the peak of the movement, squeeze your glutes and pause for a second.
Step:4 Lower your hips with control to the starting position and repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your feet elevated on a box, your left knee bent at about 90 degrees, and your right leg extended towards the ceiling. Place a dumbbell on your hips and hold it securely with both hands for support.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and press through your heel to lift your hips toward the ceiling, extending your hips until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 At the peak of the movement, squeeze your glutes and pause for a second.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down with control and repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back and place both feet on an elevated surface, with one foot on the edge and the other slightly forward so only the heel rests on top. Place a dumbbell on your hips and hold it securely with both hands for support.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and press through your heels to lift your hips toward the ceiling, extending your hips until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 At the peak of the movement, squeeze your glutes and pause for a second.
Step:4 Lower your hips with control to the starting position and repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Figure Four Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your right ankle across your left knee in a figure four position and rest a dumbbell on your hips, holding it securely with both hands.

Step:2 Engage your glutes and press through the heel of your supporting foot to lift your hips off the ground, extending through your hips until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knee.
Step:3 Lower your hips back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Figure Four Hip Thrust
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your upper back against a bench and place a dumbbell across your hips. Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the floor, then cross one ankle over the opposite knee in a figure four position.
Step:2 Press through the heel of your grounded foot to lift your hips upward in a swift motion, extending your hips until your torso forms a straight line from your shoulders to your bent knee.
Step:3 At the peak of the movement, squeeze your glutes and hold the position for a second. Lower your hips back down with control until they lightly touch the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Dumbbell floor Fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back on the floor with your legs straight on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight above your chest, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbells out to your sides in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. Lower until your upper arms slightly touch the floor.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell fly flat bench
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor for stability. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight above your chest, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbells out to your sides in a wide arc, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. Lower until your upper arms are parallel to the floor or slightly below chest level.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles, keeping the slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell fly flat bench slow
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor for stability. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight above your chest, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbells out to your sides in a wide arc, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. Lower until your upper arms are parallel to the floor or slightly below chest level.
Step:3 Slowly bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles, keeping the slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell fly incline bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on an incline bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand and lie back on the bench with your arms extended straight above your chest, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbells out to your sides in a wide arc, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. Lower until your upper arms are parallel to the floor or slightly below chest level.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles, keeping the slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control and proper form throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Frog Jumps
instructions: Step:1 Bend your knees and lower into a deep squat while keeping your chest up, with your feet wider than shoulder-width, holding a dumbbell in each hand hanging between your legs.
Step:2 Push through your heels and extend your legs to stand upright, bringing the dumbbells to your sides.
Step:3 Explosively jump straight up from the squat position, extending through your hips, knees, and ankles.
Step:4 Land softly back into the squat position with control and immediately go into the next rep.

name: Dumbbell Front Rack Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Rack the dumbbells on your shoulders by bending your elbows and positioning your upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Keep your chest up, and step forward with your right leg. Lower your body by bending both knees until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee is just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement with your left leg.
Step:4 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides and palms facing your thighs.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your arms straight and palms facing down.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your shoulders are not shrugging up towards your ears.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertical with both hands, arms fully extended down.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbell in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your shoulders are not shrugging up towards your ears.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand and racking them on your shoulders with your elbows pointing forward.
Step:2 Begin the movement by pushing your hips back and bending your knees to lower into a squat position.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor, ensuring your knees stay in line with your toes and your back remains straight.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees fully to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place a dumbbell horizontally across your hips, holding it securely with both hands.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes, and press through your heels to lift your hips toward the ceiling. Your body should form a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, holding for a brief moment while keeping the dumbbell stable on your hips.
Step:4 Lower your hips back to the starting position in a controlled manner without letting your glutes touch the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Goblet 2 sec Hold Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, between your palms. Keep your elbows pointed downward.
Step:2 Push your hips back and bend your knees until your thighs are just lower than parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Hold the squat position for 2 seconds, keeping your chest up and your weight distributed evenly through your heels.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the standing position, squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Goblet Curtsy Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, between your palms. Keep your elbows pointed downward.
Step:2 Step your right foot behind and to the outside of your left foot, lowering your body into a curtsy lunge.
Step:3 Bend both knees until your right knee almost touches the floor. Keep your chest up and your weight evenly distributed.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side.

name: Dumbbell Goblet Forward Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, elbows pointing down.
Step:2 Take a step forward with one leg and begin descending by bending both knees.
Step:3 Descend until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, then repeat on the opposite leg.

name: Dumbbell Goblet Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, between your palms. Keep your elbows pointed downward.
Step:2 Step your right foot forward into a split stance, ensuring your left foot remains stationary and slightly elevated on your forefoot.

Step:3 Lower your body by bending both knees to approximately 90 degrees, keeping your chest up and back straight. Your right knee should be directly above your right ankle, and your left knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Complete the desired number of repetitions on one side before switching to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Goblet Split Squat Front Foot Elevanted
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, between your palms. Keep your elbows pointed downward.
Step:2 Place your right foot on a step, while keeping your left leg extended on your forefoot on the floor behind you.
Step:3 Lower your body by bending the front knee to approximately 90 degrees. Your left knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Complete the desired number of repetitions on one side before switching to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell vertically against your chest with both hands, between your palms. Keep your elbows pointed downward.
Step:2 Push your hips back and bend your knees, making sure to keep your weight on your heels.

Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor, or as low as your mobility allows, while maintaining a straight back and keeping the dumbbell close to your chest.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, straightening your legs and extending your hips fully at the top.

name: Dumbbell Half Biceps Curl for 21s
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. Start with your arms fully extended by your sides.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbells upward until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle, stopping halfway up. Hold for a brief moment.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with a controlled motion.
Step:4 Repeat this half curl motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell half kneeling military press
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a half-kneeling position with your right knee on the floor and left foot flat on the floor in front of you. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Engage your core and press both dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level with control, maintaining a steady motion.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your torso). Let your arms hang straight down at your sides.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell in your right hand upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat the movement with your left arm.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl Simultaneous Arms
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your torso). Let your arms hang straight down at your sides.
Step:2 Simultaneously curl both dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps and forearms.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Grip Incline Bench Two Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle. Lie face down on the bench with your feet firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand using a hammer grip (palms facing each other).
Step:2 Let your arms hang straight down toward the floor, fully extended, with your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbells towards your torso by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Preacher Curl Simultaneous Arms
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest pressed against the pad, feet flat on the floor, and hold a dumbbell in each hand using a hammer grip (palms facing each other).
Step:2 Extend your arms fully over the bench pad, keeping a slight bend in your elbows to maintain tension on your biceps.

Step:3 Curl both dumbbells simultaneously towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps. Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms over the bench pad. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Strict Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back fully supported against a wall, feet shoulder-width apart, and hold a dumbbell in each hand using a hammer grip (palms facing each other).
Step:2 Keep your arms extended straight down by your sides, with your upper arms and elbows pressed against the wall.

Step:3 Engage your core and curl both dumbbells simultaneously towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps. Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms down by your sides. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hang Power Clean
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other), letting the dumbbells hang close to your shins.
Step:2 Explosively extend your hips and knees, shrugging your shoulders as you pull the dumbbells upward.
Step:3 As the dumbbells reach chest height, quickly rotate your wrists and elbows to catch the dumbbells on your shoulders while dropping into a partial squat.

Step:4 Stand up by extending your hips and knees, bringing the dumbbells to shoulder height. Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell High Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up). Extend both arms straight out at shoulder level, keeping the dumbbells facing up.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach close to your shoulders.
Step:4 Extend the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hip Thrust
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your upper back resting against a bench, knees bent, and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell with each hand across your hips.
Step:2 Press through your heels to lift your hips upward until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, ensuring your glutes are fully contracted.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Hip Thrust (VERSION 2)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your upper back resting against a bench, knees bent, and feet flat on the floor. Place a dumbbell across your hips, holding it with both hands for stability.
Step:2 Press through your heels to lift your hips upward until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, ensuring your glutes are fully contracted.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl the right dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.

Step:4 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position with control while simultaneously starting to curl the left dumbbell upward. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing each other.
Step:2 Curl the right dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow and rotating your wrist so that your palm faces up.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position with control, rotating the wrist as you curl. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing each other.
Step:2 Curl the right dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping your palms facing each other.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position, maintaining the hammer grip. Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms bent and dumbbells positioned near your chest.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended, keeping your palm facing forward.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position with control while simultaneously starting to press the left dumbbell upward, maintaining proper form.
Step:4 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms bent and dumbbells positioned near your chest.
Step:2 Press both dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended, keeping your palms facing forward.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the pressing motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Biceps Simultaneous Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl both dumbbells simultaneously towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Breeding
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended, elbows slightly bent, above your chest and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbells to your sides in a wide arc, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back up in a controlled manner, following the same wide arc, until they meet above your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a controlled and steady motion throughout.

name: Dumbbell Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight out to your sides at chest level, palms facing up.
Step:2 Engage your core and bring the dumbbells up in a controlled manner, following a wide arc, until they meet above your chest, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back out to your sides in a wide arc until your arms are level with your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Fly on Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball and walk your feet forward until your middle back is supported on the ball, feet slightly wider than shoulder-width, hinge your hips to form a 90 degree angle with your torso.

Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight out to your sides at chest level, palms facing up. Bring the dumbbells up in a controlled manner, following a wide arc, until they meet above your chest.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back out to your sides in a wide arc until your arms are level with your chest.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a controlled and steady motion throughout.

name: Dumbbell Incline Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle with a dumbbell in each hand, arms straight, and palms facing down just over your thighs.
Step:2 Raise both dumbbells in front of you, keeping your arms straight, until they reach opposite your chest.
Step:3 Hold the position for a second, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a steady and controlled motion.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing each other (hammer grip) and elbows bent and set perpendicular to your torso.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells forward in a controlled motion until your arms are fully extended opposite your chest, maintaining the hammer grip.
Step:3 Return the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Simultaneous Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing each other (hammer grip).
Step:2 Curl both dumbbells simultaneously towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your palms facing each other.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Lying Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle with your forefeet firm on the floor, allowing your arms to hang straight down with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing back.
Step:2 Raise both dumbbells forward and upward until your arms are in level with your torso, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder muscles at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, allowing your arms to hang down. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie on your side with your lower arm resting on the bench. Hold a dumbbell with your upper hand, arm extended at your side with your palm facing your body.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbell up in an arc motion until your arm is straight at shoulder level.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit back against it, holding a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. Your other arm can hold the bench for stability.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended above your upper chest.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height with control, keeping your elbow at a 45-degree angle to your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Incline Palms Back Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit back against it, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with elbows bent and facing the floor, with an underhand grip (palms facing back).
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended above your chest, maintaining the underhand grip.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height with control, keeping your elbows close to your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie chest-first against it, allowing your arms to hang down with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Raise both arms out to the sides until they are at shoulder height, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:3 Hold briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are parallel to the floor and in line with your shoulders.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie chest-first against it, allowing your arms to extend opposite your chest with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down.
Step:2 Row both dumbbells backward by bending your elbows and pulling them towards your sides.
Step:3 Return the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit back against it, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended at your sides, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Shrug your shoulders upward, lifting the dumbbells towards your ears, without bending your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Simultaneous Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit back against it, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended down, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Simultaneously curl both dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Squeeze Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie back against it, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other. Position the dumbbells just above your chest, pressed together.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward by extending your arms, keeping your elbows close to your torso.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms at the top, ensuring the dumbbells remain in contact with each other.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, keeping them squeezed together. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Svend Close grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie back against it. Hold a single dumbbell pressed between your palms just above your chest with your fingers extended or interlaced around the handle.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward by extending your arms, keeping your elbows close to your torso.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms at the top, continuing to press the dumbbell between your palms.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, keeping the dumbbell pressed between your palms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie back against it. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended straight up, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Bend your elbows to lower the dumbbells behind your head in a controlled motion.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until your forearms are parallel to the floor, maintaining a 90-degree angle at your elbows.
Step:4 Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping your upper arms stationary. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Twisted Fly
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie back against it, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Start with your arms extended lightly bent by your sides, palms facing up, dumbbells held at chest level.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells up over your chest in a wide arc, rotating your palms so they face backwards as you raise them up.
Step:3 Reverse the motion, bringing the dumbbells back down in a wide arc and rotating your palms back to face upward. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Two Arm Extension
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie back against it, holding a single dumbbell with both hands, gripping the handle securely. Start with the dumbbell extended straight up above your shoulders, with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbell by bending your elbows, allowing the weight to move behind your head until your forearms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, feeling the stretch in your triceps.
Step:4 Reverse the motion by extending your elbows, pushing the dumbbell back up to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms in front of your chest, keeping the dumbbells close together and your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Keep your back straight as you start to stand up. As you rise, simultaneously open your arms out to your sides, extending them at shoulder level, forming a "T" shape with your body.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are fully extended to the sides and parallel to the floor, with your palms facing forward.
Step:4 Bring your arms back in front of your chest while returning to the squat position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Jumping Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides. Keep your chest up, shoulders back, and core engaged.
Step:2 Lower yourself into a squat position by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight and the dumbbells close to your body.
Step:3 Explosively push through your heels to jump straight up into the air, extending your legs and keeping the dumbbells by your sides.
Step:4 Land softly on your forefeet. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Begin by kneeling with the right leg on a bench and the left foot firmly planted on the floor. Lean down until your torso is parallel to the floor and place your right hand on the bench for support.Hold a dumbbell in the right hand.
Step:2 Start with your right arm bent at a 90-degree angle, with the upper arm parallel to the floor and the dumbbell close to your torso.
Step:3 Extend your arm backward by straightening your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary and focusing on squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement.

Step:4 Slowly bend your elbow to return to the starting position, maintaining control and keeping your upper arm parallel to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions before switching to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Kneeling Arnold Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by kneeling on the floor with your knees shoulder-width apart. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing your body and your elbows bent and facing down.
Step:2 Rotate your palms forward as you press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Step:3 Reverse the motion, lowering the dumbbells back to shoulder height while rotating your palms back towards your body.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Kneeling Hold to Stand Clean grip
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a kneeling position on both knees with a dumbbell in each hand, held with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) at shoulder height.

Step:2 Engage your thighs and bring one foot forward, planting it flat on the floor to form a 90-degree angle with your knee. Press through the planted foot to stand up, bringing your other foot forward to meet it, standing upright.
Step:3 Lower back into the kneeling position by stepping one foot back and lowering the knee to the floor, followed by the other knee, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating the leading leg if preferred.

name: Dumbbell kneeling squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a kneeling position with both knees on the floor, torso straight upright from knees to shoulders. Holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) at shoulder height.
Step:2 Bend your knees further pushing your hips backward to sit back onto your heels, keeping your torso upright.
Step:3 Push your hips forward and squeeze your glutes to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a controlled motion throughout.

name: Dumbbell Lateral to Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms at your sides and palms facing your body.
Step:2 Lift the dumbbells laterally to shoulder height, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 From the lateral position, move the dumbbells forward until they are directly in front of you, keeping them at shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Leaning Fly
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench holding a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms hanging down by your sides and feet flat on the floor.
Step:2 Lean your torso slightly forward, keeping your back straight. Raise both arms out to your sides at shoulder height, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells down to your sides and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Low Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your left hand. Extend your left arm down, and raise your right arm straight up overhead.

Step:2 Engage your core and hinge at your hips, bending your left knee slightly while keeping your right leg straight. Lower the dumbbell toward your left foot, keeping your back flat and left arm extended upward.
Step:3 Rotate your torso slightly to follow the movement of the dumbbell. Lower the dumbbell as close to the floor as you can while maintaining proper form.
Step:4 Reverse the motion by pushing through your left foot and straightening your torso back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell lunge alternating on the spot
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides.

Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees. Your right knee should be directly above your right ankle, and your left knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating legs with each repetition.

name: Dumbbell lunge pulse
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides.

Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees. Your right knee should be directly above your right ankle, and your left knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 From the lunge position, pulse up and down by slightly raising and lowering your body a few inches for 2-3 pulses. Keeping the movement controlled and small.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating legs with each set.

name: Dumbbell lunge to overhead press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing each other.

Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees while simultaneously pressing the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. Your right knee should be directly above your right ankle, and your left knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position while lowering the dumbbells back to shoulder height.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating legs with each set.

name: Dumbbell lying external shoulder rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on the floor with your knees slightly bent for stability. Support your head with your lower hand. Hold a dumbbell in your top hand, keeping your upper arm against your side and your elbow bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Start with your forearm across your abdomen, perpendicular to the floor.
Step:3 Rotate your shoulder to lift the dumbbell, bringing your forearm to a vertical position without moving your upper arm away from your side.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Neutral Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a flat bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip, arm bent so that the forearm is parallel to the floor. Use your free hand to support the elbow of the working arm.
Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, extend your elbow to lift the dumbbell towards the ceiling.

Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, ensuring your forearm returns to being parallel to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with your legs bent and forefeet firm on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in one hand, letting it hang straight down from your shoulder and your free hand holding the bench for support.
Step:2 Keeping your elbow slightly bent, raise the dumbbell out to the side and up to shoulder level, squeezing your shoulder blade at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Supinated Triceps Extension
Dumbbell Lying Pronation Rotation on Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat. Support your head with the lower hand. Hold a dumbbell in the top hand with your elbow resting on your side, bent at a 90-degree angle, and your palm facing your head.
Step:2 Slowly rotate your forearm, turning your palm down toward the knees while keeping your upper arm and elbow stationary.
Step:3 Rotate your forearm back to the starting position with control, ensuring the movement is smooth and steady. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms hanging straight down, and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your ribcage by squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping your elbows pointed backward.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms hanging straight down, and palms facing each other.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells out to your sides until your arms are parallel to the floor, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supine Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended towards the floor by your sides, and palms facing your thighs.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbells by bending your elbows until your forearms are parallel to the floor while rotating the dumbbells to face backward.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor and knees bent at a 90-degree angle. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms bent and forearms parallel to the floor, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Keeping your elbows stable, slowly extend your elbows to raise the dumbbells towards the ceiling until your arms are fully extended, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position by bending your elbows, ensuring your forearms return to being parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movements for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control and proper form throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Lying Triceps Extension on Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Hold one dumbbell with both hands, arms extended towards the ceiling, and palms facing each other. Position the dumbbell directly above your chest with your elbows slightly bent.
Step:2 Slowly bend your elbows to lower the dumbbell towards the floor just behind your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary and elbows pointing towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbell back towards the ceiling until your arms are fully extended, keeping your upper arms stationary throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the movements for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell narrow stance squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet close together, about hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides with your palms facing your body.
Step:2 Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees to lower your body, keeping the dumbbells at your sides.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor or as low as you can comfortably go while maintaining proper form.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand back up, straightening your legs and returning to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Floor Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on the floor with your legs straight. Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your arm slightly bent on the floor, palm facing up. Keep your free hand on the floor for support.
Step:2 Slowly raise your arm over your chest in a wide arc motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position until your arm nearly touches the floor.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Floor Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on the floor with your legs straight on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your arm extended straight up towards the ceiling, palm facing forward. Keep your free hand on the floor for support.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbell by bending your elbow until your upper arm touches the floor, bringing your elbow at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Press the dumbbell back up to the starting position by extending your elbow, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your arm extended down by your side, palm facing your thigh.
Step:2 Keeping your arm straight, lift the dumbbell directly in front of you to shoulder height, ensuring your palm is facing downwards.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench and place your right elbow on the arm pad, holding a dumbbell in a neutral grip (palm facing inward).
Step:2 Keeping your elbow pressed against the pad, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by bending your elbow.
Step:3 Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Start in a semi-lunge position with your left foot firmly planted on the floor in front and your right leg leg extended behind you lightly bent on your forefoot. Lean forward and place your left arm on your left knee for support.
Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with your arm bent at a 90-degree angle, keeping your upper arm close to your torso and parallel to the floor and your forearm pointing back.
Step:3 Extend your elbow to straighten your arm, moving the dumbbell backward until your arm is fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly bend your elbow to return the dumbbell to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand by your side with your palm facing your body. Keep your other hand on your hip or relaxed by your side.
Step:2 Lift the dumbbell out to the side, maintaining a slight bend in your elbow. Raise your arm until it is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, keeping the movement smooth and controlled.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Low Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. Extend your arm straight down in front of your body, palm facing forward.
Step:2 Lift the dumbbell in front of you sideways in a wide arc, maintaining a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Raise your arm until the dumbbell is at your eye level, keeping your shoulder muscle engaged.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your right arm extended over the pad, holding a dumbbell in your right hand using an overhand grip (palm facing down). Keep your right upper arm pressed against the pad.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps and forearm muscles.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One arm Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your forearm resting on your thigh, palm facing down, holding a dumbbell with an overhand grip (palm facing down).
Step:2 Allow your wrist to extend downward so that the dumbbell hangs towards the floor, keeping your forearm stationary.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbell upward as high as possible by flexing your wrist, focusing on engaging your forearm muscles.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your wrist. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Row (rack support)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a dumbbell rack, placing your left hand on the rack for support. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with a neutral grip, arm extended down.
Step:2 Lean downwards, step back with your right leg and keep it extended, bending both knees slightly and keep your back flat.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbell upward towards your hip, bending your elbow and keeping it close to your body, focusing on squeezing your back muscles.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with a neutral grip.
Step:2 Place your right forearm on your right thigh, allowing your wrist to extend beyond your knee. Keep your left hand resting on your left thigh for support.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbell upward by flexing your wrist, squeezing your forearm muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, extending your wrist. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press (VERSION 2)
instructions: Step:1 Begin standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand at shoulder height with your palm facing forward. Place your left hand on your hip for stability.
Step:2 Engage your core and press the dumbbell overhead by extending your right arm fully overhead.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height with control, maintaining a steady and smooth motion.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Snatch
instructions: Step:1 Start in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell on the floor between your feet. Grasp the dumbbell with your right hand, using an overhand grip, while keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:2 Drive through your heels and explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles, pulling the dumbbell upward close to your body as you rise.
Step:3 As the dumbbell reaches shoulder height, raise your hand straight up to bring the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm.
Step:4 Stand up fully, keeping the dumbbell overhead. Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Triceps Extension (on bench)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand, extending your arm straight above your shoulder. Place your left hand on your hip for support.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbell slowly behind your head by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary and your wrist straight.
Step:3 Extend your arm back to the starting position, fully straightening your elbow and squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Wide Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on a bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand, extending your arm straight above your shoulder, with a wide grip and palm facing forward.
Step:2 Lower the dumbbell slowly towards the floor by bending your elbow, until your elbow passes lower than the bench.
Step:3 Push the dumbbell back up to the starting position by extending your arm, squeezing your chest muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One arm Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with your palm facing up, and rest your right forearm on your thigh, allowing your wrist to hang slightly off your knee.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upward by curling your wrist, bringing the weight as high as possible.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, extending your wrist downward.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand and perform the same steps.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand behind an incline bench and lean your right arm on the bench's headrest, holding a dumbbell in your hand with an underhand grip (palm facing up).
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary and focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrist to turn your palm downward, transitioning to an overhand grip.

Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with the overhand grip. Rotate your wrist back to the underhand grip for the next repetition. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a dumbbell with an overhand grip (palm facing down).
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the dumbbells to hang downward.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbells upward by flexing your wrists, lifting the weight as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a dumbbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up).
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the dumbbells to hang downward.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbells upward by flexing your wrists, lifting the weights as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: dumbbell overhead extension seated
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench, holding a dumbbell with both hands and extending your arms fully overhead. Hold a dumbbell with your fingers wrapped around the dumbbell handle.
Step:2 Slowly bend your elbows, lowering the dumbbell behind your head until your forearms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Press the dumbbell back up by straightening your elbows, returning to the starting position with arms fully extended overhead.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, keeping your core engaged and back pressed against the bench.

name: dumbbell overhead extension standing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands. Hold a dumbbell with your fingers wrapped around the dumbbell handle.
Step:2 Slowly bend your elbows, lowering the dumbbell behind your head until your forearms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Press the dumbbell back up by straightening your elbows, returning to the starting position with arms fully extended overhead.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, keeping your core engaged and back straight.

name: Dumbbell Overhead Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms fully overhead with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at approximately 90 degrees. Your back knee should hover just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, maintaining the dumbbells overhead throughout the movement.
Step:4 Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Overhead Sit-up
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs bent and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in both hands, extending your arms straight overhead with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the floor into a sitting position, keeping the dumbbell directly overhead.
Step:3 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position, maintaining control and keeping the dumbbell overhead.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Plyo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands, arms lowered down in front of you.
Step:2 Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and hips, ensuring your knees face outward and keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Push through your heels to raise back to the standing position, keeping your hips forward and glutes engaged throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lower back into the squat position, maintaining control and keeping your glutes engaged. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench and place your left arm on the padding. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand with an underhand grip (palm facing up), allowing your arm to hang straight down.
Step:2 Engage your biceps and curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow. Keep your upper arm stationary against the bench.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl (Turned Torso)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench and place your left arm on the padding, twisting your torso slightly to the right. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand with an underhand grip (palm facing up), allowing your arm to hang straight down.
Step:2 Engage your biceps and curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary against the bench.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl over Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of an exercise ball. Lean forward to position your chest against the ball, and rest your upper arms on the ball. Hold a dumbbell with both hands with an underhand grip (palm facing up).
Step:2 Engage your biceps and curl the dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, ensuring your upper arms remain stationary against the ball.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Press Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and hips. Make sure your thighs are parallel to the floor and your knees do not go past your toes.
Step:3 At the bottom of the squat, stay in position and press the dumbbell forward in front of your chest twice by extending your arms fully, then bring it back to your chest.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand up and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pronate-grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms bent behind your head, keeping your arms at 45 degrees, holding the dumbbell with an overhand grip at shoulder width.
Step:2 Keeping your elbows stationary, bend your arms to lower the dumbbell behind your head.
Step:3 Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Prone Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie chest first on the bench. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended down and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Prone Incline Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie chest first on the bench. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended down and palms facing each other.
Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying across a bench, with only your upper back and shoulders supported. Your feet should be flat on the floor, and your hips slightly lowered. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed against the underside of the plates, arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head until your upper arms are in line with your torso.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbell back over your chest by contracting your chest and lats, following the same arc as you lowered it.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover (VERSION 2)
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a flat bench, with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed against the underside of the plates, arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head until your upper arms are in line with your torso.
Step:3 Pull the dumbbell back over your chest by contracting your chest and lats, following the same arc as you lowered it.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover Hip Extension on Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying with your back on an exercise ball, feet flat on the floor, and knees bent at 90 degrees. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed against the underside of the plates, arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Lower your hips towards the floor by bending your knees, while simultaneously lowering the dumbbell in an arc over your head until your upper arms are in line with your torso.

Step:3 Extend your hips back to the starting position by squeezing your glutes and lifting your hips, while simultaneously pulling the dumbbell back over your chest by contracting your chest and lats.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover on floor
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms pressed against the underside of the plates, arms extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc over your head, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until your upper arms are in line with your torso.
Step:3 Just before touching the floor, pull the dumbbell back over your chest by contracting your chest and lats, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Push Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing each other. Keep your elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees and lower your body into a quarter squat, then explosively extend your legs and perform a light jump to drive the dumbbells upward.
Step:3 Press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully, locking out your elbows at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height in a controlled manner and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell rdl stretch isometric
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your left hand, arm fully extended by your side, and your palm facing your thigh.

Step:2 Hinge at your hips, lowering the dumbbell towards the floor while raising your left leg straight behind you, keeping it in line with your body. Your left leg should move in unison with your torso.
Step:3 Continue lowering the dumbbell until your torso is parallel to the floor and you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Step:4 Hold this stretched position for the desired duration, then return to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Kneel with your right knee on a bench and your left foot firmly planted on the floor for stability. Lean forward until your torso is parallel to the floor, and place your right hand on the bench for support. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand with an overhand grip, allowing it to hang straight down from your shoulder.
Step:2 Row the dumbbell up towards your side, allowing your elbow to flare out to the side. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Hold the top position briefly, ensuring your upper arm is parallel to the floor and your elbow is pointing outward.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, allowing your arm to fully extend.

name: Dumbbell Rear Full Shrugs
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Hold the dumbbells behind your back at shoulder width, with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders as high as possible towards your ears, squeezing your shoulders at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control, allowing your arms to fully extend.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging straight down and palms facing each other.
Step:2 Hinge at the hips to lean forward, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. Your torso should be almost parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Lift the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until your arms are in line with your shoulders. Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Step your right foot back and lower your body into a lunge position, keeping your left knee over your left ankle and lowering your right knee towards the floor.
Step:3 Just before  your right knee touches the floor, push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right foot forward to stand up straight.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg stepping back. Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge from Step
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a step with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Step your right foot back off the step and lower your body into a lunge position, keeping your left knee over your left ankle and lowering your right knee towards the floor.
Step:3 Just before  your right knee touches the floor, push through your left heel to return to the starting position on the step, bringing your right foot forward to stand up straight.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg stepping back off the step. Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Renegade Row
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your feet hip-width apart and each hand holding a dumbbell, arms fully extended, and body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right hand off the floor, rowing the dumbbell towards your right hip by bending your elbow and keeping your arm close to your body.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the floor with control, returning to the plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the row with your left hand. Alternate arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying chest-first on an incline bench, with your feet planted firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging down, palms facing each other.
Step:2 With a slight bend in your elbows, raise the dumbbells out to your sides until your arms are in line with your shoulders.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, maintaining the slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse grip Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down). Let the dumbbells hang by your sides.
Step:2 Keep your upper arms close to your body. Curl the dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell reverse lunge on the spot
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing your body.
Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee is just above the floor.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right foot back to meet your left.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell reverse lunges pulses
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing your body.
Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, lowering your body until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee is just above the floor.
Step:3 Perform two small pulses by slightly raising and lowering your body while maintaining the lunge position.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right foot back to meet your left. Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, with your chest supported on the bench and your forefeet planted firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down), arms fully extended toward the floor.
Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary as you curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring your elbows remain steady.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down). Rest your forearms on your thighs, letting your wrists hang over the edge of your knees.
Step:2 Start with your wrists in a neutral position, holding the dumbbells so that they point straight down.
