Step:3 Curl the dumbbells up by extending your wrists upwards.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing your thighs). Keep your arms straight and the dumbbells close to your body.
Step:2 Hinge at the hips, pushing your hips back and lowering the dumbbells towards the floor. Keep a slight bend in your knees and maintain a neutral spine.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until the dumbbells reach just under your knees or until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings.
Step:4 Push through your heels to extend your hips and return to the starting position, bringing the dumbbells back to your thighs. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Russian Twist with Legs Floor Off
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and your feet lifted slightly off the floor, balancing on your glutes. Hold a dumbbell with both hands at chest level, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:2 Lean back slightly to form a V-shape with your torso and thighs, maintaining a straight spine.
Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, bringing the dumbbell beside your right hip while keeping your legs stable together.
Step:4 Return to the center, then rotate your torso to the left, bringing the dumbbell beside your left hip. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Scott Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your face, arms bent at 90 degrees, upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Move the dumbbells outward in an arc motion, keeping your elbows bent and slightly raised, until your arms are extended to your sides just higher than shoulder height.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back to the starting position in front of your face, maintaining the 90-degree bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat the arc motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Scott Press (360 degrees)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your face, arms bent at 90 degrees, upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Move the dumbbells outward in an arc motion, keeping your elbows bent and slightly raised, until your arms are extended to your sides just higher than shoulder height.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells back to the starting position in front of your face, maintaining the 90-degree bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat the arc motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back straight, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging at your sides, palms facing your thighs.
Step:2 Raise your right arm straight in front of you to shoulder height while rotating the dumbbell to face down, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Lower your right arm back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat by alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight on the backrest and feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your face, arms bent at 90 degrees, upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended, keeping your left dumbbell in place.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to starting position and then press the left dumbbell overhead.
Step:4 Continue to alternate arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level, elbows facing outside, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended, keeping your left dumbbell at shoulder level.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to shoulder level while simultaneously pressing the left dumbbell overhead.
Step:4 Continue to alternate arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bench Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell with both hands, positioning it behind your head.
Step:2 Begin with your elbows bent and pointed upwards, keeping your upper arms close to your head.
Step:3 Extend your elbows to lift the dumbbell upwards until your arms are fully extended, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, bending your elbows.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Arm Lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended by your sides, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Raise your arms to the sides at shoulder level, keeping a light bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your forefeet on a weight plate with heels extended to the floor, feet hip-width apart. Place a dumbbell on each knee, holding them in place with your hands.
Step:2 Lift your heels off the floor by extending your ankles, pushing through your forefeet to raise the dumbbells.
Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, squeezing your calf muscles.
Step:4 Lower your heels back just before touching the floor with control, returning to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Close Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight on the backrest and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, bringing them close in front of your face with your palms facing your head.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are extended overhead, maintaining a close grip throughout the movement.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, keeping the weights close together. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, letting your arms hang down by your sides with your palms facing your body (neutral grip).
Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows while rotating both wrists until your palms face the shoulders.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the peak of the movement and hold for a second.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit upright on a bench with your back on the backrest and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, allowing your arms to hang down by your sides. Your palms should face your thighs.
Step:2 Begin the movement by raising both dumbbells in front of you, maintaining straight arms and rotating your palms to face down as the dumbbells rise.
Step:3 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor and the dumbbells are at shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly and with control, lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, reversing the rotation of your palms to face your thighs again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit upright on a bench with your back on the backrest and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, letting your arms hang down by your sides with your palms facing your body (neutral grip).
Step:2 Begin the movement by bending your elbows, curling the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. Your palms should continue to face each other throughout the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height while keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, leaning slightly forward from your hips while keeping your back straight.
Step:2 Lift both upper arms so that they are parallel to the floor, keeping your elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. Your forearms should be hanging down, and your palms facing your body.
Step:3 Extend your arms straight back by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arm stationary. Squeeze your triceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly bend your elbows to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Let your arms hang down by your sides with your palms facing your body.
Step:2 Keep a slight bend in your elbows as you lift both arms out to the sides until they reach shoulder height,  forming a "T" shape with your body.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs with your wrists hanging over the edge of your knees.
Step:3 Begin with your wrists in a neutral position, then curl the dumbbells upward by flexing your wrists.
Step:4 Hold the contraction briefly at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell seated on exercise ball shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:3 Briefly hold the position at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise Hammer Grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your right forefoot on a weightplate. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand and place it on your right thigh near your knee.
Step:2 Push through your right forefoot to raise your heel as high as possible, lifting the dumbbell. Briefly hold this position, squeezing your calf muscle.
Step:3 Slowly lower your heel back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Dumbbell Seated Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the support pad and your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up).
Step:2 Extend your arms fully over the preacher bench pad, allowing the dumbbells to hang down in front of you.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary against the pad.
Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Reverse Close Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a reverse grip (palms facing your body). Position the dumbbells near your shoulders, elbows bent and close to your torso.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells straight up until your arms are fully extended above your head, keeping your palms facing inward.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled motion.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Reverse grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread and your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with an overhand grip (palm facing down), lean forward and place your right elbow against the inside of your right thigh.
Step:2 Allow the dumbbell to hang straight down towards the floor while keeping your arm fully extended.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps and forearms.
Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back supported, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top, ensuring your arms are straight but not locked.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell seated shoulder press parallel grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, with your elbows bent at 90 degrees at chest level, facing forward, and your palms facing each other (parallel grip).
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward by extending your elbows, until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring that your arms are straight but not locked.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to starting position following the steps in reverse. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell shrugs
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended by your sides. Your palms should be facing your thighs.
Step:2 Raise your shoulders towards your ears by contracting your trapezius muscles, lifting the dumbbells without bending your elbows.
Step:3 Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Step:4 Lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand with your arm fully extended by your side. Place your left hand behind your head.
Step:2 Slowly bend to your right side at the waist, lowering the dumbbell towards the floor.
Step:3 Bend as far as comfortably possible, feeling a stretch in your left oblique muscles.
Step:4 Return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left side.

name: Dumbbell side lunge alternating
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms at your sides.

Step:2 Take a large step to your right with your right foot, bending your right knee and lowering your hips down and back as if you are sitting into a chair. Keeping your left leg straight and rotating it until your left foot points to the ceiling.

Step:3 Lower yourself until your right thigh is parallel to the floor, ensuring your knee does not extend past your toes. The dumbbells should be hanging down towards the floor on either side of your right leg.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell side lunge left n right
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Take a large step to your right with your right foot, bending your right knee and lowering your hips down and back as if you are sitting into a chair. Keeping your left leg straight.

Step:3 Lower yourself until your right thigh is parallel to the floor, ensuring your knee does not extend past your toes. The dumbbells should be hanging down towards the floor on either side of your right leg.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Lunge Single Leg
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together, holding a dumbbell with both hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Take a large step to your left with your left foot, bending your left knee and lowering your hips down and back as if you are sitting into a chair. Keep your right leg straight.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your left thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Perform all repetitions on the left side before switching to the right side and repeating the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Side Lying One Hand Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your right side on a bench, with your legs stacked and your right elbow on the bench for support. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand with your arm resting along your left side.
Step:2 Slowly raise the dumbbell towards the ceiling, keeping your arm straight until it is fully extended.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner, focusing on engaging your shoulder muscles throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions on your left side.

name: Dumbbell Side Plank with Rear Fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by positioning yourself in a side plank on your right side, with your right elbow directly under your shoulder and both feet on the floor   shoulder-width apart. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand, with your arm extended straight out in front of your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core to lift your hips off the floor, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. Maintain this plank position throughout the exercise.
Step:3 Slowly raise the dumbbell in a wide arc motion outwards, lifting your arm until it is just higher than parallel to the floor, while slightly rotating your torso to the left.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Squat Side to Side
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell close to your chest.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg, bending your knee and pushing your hips back to lower into a side lunge. Keep your left leg straight and your chest up.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, straightening your leg.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Simultaneous Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Simultaneously curl both dumbbells upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand with your arm bent and your elbow touching the floor, at a 45-degree angle from your body.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell up by extending your arm until it is fully straightened towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back down with control, bringing your elbow back to a few inches off the floor.
Step:4 Complete the desired number of repetitions with the right arm, then switch to the left arm and repeat the movement.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Press From Close Elbow
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand, positioning your arm close to your body with your elbow touching the floor and bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell up by extending your arm until it is fully straightened towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back down with control, bringing your elbow back to the starting position close to your body and touching the floor.
Step:4 Complete the desired number of repetitions with the right arm, then switch to the left arm and repeat the movement.

name: Dumbbell Single arm Leaning Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing next to a weight cage, and grasp it with one hand for support. Lean your body slightly away from the surface, keeping your feet together. Hold a dumbbell in the other hand with your arm extended down by your side and palm facing your body.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbell out to the side until your arm reaches shoulder height, keeping a slight bend in your elbow and maintaining a controlled motion.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arm is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Carry
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Press the dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended.
Step:2 Walk forward in a straight line for the desired distance, keeping the dumbbell steady overhead.
Step:3 Once you've covered the desired distance, carefully lower the dumbbell back to your shoulder and switch to your left hand. Repeat the movement with your left arm overhead.

name: Dumbbell single arm overhead lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Press the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot into a lunge position, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, maintaining the dumbbell overhead throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell single arm row
instructions: Step:1 Place your left knee and left hand on a bench, lean your back down to almost parallel to the floor. Your right foot should be planted firmly on the floor, knee bent and slightly behind for balance. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand, arm extended towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbell towards your hip by bending your elbow, keeping it close to your body. Focus on squeezing your back muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to perform the exercise with your left arm.

name: Dumbbell single arm shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Position the dumbbell at shoulder height, by its side, with your palm facing forward and your elbow bent and your free hand on your hip.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell overhead by extending your arm until it is fully straight.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left hand.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Starfish Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your arms and legs extended in a starfish position. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand and keep the left hand firm on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your left leg and right arm simultaneously, aiming to touch the dumbbell to your left foot.
Step:3 Reach as high as possible, squeezing your abdominal muscles at the top of the movement.

Step:4 Lower your arm and leg back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to holding the dumbbell in your left hand and raising your right leg.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Underhand Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand with an underhand grip (palm facing forward). Let your arm hang straight down at your side.
Step:2 Slowly raise the dumbbell in front of you to shoulder height, keeping your arm straight and your palm facing up.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arm is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise Wall Support
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your right side facing a wall, placing your right hand on the wall for support and holding a dumbbell in your left hand. Lift your right leg off the floor, balancing on your left leg.
Step:2 Press through your eight forefoot to raise your heel off the floor as high as possible.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, squeezing your calf muscle.
Step:4 Lower your heel back to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand extended down in front of you. Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot slightly off the floor behind you.
Step:2 Begin to hinge at your hips, extending your right leg straight behind you while lowering the dumbbells towards the floor. Keep a slight bend in your left knee.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until your torso is parallel to the floor, or as far as your flexibility allows, maintaining a straight line from your head to your right heel.

Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving through your left heel and bringing your right leg forward, keeping it off the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left hand and right leg.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell across your hips with both hands. Extend your left leg straight out in front of you, keeping it in line with your right thigh.
Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your glutes. Drive through your right heel to lift your hips towards the ceiling, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your right knee.
Step:3 Hold the top position briefly, squeezing your glutes and maintaining a straight line with your body.
Step:4 Lower your hips back to the starting position with control, ensuring your left leg remains extended. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift_Female
Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your back facing a bench. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Lift your left foot back to rest on the bench behind you.

Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your right knee, keeping your torso upright. Your right knee should align over your ankle, and your left knee should lower towards the floor without touching it.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, straightening your right leg.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing on your right leg, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Lift your left leg slightly off the floor, keeping it straight and extended in front of you.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your right knee. Your left leg should remain extended in front of you without touching the floor.
Step:3 Lower until your right thigh is parallel to the floor, ensuring your knee stays aligned with your foot and doesn't go past your toes.
Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to standing position, keeping your left leg extended. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat with Support (pistol)
instructions: Step:1 Stand next to a lifting cage and hold the lifting cage bar for support with your right hand. Hold a dumbbell in your left hand, allowing it to hang down to your side. Position your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lift your right leg off the floor and extend it forward.
Step:3 Bend your right knee to lower your body into a squat position. Lower yourself as far as you can while maintaining control and balance.
Step:4 Press through the heel of your right leg to return to the starting position, fully extending your leg. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a sturdy platform, holding a dumbbell in each hand with arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lift and place your right foot on the platform, ensuring your entire foot is firm.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to lift your body onto the bench, bringing your left foot up to meet your right foot on the bench.
Step:4 Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of reps, then switch to the left leg.

name: Dumbbell Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides.
Step:2 Step your right foot forward and your left foot back, keeping your feet hip-width apart for balance.
Step:3 Lower your body into a lunge position by bending both knees until your front knee is directly above your ankle and your back knee is hovering just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Keep your chest up and shoulders back.
Step:2 Bend your knees and push your hips back as if you are sitting in a chair, lowering your body into a squat position. Ensure your knees do not extend beyond your toes.
Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the floor, keeping your weight evenly distributed through your heels.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position, squeezing your glutes at the top.

name: Dumbbell squats to shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height just in front of your shoulders, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Lower into a squat by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight and chest up until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand up while simultaneously pressing the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height as you prepare for the next squat. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended while keeping the left dumbbell at shoulder height.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to shoulder height and then press the left dumbbell overhead until your left arm is fully extended.
Step:4 Continue alternating the press between your right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides and palms facing backward.
Step:2 Raise the right dumbbell in front of you until your arm is parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position and then raise the left dumbbell in front of you until your arm is parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Continue alternating the raise between your right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Vertical Front Raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging straight down by your sides, palms facing your body.
Step:2 Raise the right dumbbell in front of you, keeping your arm straight but not locked, until it reaches shoulder height.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to the starting position and then raise the left dumbbell in front of you to shoulder height.
Step:4 Continue alternating the raise between your right and left arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Around World
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Slowly raise both dumbbells outward to the sides, keeping your arms straight, until they reach shoulder height.
Step:3 Continue lifting the dumbbells in a circular motion above your head until they meet at the top with your arms fully extended.
Step:4 Reverse the motion, lowering the dumbbells back down in the same circular path until they are by your sides again. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Behind Back Shoulders Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Your hands should be at a level behind your neck with your palms facing forward and elbows bent.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells upward overhead by extending your arms fully.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulders at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are fully extended and in line with your shoulders.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Both Arms Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your torso almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Begin with your arms bent at 90 degrees, elbows close to your sides, and dumbbells hanging down.
Step:3 Extend both arms straight back by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body. Focus on squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly bend your elbows to return the dumbbells to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell standing calf raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Keep your posture straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Slowly raise your heels off the floor by pushing through your forefeet, lifting your body upward as high as possible.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a brief moment, feeling the contraction in your calf muscles.
Step:4 Lower your heels back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise on Step
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a step platform with your heels hanging off the edge, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Position your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible by pushing through your forefeet, lifting your body upward.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a brief moment, feeling the contraction in your calf muscles.
Step:4 Lower your heels below the edge of the step, feeling a stretch in your calves. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Slightly bend your knees and lean your torso forward, placing your left hand on your left knee for support. Allow your right arm to hang straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell towards your opposite shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the peak of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches close to your shoulder.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing Curl Arnold Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand, positioned just in front of your shoulders. Your elbows should be facing down, and your palms facing your shoulders.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells overhead while rotating your wrists so your palms face forward, fully extending your arms at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Reverse the movement by lowering the dumbbells back to shoulder level, rotating your wrists back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the press and rotation for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Front Raise Above Head
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down). Let your arms hang straight down in front of your hips.
Step:2 Raise both dumbbells simultaneously in front of you, keeping your arms straight and lifting until the dumbbells are above your head.
Step:3 Hold the position briefly at the top, ensuring your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, keeping your movements slow and steady. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Hammer Drag Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). Let the dumbbells hang by your sides.
Step:2 Drag the dumbbells upward keeping the dumbbells close to your torso by pulling your elbows backward while lifting.
Step:3 Continue dragging the dumbbells until they reach the level of your lower chest, squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Bend your knees and hinge to your hips to lean forward and place your right elbow on the inside of your right thigh and your left hand on your left knee for support.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Curl Over Incline Bench
instructions: Step:1 Stand behind an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in your right hand using an underhand grip (palm facing up). Place your right arm over the bench so your upper arm rests against the incline pad.
Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and your elbow slightly bent. Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand and place your left hand to your hip for support. Raise your right arm overhead, extending it fully with your palm facing forward.
Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and your elbow close to your head. Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow.
Step:3 Extend your arm back to the starting position by straightening your elbow. Ensure your upper arm remains stationary throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height to your sides, with your palms facing forward and elbows bent.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully without locking your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height in a controlled motion.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Palms In Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at head height with your palms facing each other and elbows bent.
Step:2 Press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully without locking your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells back to head height in a controlled motion, keeping your core engaged and back straight.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. Position yourself behind a preacher bench and place the back of your upper arm on the bench arm pad.
Step:2 Start with your arm fully extended and the dumbbell in a supinated grip (palm facing up).
Step:3 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your shoulder by bending your elbow, keeping the back of your arm pressed against the bench.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). Let your arms hang straight by your sides.
Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows while rotating your wrists so your palms face down.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps muscles at the peak of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Simultaneous Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). Let your arms hang straight by your sides.
Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows while rotating your wrists so your palms face up.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps muscles at the peak of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetition.

name: Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Cross Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand with a neutral grip. Extend your right arm straight down at your side. Your left hand should be on your hip for support.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbell diagonally across your body towards your left shoulder, keeping your arm straight and maintaining a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Hold the position briefly at the top, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, keeping your movements slow and steady. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

name: Dumbbell Standing Single Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your left foot on the floor, keeping your right foot a few inches off the floor, holding a dumbbell in both hands with your arms hanging by your sides.
Step:2 Press through your left heel to raise your heel off the floor as high as possible by extending your ankle.
Step:3 Hold the position briefly at the top, squeezing your calf muscle.
Step:4 Lower your heel back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Dumbbell Standing Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands behind your head. Your elbows should be bent, and your upper arms should be close to your ears.
Step:2 Extend your arms fully by pressing the dumbbell overhead until your arms are straight. Keep your elbows close to your head.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back down behind your head by bending your elbows, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the extension and flexion of your arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Wide Simultaneous Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing slightly outwards and your arms extended down by your sides. Position your arms slightly wider than your shoulders.
Step:2 Curl both dumbbells diagonally upward simultaneously by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement when the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands with an underhand grip (palms facing forward). Let your arms hang straight down in front of your hips.
Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl your wrists upward as far as possible, bringing the dumbbell up towards your forearms.
Step:3 Squeeze your forearm muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Starfish Crunch Alternating
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your arms and legs extended out in a starfish position, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your right arm and left leg towards each other, crunching your torso and bringing the dumbbell towards your left foot.
Step:3 Lower back down to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left arm and right leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Static Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Step your right foot forward and your left foot back.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending both knees until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, keeping your feet in the same place.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions before switching to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Step up on Bench
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing in front of a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides.
Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted. Push through your right heel to lift your body onto the bench, bringing your left foot up to meet the right.
Step:3 Step down with your left foot first, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Step-up with Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing in front of a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides.

Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted. Push through your right heel to lift your body onto the bench, simultaneously lifting your left knee up towards your chest.
Step:3 Lower your left leg back down to the floor, followed by your right leg, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs with your palms facing your body.
Step:2 Keeping a slight bend in your knees, hinge at your hips and lower the dumbbells towards the floor, maintaining a straight back and keeping the dumbbells close to your legs.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, ensuring your back remains straight.
Step:4 Return to the starting position, extending your hips and standing tall. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Arm Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell with both hands extended straight above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper back off the floor, raising the dumbbell towards the ceiling as high as possible, while keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Lower your upper back, back to the floor with control, maintaining the arms extended above your chest. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Arm Twisting Sit-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell with both hands extended straight above your chest.

Step:2 Bend your core and lift your upper body off the floor, raising the dumbbell towards the ceiling as high as possible. As you crunch, twist your torso to the right, bringing the dumbbell towards your right side.

Step:3 Lower your upper body back to the floor with control, maintaining your arms extended above your chest. Repeat the movement, this time twisting to the left. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. Keep your legs straight but not locked.
Step:2 Keep your back straight and hinge at your hips, lowering the dumbbells towards the floor. Push your hips back while keeping the dumbbells close to your legs.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, ensuring your back remains straight.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving your hips forward and standing up straight, squeezing your glutes at the top. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Russian Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight just off the floor, and hold a dumbbell with both hands close to your chest. Lean back slightly to engage your core, keeping your back straight.
Step:2 Rotate your torso to the right, moving the dumbbell towards the floor beside your right hip while keeping your legs extended just off the floor.
Step:3 Rotate your torso back to the center, bringing the dumbbell back to center.
Step:4 Continue rotating your torso to the left, moving the dumbbell towards the floor beside your left hip. Return to the center. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating sides.

name: Dumbbell Suitcase Carry
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand at your side, allowing your arm to hang. Ensure your shoulders are level and your posture is upright.
Step:2 Begin walking forward in a straight line, keeping the dumbbell close to your body. Walk for the desired distance or time.
Step:3 Maintain a neutral spine and avoid leaning to one side to balance the weight. Focus on keeping your torso stable and your strides even.
Step:4 After completing the desired distance or time, switch the dumbbell to the other hand and repeat the exercise, ensuring equal work on both sides.

name: Dumbbell Sumo Squat Off Benches
instructions: Step:1 Stand between two benches with a wide stance, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, letting it hang between your legs.
Step:2 Lower yourself into a wide squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. Lower until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the squat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Supported Sissy Squat
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on a sissy squat machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your lower legs securely supported by the machine's pads. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both hands.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body by bending your knees, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Lower until your thighs are almost parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your thighs to rise back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Svend Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands. Position the dumbbell vertically in front of your chest with your palms facing each other and your fingers interlocked.
Step:2 Engage your chest and press the dumbbells together with your palms, activating your chest muscles.
Step:3 Extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height, keeping the dumbbell pressed together in your palms.
Step:4 Bring the dumbbell back to your chest. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tate Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Position the dumbbells above your chest, with your arms fully extended and your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower the dumbbells inward and towards your chest, keeping the dumbbells facing forward.
Step:3 Bring the dumbbells together just before touching your chest, elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position, extending the dumbbells upward. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: dumbbell triceps kick back single arm
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at your hips, keeping your back straight. Place your left hand on your left knee for support.
Step:2 Lift your right elbow backward to bring the dumbbell close to your torso, with your upper arm parallel to the floor and your forearm perpendicular to the floor.
Step:3 Extend your right arm fully behind you by straightening your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary. Squeeze your triceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return the dumbbell to the starting position by bending your elbow. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm and repeat.

name: dumbbell upright shoulder external rotatio
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Bend your right elbow to 90 degrees, keeping your elbow at shoulder level, extended to your side and lower your forearm vertical to the floor.
Step:2 Keep your elbow fixed at your side and slowly rotate your forearm upward, raising the dumbbell until your forearm is up vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly return the dumbbell to the starting position by rotating your forearm down. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm and repeat.

name: Dumbbell upright shoulder external rotation
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Bend your right elbow to 90 degrees, keeping your elbow at shoulder level, extended to your side and lower your forearm vertical to the floor.
Step:2 Keep your elbow fixed at your side and slowly rotate your forearm upward, raising the dumbbell until your forearm is up vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly return the dumbbell to the starting position by rotating your forearm down. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm and repeat.

name: Dumbbell V-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your legs extended straight and holding a dumbbell with both hands extended on the floor, arms fully extended.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your legs, upper body and dumbbell off the floor, bringing your legs and arms together to form a V-shape.
Step:3 Reach the dumbbell towards your feet, keeping your arms and legs as straight as possible.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs, upper body and dumbbell back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell w press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend your elbows at 90 degrees to bring the dumbbells up to shoulder height, with palms facing forward. Elbows should be pointing out and lower than shoulder level.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells upward, in an arc motion, until both dumbbells are above your head.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, keeping your elbows bent at 90 degrees.
Step:4 Repeat the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Waiter Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands vertically and elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upwards towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing forward) and arms fully extended by your sides.
Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary as you curl the dumbbells upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists to turn your palms downward (overhand grip), then lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the underhand grip at the bottom, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up). Position your upper arms on the preacher bench pad and fully extend your arms.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbells upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows.
Step:3 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists to turn your palms downward (overhand grip), then lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the underhand grip at the bottom, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbells around the world
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended down by your sides and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Slowly lift the dumbbells in a wide arc out to your sides, keeping your arms straight but not locked.
Step:3 Continue the movement until the dumbbells meet above your head, forming a full circle with your arms.

Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back down in the same wide arc to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and controlled motion throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbells bent over row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips. Let your arms hang straight down from your shoulders.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your hips, keeping your elbows close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a moment, focusing on engaging your back muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbells bent over row pronated grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips. Let your arms hang straight down from your shoulders.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your hips, keeping your elbows close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a moment, focusing on engaging your back muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbells plank to alternating row
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a high plank position with your hands gripping a dumbbell each on the floor, directly under your shoulders, and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Your feet should be slightly wider than hip-width apart for stability.
Step:2 Keeping your core tight, lift the right dumbbell off the floor, rowing it towards your right hip while balancing on your left hand and feet.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the floor with control, returning to the high plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the rowing motion with your left hand, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: dumbbells triceps kick back both arms
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at your hips and lower your upper body to almost parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Bend your elbows to bring the dumbbells close to your torso, with your upper arms parallel to the floor and your forearms perpendicular to the floor.
Step:3 Extend your arms fully behind you by straightening your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. Squeeze your triceps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return the dumbbells to the starting position by bending your elbows. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbell Burpee
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Lower the dumbbells to the floor as you squat down, placing them shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Jump your feet back into a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:3 Jump your feet back towards the dumbbells, landing in a squat position. As you stand up, lift the dumbbells off the floor.
Step:4 Jump up explosively, extending your arms overhead with the dumbbells. Land softly and immediately lower the dumbbells back to the floor to start the next repetition.

name: Dynamic Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms straight down by your sides.
Step:2 Explosively swing your arms upwards in a wide arc until they are overhead, stretching your back muscles dynamically.
Step:3 Immediately swing your arms back down to your sides in a controlled manner, allowing your back to relax.
Step:4 Repeat the movement continuously for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dynamic Leg Swing
instructions: Step:1 Stand next to a wall or sturdy object, using your right hand to support yourself and left hand on your hip. Position your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Swing your left leg forward and backward in a controlled, yet dynamic motion while lightly rotating your hips. Keep your leg straight but not locked at the knee.
Step:3 Allow the movement to be fluid, swinging your leg as high forward and backward as your flexibility allows.
Step:4 After completing the desired number of repetitions, switch sides and repeat the movement with your right leg while supporting yourself with your left hand.

name: Elbow back stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Bring both hands behind you and place them on your lower back, fingers pointing downward.
Step:3 Gently push your hips forward and lean your upper body backward, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow Extension And Supination Pronation Forearm Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you at hip level, palms open and over each other, with one hand crossing over the other.
Step:2 Keep your palms crossed over each other and perform a wrist curl by bending your wrists upward.
Step:3 Extend your wrists back down to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the wrist curl and extension movements for the desired number of repetitions, then switch the position of your hands and repeat.

name: Elbow Flexor Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand next to a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart, and extend your right arm out fully against the wall at shoulder height, palm facing the wall.
Step:2 Rotate your torso away from the wall to increase the stretch in your arm.
Step:3 Ensure your right arm is straight and press your palm firmly against the wall.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your forearm and elbow flexors, then switch to the other arm.

name: Elbow Lift Reverse Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor between two chairs, with your torso facing the ceiling and your elbows resting on the chairs, arms bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Extend your legs out in front of you, keeping them together and straight, and lift your hips into a reverse plank position, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your heels.
Step:3 Press through your elbows to lift your torso and hips slightly higher, engaging your triceps and core muscles.
Step:4 Lower your body back down by bending your elbows, keeping your torso and legs straight throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow Push Plank Up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a forearm plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming an arch line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Push through your forearms to lift your elbows a few inches off the floor, keeping your fists on the floor.
Step:3 Keep pressing through your forearms to raise your hips off the floor until your torso is straight, maintaining the plank position.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down to the floor, followed by your elbows, returning to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbows Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Bring both hands behind you and place them on your lower back, fingers pointing downward.
Step:3 Gently push your hips forward and lean your upper body backward, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow-Up and Down Dynamic Plank
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a forearm plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Lift your elbows a few inches off the floor, keeping your forearms off the floor and fists on the floor.
Step:3 Place your right hand on the floor, followed by your left hand, pushing your body up into a high plank position with your arms fully extended.
Step:4 Lower your right hand back to the floor, followed by your left hand, returning to the starting position. Repeat the movement, alternating which arm you start with each time.

name: Elevated Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on elevated surfaces just wider than shoulder-width apart. Position your feet together on the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and lower your chest towards the elevated surfaces by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle from your body.
Step:3 Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor between the elevated surfaces, maintaining a straight back and tight core throughout the movement.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elevated Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step with your heels hanging off, placing your forefeet securely on the edge. Hold onto a stable surface for balance if necessary.
Step:2 Lower your heels below the level of the platform to feel a stretch in your calf muscles.
Step:3 Press through your forefeet to raise your heels as high as possible, fully contracting your calf muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Hands Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself face down on an exercise ball with your hips resting on the ball and your feet anchored against a wall or stable surface for balance.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head, elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lower your upper body towards the floor, rounding your back slightly.
Step:4 Lift your upper body back up until your body forms a straight line from your head to your hips. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise ball back stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart, and your hands resting on your thighs.
Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward and roll your body down the ball, allowing your back to drape over the ball until your lower back is supported.
Step:3 Extend your arms at your sides, allowing them to hang naturally to the floor, and relax into the stretch, letting your spine gently curve over the ball.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and allowing your back muscles to relax.

name: Exercise Ball Body Saw
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your forearms resting on an exercise ball and your body forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the ball a few inches away from your body.
Step:3 Reverse the motion by rolling the ball closer to your forearms.
Step:4 Continue the rolling motion for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a straight body line throughout.

name: Exercise ball hip flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball in a lunge position with your left foot flat on the floor in front of you and your right leg extended behind you, the ball supporting your hips.
Step:2 Lower your hips downwards towards the floor, allowing the ball to support your weight and feeling a stretch in your right hip flexor.
Step:3 Keep your torso upright and your core engaged as you hold the stretch.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then switch legs and repeat on the other side.

name: Exercise ball lat stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin on the floor in a tabletop position with your hands and knees on the floor.
Step:2 Have an exercise ball on your right side and position your right hand on the ball, keeping your arm bent at 90 degrees.
Step:3 Slowly roll the ball forward with your right hand, extending your right arm overhead and lowering your chest lightly towards the floor, feeling the stretch along your back.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly roll the ball back towards you to return to the starting position. Repeat on the left side.

name: Exercise Ball Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your arms at your sides, palms facing down. Place your heels and calves on top of an exercise ball.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your heels. This is your starting position.
Step:3 Bend your knees and roll the ball towards your glutes by pulling your heels in. Keep your hips elevated and maintain the straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:4 Slowly extend your legs, rolling the ball back to the starting position while keeping your hips lifted. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise ball lower back dynamic stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin on your hands and feet with your arms and legs straight, positioning an exercise ball under your hips.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body onto the ball, allowing it to support your hips and torso, while keeping your arms and legs straight and your hips bent.
Step:3 Relax into the stretch for a second, letting your back gently arch over the ball and feeling a stretch in your lower back.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise ball lower back prone stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin on your hands and feet with your arms and legs straight, positioning an exercise ball under your hips.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body onto the ball, allowing it to support your hips and torso, while keeping your arms and legs straight and your hips bent.
Step:3 Relax into the stretch, letting your back gently arch over the ball and feeling a stretch in your lower back.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise ball lying side lat stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your side with an exercise ball positioned under your armpit and lower ribs. Extend your top leg straight and bend your lower leg, placing the foot flat on the floor for stability.
Step:2 Extend your top arm on your side, keeping it along the line of your body, and allow your bottom arm to hang in a comfortable position for support over the ball.
Step:3 Allow your body to relax over the ball, feeling a stretch along the side of your torso and through your latissimus dorsi (lats).
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Slowly roll back to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

name: Exercise Ball Lying Side Lat Stretch V.2
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your side with an exercise ball positioned under your armpit and lower ribs. Extend your top leg straight and bend your lower leg, placing the foot flat on the floor for stability.
Step:2 Allow your bottom arm to hang in a comfortable position for support over the ball and extend your left arm overhead, reaching it along the line of your body.
Step:3 Allow your body to relax over the ball, feeling a stretch along the side of your torso and through your latissimus dorsi (lats).
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Slowly roll back to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

name: Exercise Ball One Legged Diagonal Kick Hamstring Curl
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your arms at your sides, palms facing down. Place your left heel and calf on top of an exercise ball, with your right leg extended straight and aligned with your hips.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your left heel.
Step:3 Bend your left knee and roll the ball diagonally towards the middle of your hips, pulling your heel in while simultaneously raising your right leg upwards along the line of your hips.
Step:4 Extend your left leg, rolling the ball back to the starting position, while lowering your right leg back to the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the movement with your right heel and calf on the ball and your left leg extending upwards.

name: Exercise ball seated hamstring stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart, and your back straight.
Step:2 Extend your right leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the floor and your toes pointing up.

Step:3 Slowly hinge at your hips, leaning forward while keeping your back straight, and reach towards your right toes with your right hand. Feel the stretch along the back of your right leg (hamstring).
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Return to the starting position and repeat with your left leg.

name: Exercise ball seated quad stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Step:2 Slowly roll forward until your back is supported on the ball, keeping your shoulders and head relaxed on the ball, and place your arms at your sides for balance.
Step:3 Bend your left leg with your foot flat on the floor for support. Bend your right leg, placing the forefoot on the floor and the heel on the ball to feel the stretch in your right quadriceps.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Slowly return to the starting position and repeat with the opposite leg.

name: Exercise ball sit ups
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart, leaning back so the ball supports your lower back and hips. Place your hands behind your head.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body until vertical to the floor, performing a sit-up while keeping your chin slightly tucked and your back straight.
Step:3 Lower your upper body back down to the starting position with control, maintaining tension in your core.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Wall Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place an exercise ball between your lower back and a wall. Lean slightly into the ball for support.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight and allowing the ball to roll along your back.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor, ensuring your knees do not extend past your toes.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, straightening your legs. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Explosive push ups
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standard push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping your core tight and your body straight.
Step:3 Push through your hands explosively to extend your arms rapidly, generating maximum force without lifting your hands off the floor.
Step:4 Lower into the next push-up with control, immediately repeating the explosive movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Extended Side Angle
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wide apart, about 3-4 feet, with your right foot turned out 90 degrees and your left foot slightly turned in. Place your hands on your hips.
