Step:2 Bend your right knee, ensuring it aligns over your right ankle, and lower your right thigh until it is parallel to the floor. Extend your left leg straight.

Step:3 Lean to your right side by bending your right knee further and place your right elbow on your right thigh. Raise your left arm overhead, creating a straight line from your left hand to your left foot.
Step:4 Hold the position for a moment, then return to the starting position with control. Repeat on the other side.

name: Extended side Angle Pose With Block
Extended side Angle Pose With Block_Female
Extension And Inclination Neck Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back straight and shoulders relaxed.
Step:2 Slowly rotate your head to the left side while diagonally lowering your head, bringing your chin towards your left shoulder to feel a stretch in your neck.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, breathing deeply and steadily.

Step:4 Return to the neutral position and repeat on the other side by rotating your head to the right and diagonally lowering your head towards your right shoulder. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Extension Of Arms In Vertical Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, your back straight, and your core engaged.
Step:2 Raise your arms overhead, interlocking your fingers and turning your palms upward.
Step:3 Stretch upwards as much as possible, lengthening your spine and reaching towards the ceiling. Hold the position for 15-30 seconds.
Step:4 Slowly release the stretch and bring your arms back down to your sides. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar biceps curl close grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar with hands closer than shoulder-width, palms facing forward, and your arms fully extended down.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar biceps curl normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar with hands at shoulder-width, palms facing forward, and your arms fully extended down.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar biceps curl wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar with hands just wider than shoulder-width, palms facing forward, and your arms fully extended down.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your chest by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar cable curl wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar attached to the low pulley, hands just wider than shoulder-width, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulder by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar cable curl wide grip crossover machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar attached to the low pulley of a crossover machine, hands just wider than shoulder-width, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulder by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary and close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez bar overhead extensions standing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar with an overhand grip. Raise the bar overhead until your arms are fully extended, with your hands positioned closer together on the bar.
Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your head and slowly lower the bar behind your head by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Lower the bar until your arms are fully bent.
Step:4 Extend your elbows to raise the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms overhead.

name: Ez bar seated close grip shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support, holding an EZ bar with a close overhand grip. Position the bar at shoulder height with your palms facing your neck and your elbows pointing forward.
Step:2 Press the bar overhead by extending your elbows upward.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms without locking your elbows at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the bar back to the starting position at shoulder height with control, keeping your elbows pointing forward.

name: EZ Bar Seated Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench holding an EZ bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up). Rest your forearms on your thighs with your wrists just beyond the edge, allowing the bar to hang down.
Step:2 Curl your wrists upward by flexing your forearms, lifting the EZ bar as high as possible while keeping your forearms stationary on your thighs.
Step:3 Squeeze your forearms at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the bar back to the starting position in a controlled manner, allowing your wrists to fully extend.

name: EZ Bar Standing Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ bar with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Let the bar hang in front of your thighs.
Step:2 Raise the EZ bar directly in front of you to shoulder height until parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, squeezing your shoulder muscles.
Step:4 Lower the bar back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: EZ Barbell Anti Gravity Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest first on an incline bench, holding an EZ barbell with palms facing the floor, hands positioned shoulder-width apart. Hold the barbell close to your shoulders, just under your face, with elbows bent.
Step:2 Press the barbell forward in a straight line until your arms are fully extended, keeping the bar parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, ensuring your arms are straight and the barbell is fully extended forward.
Step:4 Return the barbell back to the starting position with control, bringing it close to your shoulders. Repeat the exercise.

name: EZ Barbell Close grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ barbell with a close grip (hands positioned closer than shoulder-width apart) and palms facing up.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.

name: EZ Barbell Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ barbell with a normal grip (hands positioned at shoulder-width apart) and palms facing up.
Step:2 Curl the barbell upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.

name: Fast feet
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Quickly alternate lifting your feet off the floor, moving them up and down rapidly as if running in place, but without moving forward.
Step:3 Keep your core engaged and maintain a slight bend in your knees to stay light on your feet.
Step:4 Continue the rapid foot movement for the desired duration, maintaining a steady and controlled pace.

name: Feet together barbell squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip. Ensure the barbell is balanced and rests comfortably on your traps.
Step:2 Slowly lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hips, keeping your knees aligned with your toes.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor, or as low as your flexibility allows, without compromising form.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand back up, extending your knees and hips to return to the starting position.

name: Fire hydrant bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin on the floor in an all-fours position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Keeping your knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift your right leg out to the side until your thigh is parallel to the floor. Keep your hips level and avoid rotating your torso.
Step:3 Hold the position for a moment, then lower your right leg back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left leg and repeat.

name: Fire hydrant circle bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin on the floor in an all-fours position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Keeping your knee bent at a 90-degree angle, lift your right leg out to the side until your thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Move your right leg in a circular motion, making small controlled circles with your knee while keeping your hips level and avoiding torso rotation.
Step:4 Complete the desired number of circles, then lower your right leg back to the starting position. Repeat on the left side.

name: Fixed bar stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a fixed vertical bar. Position your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the bar with both hands, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Step back slightly and lean your hips backward, allowing your arms to extend fully and your upper body to lean forward. Keep your back straight and your knees bent.
Step:3 Lean backwards and down to the floor while pulling back with your hips to feel a deep stretch in your shoulders, upper back, and lats.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Slowly return to the starting position by stepping forward and releasing the bar.

name: Flat bench cable fly
instructions: Step:1 Position a flat bench between two cable machines with the pulleys set at the lowest position. Attach handles to the pulleys and lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the floor.
Step:2 Grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing up, and extend your arms out to your sides at chest level.
Step:3 Raise the handles over your chest in a wide arc, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, squeezing your chest at the top.
Step:4 Slowly bring the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Floor cable Resistance band press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Position a resistance band under your upper back, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Position your elbows on the floor bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Press the handles straight up towards the ceiling until your arms are fully extended, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flutter kicks
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms at your sides, palms facing down. Place your hands under your hips for added support if needed.
Step:2 Lift your legs off the floor a few inches, keeping them straight and close together.
Step:3 Quickly alternate kicking your legs up and down in a small, controlled motion, engaging your core throughout the movement.
Step:4 Continue the flutter kicks for the desired duration, maintaining a steady and controlled pace. Lower your legs back to the floor to complete the exercise.

Front raise Resistance bands
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the resistance band under both feet. Hold the handles of the resistance band with your palms facing backwards and your arms extended down in front of you.
Step:2 Raise your arms straight in front of you to shoulder height, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Front raises barbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing your hips), hands placed at shoulder-width.
Step:2 Lift the barbell in front of you by raising your arms straight out until they are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Hold the barbell at the top of the movement for a brief moment, ensuring your shoulders are fully engaged.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position in a controlled manner, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement.

name: Front raises dumbbell seated
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down), arms hanging down by your sides.
Step:2 Lift the dumbbells in front of you by raising your arms straight forward until they are at head height.
Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at the top of the movement for a brief moment, ensuring your shoulders are fully engaged.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Front shoulder stretch with bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a bar with both hands, palms facing down, and hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your arms straight down in front of you at shoulder height, keeping your back straight and core engaged.
Step:3 Gently raise the bar overhead and bend them both at 90 degrees to lower them until you feel a stretch in your shoulders.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. Repeat as needed.

name: Front squats dumbbell low
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly out. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, hanging by your sides, with your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hinging at your hips, pushing your knees lightly outwards as you descend.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are just lower than parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Front squats dumbbell over shoulders
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Position the dumbbells over your shoulders with your palms facing forward and elbows pointing down.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hinging at your hips, pushing your knees lightly outwards as you descend.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are just lower than parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Front squats kettlelbell over shoulders
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand. Place the kettlebells resting on opposite shoulders with your palms facing down and elbows pointing forward.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hinging at your hips, pushing your knees lightly outwards as you descend.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Full planche push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a full planche position with your hands placed on the floor shoulder-width apart and your body parallel to the floor, fully supported by your hands. Your legs should be extended straight behind you, and your core and glutes engaged to maintain a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a horizontal position throughout the movement.
Step:3 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting planche position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining control and stability throughout the exercise.

Glute bridge with abduction bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place your arms at your sides with palms facing down.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes and lift your hips towards the ceiling until your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 While holding the bridge position, spread your knees apart as far as comfortable, keeping your feet flat on the floor.
Step:4 Bring your knees back together, then lower your hips back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Goblet kettlebell squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands, gripping at the handle.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and hinging at your hips.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Push through your heels to return to the starting position, extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Good morning resistace band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing a resistance band under both feet. Hold a handle with each hand and place it close to your shoulders.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips to lower your torso forward until it is almost parallel to the floor, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position by extending your hips and knees to raise your torso.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Good mornings barbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip.
Step:2 Begin to hinge at your hips, pushing your hips back while lowering your torso towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving your hips forward and raising your torso back up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Good mornings dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bring the dumbbells at shoulder height, with your elbows bent and pointing forward.
Step:2 Begin to hinge at your hips, pushing your hips back while lowering your torso towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the floor, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving your hips forward and raising your torso back up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Good mornings kettlebell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell with both hands at chest height. Keep your elbows bent and pointing downward.
Step:2 Begin to hinge at your hips, pushing your hips back while lowering your torso towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the floor, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving your hips forward and raising your torso back up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Gym Elliptical Machine Fast Speed
instructions: Step:1 Step on the elliptical machine and place your feet securely on the pedals. Grip the handles with both hands for stability.
Step:2 Begin moving your legs in a smooth, elliptical motion, coordinating with the handles as they move back and forth. Start at a moderate pace to get comfortable with the movement.
Step:3 Gradually increase your speed to a fast pace, maintaining a smooth and controlled motion with both your legs and arms.
Step:4 Continue pedaling and moving the handles at a fast pace for the desired duration.

name: Gym Rowing Machine Fast Speed
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet securely strapped into the footrests, knees bent, and hands grasping the handle with an overhand grip.
Step:2 Push through your legs to extend your knees and drive your body backward, keeping your arms straight until your legs are almost fully extended.
Step:3 Just before your legs are fully extended, pull the handle towards your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Reverse the motion by extending your arms forward first, then bending your knees to return to the starting position. Repeat the motion at a fast pace for the desired duration.

name: Hack Squat Machine Squat
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the hack squat machine with your shoulders under the pads and your feet shoulder-width apart on the foot platform. Keep your back pressed against the backrest.
Step:2 Release the safety handles and slowly lower your body by bending your knees until your thighs are parallel to the foot platform.
Step:3 Push through your heels to extend your legs and return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Half burpees
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a high plank position with your hands placed directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Quickly jump your feet forward towards your hands, landing with your heels on the floor in a squat position.
Step:3 Immediately jump your feet back to return to the high plank position, keeping your body straight and your core engaged.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a quick and controlled pace.

name: Hammer curl Resistance band simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the resistance band under both feet. Hold the handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended down at your sides.
Step:2 Curl the handles up towards your shoulders simultaneously by bending your elbows, keeping your palms facing each other throughout the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: HAMMER STRENGTH ISO-LATERAL LEG CURL Alternating Legs_Female
equipments: Hammer Strength Iso-Lateral Leg Curl Machine
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the Hammer Strength Iso-Lateral Leg Curl machine, placing your ankles under the leg pads and holding the handles on the sides of the machine for stability. Start with both legs fully extended.
Step:2 Curl one leg by bending your knee and pulling your ankle towards your glutes, keeping the other leg extended.
Step:3 Squeeze your hamstrings at the top of the movement and slowly lower your leg back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat with the other leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

Hamstring lying curl up stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your chest until thigh is vertical to the floor, interlacing your fingers behind your thigh.
Step:3 Slowly straighten your right leg, extending your heel towards the ceiling and feeling the stretch in your hamstring. Keep your left leg extended and flat on the floor.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly bend your right knee and lower your leg back to the starting position. Repeat on the left side.

name: Hamstring lying straight leg stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lift your right leg towards the ceiling, keeping it straight. Use both hands to gently hold the back of your right leg, just below the knee or higher if possible.
Step:3 Pull your right leg gently towards your torso, feeling the stretch in your hamstring. Keep your left leg extended and flat on the floor.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly lower your right leg back to the starting position. Repeat on the left side.

name: Handstand push on chair
instructions: Step:1 Begin by placing a sturdy chair against a wall for stability. Position yourself in front of the chair, with your back facing it.
Step:2 Place your hands on the floor slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, about a foot away from the chair. Kick up into a handstand position, with your feet resting on the seat of the chair.
Step:3 Slowly lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight and your core engaged.
Step:4 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting handstand position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging knee raises
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward or towards each other. Allow your body to hang straight with your feet off the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and, keeping your legs together, bend your knees and lift them towards your chest.
Step:3 Raise your knees as high as comfortably possible, aiming to bring them towards your chest.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging oblique crunches
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward or towards each other. Allow your body to hang straight with your feet off the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and, keeping your legs together, bend your knees and lift them towards your right elbow, twisting your torso to engage your obliques.
Step:3 Raise your knees as high as comfortably possible, aiming to bring them towards your elbow.

Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement, this time lifting your knees towards your left elbow. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Heel touches
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Position your arms along your sides with your palms facing down.
Step:2 Lift your shoulders slightly off the floor, engaging your core and keeping your neck relaxed.
Step:3 Reach your right hand towards your right heel, bending your torso to the side. Return to the center and then reach your left hand towards your left heel.
Step:4 Alternate sides in a controlled manner, maintaining the contraction in your core throughout the exercise. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: High cable kneeling crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a high pulley on a cable machine. Kneel down facing the machine, holding the rope handles with both hands, and position them close to your head.
Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core muscles topull the rope down by crunching your torso towards your knees, bringing your elbows towards your thighs.
Step:3 Just before your elbows touch your thighs, return to the starting position with control, keeping the tension on the cable.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: High knee twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms raised to shoulder height in front of you, palms facing down.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards your left elbow while simultaneously twisting your torso to the right, engaging your core.
Step:3 Return to the starting position, then lift your left knee towards your right elbow while twisting your torso to the left.
Step:4 Alternate sides in a controlled manner, maintaining a steady rhythm. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: High knees
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Begin by lifting your right knee towards your chest as high as possible while simultaneously swinging your left arm forward.
Step:3 Quickly switch to lift your left knee towards your chest while swinging your right arm forward, mimicking a running motion.
Step:4 Continue to alternate knees rapidly, maintaining a steady rhythm and engaging your core. Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: High plank
instructions: Step:1 Begin on the floor on your hands and knees. Position your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Extend your legs straight back, one at a time, coming onto the balls of your feet to form a straight line from your head to your heels. Your body should be in a high plank position.
Step:3 Engage your core, glutes, and legs to maintain a straight body line. Keep your shoulders directly over your wrists.
Step:4 Hold the plank position for the desired amount of time, maintaining proper form and steady breathing.

name: High Resistance band kneeling crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to a high anchor point. Kneel down facing the anchor point, holding the handles of the resistance band with both hands, bend your arms at 90 degrees to bring your hands close to your face, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Pull the resistance band down by crunching your torso towards your knees, bringing your elbows towards your thighs.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, keeping the tension on the band.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hold the world med ball chest press
Hold the world med ball chest press_Female
Hollow hold
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms stretched overhead.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your shoulders and legs off the floor, keeping your lower back pressed into the floor. Your body should form a slight curve with your arms and legs elevated.
Step:3 Hold this position, maintaining tension in your core and keeping your lower back flat against the floor.
Step:4 Continue to hold the position for the desired duration, then slowly lower your shoulders and legs back to the starting position.

name: In and out squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart, and clasp your hands in front of your chest.
Step:2 Lower your hips, jump up and land into a squat position with your knees bent, thighs parallel to the floor, and feet placed wider than your shoulder width.
Step:3 Then lower your hips again, jump up, and land into a squat position with your knees bent, thighs parallel to the floor, and feet placed hip-width apart this time.
Step:4 Repeat by jumping in and out alternately.

name: In and out squats jump bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, feet shoulder-width apart, and clasp your hands in front of your chest.
Step:2 Lower your hips, jump up and land into a squat position with your knees bent, thighs parallel to the floor, and feet placed wider than your shoulder width.
Step:3 Then lower your hips again, jump up, and land into a squat position with your knees bent, thighs parallel to the floor, and feet placed hip-width apart this time.
Step:4 Repeat by jumping in and out alternately.

Step:3 Then lower your hips again, jump up, and land into a squat position with your knees bent, thighs parallel to the floor, and feet placed hip-width apart this time.
Step:4 Repeat by jumping in and out alternately.

name: Incline bench cable fly
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench between two cable machines with the pulleys positioned at the middle setting. Lie back on the bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grasp a handle in each hand, with your palms facing up and your arms extended to your sides.
Step:2 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and your back pressed firmly against the bench.
Step:3 Raise the handles opposite your chest in a wide arc, until your arms are level with your chest, squeezing your chest muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the handles back the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: incline diamond push up On Bench
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself facing a bench. Place your hands on the edge of the bench close together so that your thumbs and index fingers form a diamond shape.
Step:2 Step your feet back to extend your legs fully, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core to maintain stability.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the bench by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline diamond push up on bench
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself facing a bench. Place your hands on the edge of the bench close together so that your thumbs and index fingers form a diamond shape.
Step:2 Step your feet back to extend your legs fully, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core to maintain stability.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the bench by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:4 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline dumbbell curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an adjustable bench to a 45-degree incline and sit back against it with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended down by your sides, palms facing forward (supinated grip).
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your elbows close to your torso. Slowly curl both dumbbells up towards your shoulders simultaneously, maintaining the supinated grip with your palms facing upward.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline lateral raises dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Adjust an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie chest-first against it, with your feet firmly planted on the floor for stability.
Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other), allowing the dumbbells to hang down towards the floor in line with your shoulders.
Step:3 Keeping your arms slightly bent at the elbows, raise the dumbbells up and out to the sides until they reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline push ups on chair
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a chair and place your hands on top, close to the edge, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Step your feet back to extend your legs behind you, forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body straight. Lower your chest towards the chair by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your chest is close to the chair, then push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push-Up (on box)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a sturdy box and place your hands on top, close to the edge, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Step your feet back to extend your legs behind you, forming a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body straight. Lower your chest towards the box by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your chest is close to the box, then push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intermediate hip flexor and quad stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your stomach with your legs extended and your arms at your sides. Position an elastic cable around your right ankle.
Step:2 Bend your right knee to bring your foot towards your glutes, holding the elastic cable in your both hands.
Step:3 Gently pull on the cable to bring your foot closer to your glutes, feeling the stretch in your quadriceps. Hold this position for a moment.

Step:4 Extend your right leg lightly backwards, allowing the cable to provide resistance and deepen the stretch in your hip flexor and quadriceps. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Inverted rows on smith machine
instructions: Step:1 Position a bar on the smith machine at about waist height. Lie on your back underneath the bar with your legs extended and your heels on the floor.
Step:2 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Iron cross stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your arms extended out to your sides, forming a T-shape, and your legs extended straight.
Step:2 Lift your right leg towards the ceiling, keeping it straight, and then lower it across your body towards your left hand while keeping your shoulders flat on the floor.
Step:3 Allow your right leg to lower as far as comfortably possible, feeling a stretch in your lower back, glutes, and hamstrings.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly return your right leg to the starting position. Repeat on the other side with your left leg.

name: Iso Lateral Shoulder Press Alternate Arms
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the Iso-Lateral Shoulder Press machine, back pressed against the backrest and feet flat on the floor. Grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press one handle upward by extending your arm fully while keeping the other arm stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder muscles at the top of the movement and slowly return the handle to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat with the other arm, alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jack knives
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms stretched on your sides.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your upper body and legs towards each other, reaching your hands towards your feet. Engage your core to lift both your torso and legs.
Step:3 Try to touch your hands to your feet at the top of the movement, forming a "V" shape with your body.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body and legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jogging
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Begin jogging by taking short, quick steps, lifting your knees slightly higher than walking pace.
Step:3 Swing your arms naturally with each step, keeping them bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:4 Maintain a steady, comfortable pace and continue jogging for the desired duration or distance.

name: Jump Rope alternating foot
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together, holding a jump rope with the handles in each hand. Position the rope behind you, ready to swing it over your head.
Step:2 Swing the rope over your head and, as it passes under your feet, lift one foot off the floor, quickly followed by the other foot, allowing the rope to pass beneath both feet in succession.
Step:3 Continue to alternate feet with each jump, lifting one foot after the other, maintaining a steady rhythm and keeping your jumps low and controlled.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions, ensuring a smooth and continuous motion.

Step:3 Land softly on your forefeet and immediately swing the rope over your head again for the next jump.
Step:4 Continue jumping at a steady rhythm, maintaining a smooth and continuous motion for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

Step:3 Immediately perform a second smaller bounce while keeping the rope in motion and preparing for the next swing.
Step:4 Continue with the double bounce rhythm, maintaining a smooth and controlled motion for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Jump Rope face pull
instructions: Step:1 Loop the jump rope over a vertical bar or similar stable structure, ensuring the rope is at about hip height. Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles of the jump rope with both hands.
Step:2 Step back slightly to create tension in the rope, keeping your core engaged and your back straight.
Step:3 Pull the rope towards your face by bending your elbows and bringing your hands towards your ears, engaging your upper back and shoulder muscles.
Step:4 Extend your arms back out to the starting position with control. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, keeping your chest up and your core engaged.
Step:3 Explosively jump up, extending your legs fully and swinging your arms up for momentum.
Step:4 Land softly back into the squat position with your knees bent and your hips pushed back. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jumping jack
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Jump your feet out to the sides while simultaneously raising your arms overhead, forming an "X" shape with your body.
Step:3 Quickly jump back to the starting position with your feet together and your arms at your sides.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions, maintaining a steady rhythm.

name: Kettlebell bulgarian split squat right
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a bench, holding a kettlebell in each hand with arms hanging by your sides. Place your right foot on the bench behind you.
Step:2 Keep your left foot firmly planted on the floor and lower your body by bending your left knee, descending until your left thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Press through your left heel to return to the starting position, straightening your leg.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell bulgarian split squat right side view
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a bench, holding a kettlebell in each hand with arms hanging by your sides. Place your left foot on the bench behind you.
Step:2 Keep your right foot firmly planted on the floor and lower your body by bending your right knee, descending until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Press through your right heel to return to the starting position, straightening your leg.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell half kneeling shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a half-kneeling position with your right knee on the floor and your left foot flat on the floor in front of you. Hold a kettlebell in your right hand, racked at shoulder height with your elbow bent, facing the floor, and close to your body.
Step:2 Press the kettlebell overhead by extending your right arm fully, keeping your wrist straight and in line with your shoulder.
Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell kneeling one arm shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a kneeling position on both knees with your torso upright. Hold a kettlebell in your right hand at shoulder height, with your elbow bent, facing the floor, and close to your body.
Step:2 Press the kettlebell overhead by extending your right arm fully, keeping your wrist straight and aligned with your shoulder.
Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell seesaw press
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. Your elbows should be bent, facing the floor and your palms facing inward.
Step:2 Press the kettlebell in your right hand overhead by extending your right arm fully while slightly leaning your torso to your left side.
Step:3 Lower the right kettlebell back to shoulder height and then press the kettlebell in your left hand overhead by extending your left arm fully and slightly leaning your torso to the right side.
Step:4 Continue alternating the presses for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell single arm clean and press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the kettlebell placed on the floor between your feet. Bend your knees and hinge at your hips to grab the kettlebell with your right hand.

Step:2 Explosively extend your hips and knees to lift the kettlebell off the floor and swing it up to shoulder height. As the kettlebell rises, rotate your wrist to catch it in a rack position with your elbow bent and close to your body.
Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead by extending your right arm fully, keeping your wrist straight and aligned with your shoulder.
Step:4 Lower the kettlebell back to the rack position with control, then return it to the starting position on the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left hand.

name: Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly
Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly_Female
Kettlebell single leg glute bridge pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, holding a kettlebell with both hands extended straight on the floor. Extend your right leg upwards bent at 90 degrees.

Step:2 Press through your left heel to lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your left knee. Simultaneously, extend the kettlebell overhead with both arms, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower your hips back to the floor while bringing the kettlebell back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left leg extended and perform the same motion.

name: Kettlebell situp press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your legs straight on the floor, holding a kettlebell with both hands at your chest.
Step:2 Lift your upper body off the floor until it is vertical to the floor, and then press the kettlebell overhead by extending your arms.
Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back close to your chest.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

name: Kettlebell split squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides. Take a step forward with your right foot and position your left foot back, standing on the ball of your left foot.
Step:2 Bend both knees to lower your body into a split squat. Your back knee should hover just above the floor, and your front thigh should be parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, fully extending both legs.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and perform the same number of repetitions on the other side.

name: Kettlebell squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell with each hand hanging by your sides.
Step:2 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if sitting in a chair.
Step:3 Continue lowering yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor, making sure your knees track over your toes.
Step:4 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position, fully extending your legs.

name: Kettlebell Standing Bottoms-up One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand with the bell facing up (bottoms-up position). Place your  left hand on your hip.
Step:2 Press the kettlebell overhead by extending your elbow, keeping your wrist straight.
Step:3 Once your arm is fully extended overhead, pause for a second to fully activate the shoulder muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back to the starting position with control, keeping the bottoms-up orientation throughout the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Step Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a bench, holding a kettlebell in each hand with your arms hanging at your sides.
Step:2 Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pressing through your heel to lift your body up. Bring your left foot up to meet your right foot on the bench.
Step:3 Step down with your left foot first, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Step Up_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a bench, holding a kettlebell in each hand with your arms hanging at your sides.
Step:2 Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pressing through your heel to lift your body up. Bring your left foot up to meet your right foot on the bench.
Step:3 Step down with your left foot first, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell strict press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand, close to the front of your shoulder. The kettlebell should rest against the back of your wrist, with your palm facing inward and your elbow close to your body facing down.
Step:2 Press the kettlebell directly overhead by extending your arm upward, keeping your wrist straight.
Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position with control, returning it to shoulder height.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left hand and perform the exercise on the other side.

name: Kettlebell suitcase squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand next to your right thigh, with your arm extended. Your left arm can hang by your side or be extended in front of you for counterbalance.
Step:2 Push your hips back as if sitting into a chair to lower your body into a squat until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position, maintaining a straight back and engaged core.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch the kettlebell to your left hand and perform the exercise on the other side.

name: Kettlebell sumo deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Place a kettlebell on the floor between your feet. Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointed slightly outward.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and bend your knees to lower your body, reaching down to grasp the kettlebell handle with both hands, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Step:3 Push through your heels to lift the kettlebell off the floor, extending your hips and knees simultaneously.
Step:4 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Sumo Deadlift with High Pull
instructions: Step:1 Place a kettlebell on the floor between your feet. Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointed slightly outward.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and bend your knees to lower your body, reaching down to grasp the kettlebell handle with both hands, keeping your back straight and chest up.

Step:3 Push through your heels to lift the kettlebell off the floor, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. As you reach the standing position, explosively pull the kettlebell upward towards your chin by bending your elbows and keeping them pointed outward.
Step:4 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell sumo squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold a kettlebell with both hands close to your chest.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips while bending your knees to lower your body into a squat.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor or slightly below.
Step:4 Push through your heels to rise back to the starting position, fully extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell sumo squat (version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold a kettlebell with both hands, letting it hang down between your legs.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips while bending your knees to lower your body into a squat.
Step:3 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the floor or slightly below.
Step:4 Push through your heels to rise back to the starting position, fully extending your hips and knees. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell sumo squat off stepbox
instructions: Step:1 Stand between two stepboxes with a wide stance, toes pointed slightly outward. Hold a kettlebell with both hands, letting it hang between your legs.
Step:2 Lower yourself into a wide squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. Lower until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Repeat the squat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell swing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Place a kettlebell on the floor between your feet. Bend at your hips and knees to reach forward and grab the kettlebell with both hands, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips to swing the kettlebell back between your legs, allowing a slight bend in your knees.

Step:3 Drive through your hips, extending them forcefully to swing the kettlebell forward and up to shoulder height. Allow the momentum to carry the kettlebell upwards, keeping your arms straight but not locked.
Step:4 As the kettlebell begins to descend, hinge at your hips again to let it swing back between your legs, preparing for the next repetition. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell swing (Version 2)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Place a kettlebell vertically on the floor between your feet. Bend at your hips and knees to reach forward and grab the kettlebell with both hands, interlocking your fingers.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips to swing the kettlebell back between your legs, allowing a slight bend in your knees.

Step:3 Drive through your hips, extending them forcefully to swing the kettlebell forward and up to shoulder height. Allow the momentum to carry the kettlebell upwards, keeping your arms straight but not locked.
Step:4 As the kettlebell begins to descend, hinge at your hips again to let it swing back between your legs, preparing for the next repetition. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell thruster
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder level, palms facing inward. Keep your elbows close to your.
Step:2 Lower into a squat by bending your hips and knees until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up while simultaneously pressing the kettlebells overhead. Fully extend your arms at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder level as you prepare for the next repetition. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebells sumo deadlift with high pull
instructions: Step:1 Place two kettlebells on the floor between your feet. Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your toes pointed slightly outward.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and bend your knees to lower your body, reaching down to grasp the kettlebell handles, one in each hand, keeping your back straight and chest up.

Step:3 Push through your heels to lift the kettlebells off the floor, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. As you reach the standing position, pull the kettlebells upward towards your chin by bending your elbows and keeping them pointed outward.
Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Knee to chest stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards your chest, wrapping your hands around your knee to gently pull your knee closer to your chest.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch. Keep your left leg straight and maintain your balance.
Step:4 Release your right knee and lower your leg back to the starting position. Repeat the stretch with your left knee. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling hip flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a kneeling position with your right knee on the floor and your left foot in front of you, forming a 90-degree angle with your left knee.
Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or on your left thigh for support. Engage your core and keep your back straight.
Step:3 Gently push your hips forward, feeling the stretch in your right hip flexor. Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and switch legs, performing the stretch with your left knee on the floor and your right foot in front. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling lat floor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a tabletop position on the floor with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Extend your right arm forward on the floor, palm facing up, while keeping your left hand in place.
Step:3 Bend your left elbow to lower your chest towards the floor, feeling the stretch in your lat muscles and upper back. Keep your head relaxed and look down at the floor.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Slowly return to the starting position and repeat on the other side by extending your left arm forward and bending your right elbow.

name: Kneeling leg curl machine
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the leg curl machine with one leg bent on the knee rest behind you and the other leg extended and secured under the pad.
Step:2 Hold onto the handles for stability and keep your back straight.
Step:3 Curl the extended leg by bending your knee and pulling your heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return your leg to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Kneeling squat jumps bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a kneeling position on the floor with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing behind you. Sit back on your heels with your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes, then swing your arms forward and upward to generate momentum.
Step:3 Explosively jump up from your knees, bringing your feet forward to land in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees bent.
Step:4 Stand up from the squat position and then return to the starting kneeling position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling wrist flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a tabletop position on the floor with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
Step:2 Rotate your hands so that your fingers are pointing towards your knees, palms flat on the floor.
Step:3 Slowly shift your weight back towards your heels to increase the stretch in your wrists and forearms, keeping your palms flat on the floor.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily. Release the stretch by shifting your weight forward and gently lifting your hands off the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press
Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press_Female
Landmine chest press
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the end of a barbell with the right hand at chest level. The other end of the barbell should be anchored securely in a landmine attachment or corner.
Step:2 Press the barbell forward and slightly upward until your arm is fully extended.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position at chest level. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Landmine Half Kneeling Single Arm Overhead Press
Landmine Half Kneeling Single Arm Overhead Press_Female
Landmine row
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. Position yourself so that the end of a barbell, anchored in a landmine attachment or a secure corner, is between your feet.
Step:2 Bend at the hips and knees to lean forward and grab the barbell with both hands using a v handle.
Step:3 Pull the barbell towards your chest by squeezing your shoulder blades together and bending your elbows.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lat pull down close grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar with both hands just closer than shoulder-width apart, and your arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lat pull down normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar with both hands, just wider than shoulder-width apart, and your arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lat pull down wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit at the lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar with both hands, wider than shoulder-width apart, and your arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lateral raise bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent and your palms facing down.
Step:3 Hold the position for a second, then slowly lower your arms back to your sides with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a steady and controlled pace.

name: Lateral raise to shoulder press Resistance band cable
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the resistance band under both feet. Hold the handles of the resistance band with your palms facing inward and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Perform a lateral raise by lifting the handles out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Once your arms are parallel to the floor, rotate your wrists so your palms face forward, bend your arms at 90 degrees up and press the handles overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Lower the handles back to shoulder height, rotate your wrists back to the starting position, and then lower your arms back to your sides. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lateral raises dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides with your palms facing your body.
Step:2 Raise both arms out to the sides until they reach shoulder height, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: lateral raises dumbbell seated with swing
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms hanging by your sides and palms facing your body. Keep your torso leaning towards the floor.
Step:2 Begin raising your torso while swinging both arms out to the sides until they reach shoulder height, using a controlled momentum and bending your elbows at 90 degrees as you raise up.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, ensuring your arms are parallel and your torso vertical to the floor.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lateral raises on cable machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your right side facing the cable machine, feet shoulder-width apart. Attach a handle to the low pulley and grasp the handle with your left hand, palm facing inward.
Step:2 Raise the handle out to your side until your left arm is parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handle back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to work the opposite arm.

name: Leaning Dumbbell Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand next to a lifting cage, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Grasp the lifting cage bar for support with your left hand and lean your body to the opposite side by extending your arm.
Step:2 With your right arm hanging down, raise the dumbbell out to your side until your arm is parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbow and your palm facing down.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Complete the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg extended stretch on bench
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on the edge of a bench with both legs bent and your feet flat on the floor. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Extend your right leg forward until it is parallel to the floor, keeping your leg straight.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your hamstring and lower back.

Step:4 Slowly bring your right leg back to the starting position with both feet flat on the floor. Repeat the stretch with your left leg extended. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg lift circles
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms at your sides, palms facing down.
Step:2 Lift both legs off the floor, about a foot above the floor, keeping your legs straight and your core engaged.
Step:3 Begin to draw small circles in the air with both legs moving together in a controlled and steady motion. Perform the circles in one direction for a set number of repetitions.
Step:4 Switch directions and draw circles with both legs in the opposite direction for the same number of repetitions. Lower your legs back to the starting position.

name: Leg press machine close stance
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet close together in the center of the foot platform, keeping your feet flat and parallel. Adjust the seat so that your knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Hold the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. Keep your back pressed against the backrest and your core engaged.
Step:3 Press through your heels to extend your legs, pushing the platform away from you until your legs are fully extended but not locked at the knees.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg press machine normal stance
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet at shoulder-width, in the center of the foot platform, keeping your feet flat and parallel. Adjust the seat so that your knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Hold the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. Keep your back pressed against the backrest and your core engaged.
Step:3 Press through your heels to extend your legs, pushing the platform away from you until your legs are fully extended but not locked at the knees.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg press machine normal stance_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet at shoulder-width, in the center of the foot platform, keeping your feet flat and parallel. Adjust the seat so that your knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Hold the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. Keep your back pressed against the backrest and your core engaged.
Step:3 Press through your heels to extend your legs, pushing the platform away from you until your legs are fully extended but not locked at the knees.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg press wide high stance
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet just wider than shoulder-width, high in the center of the foot platform, keeping your feet flat and parallel. Adjust the seat so that your knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Hold the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. Keep your back pressed against the backrest and your core engaged.
Step:3 Press through your heels to extend your legs, pushing the platform away from you until your legs are fully extended but not locked at the knees.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg press wide high stance behind view
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg press machine and position your feet just wider than shoulder-width, high in the center of the foot platform, keeping your feet flat and parallel. Adjust the seat so that your knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Hold the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. Keep your back pressed against the backrest and your core engaged.
Step:3 Press through your heels to extend your legs, pushing the platform away from you until your legs are fully extended but not locked at the knees.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg raises (straight legs)
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on a captain's chair, supporting your body weight with your forearms on the arm pads and your back against the backrest. Let your legs hang straight down.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your legs straight. Lift both legs together while keeping them straight.
Step:3 Raise your legs until they are parallel to the floor or as high as you can comfortably go, maintaining control throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position without swinging. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Legs hand reach spine stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by sitting on the floor with your legs extended straight together in front of you. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Slowly bend forward at the hips, reaching your hands towards your feet. Keep your legs straight and your toes pointing up.
Step:3 Continue to reach forward, aiming to touch your toes or go as far as your flexibility allows. Allow your head and neck to relax as you stretch.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily.

name: Lever Leg Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the lever leg extension machine. Position your feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your legs by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knees, then slowly lower the weight back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Leg Extension_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the lever leg extension machine. Position your feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your legs by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knees, then slowly lower the weight back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Long arm crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Extend your arms straight in line with your head, keeping them close to your ears, and hands crossed over each other.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the floor, with your arms following your torso line, until it forms a 45-degree angle with the floor.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, squeezing your abdominal muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Low Cable Overhead Flyes
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable machine with the pulleys set at the lowest position. Grasp the handles with each hand, palms facing up, and take a step forward to create tension in the cables.
Step:2 Lean lightly forward and position your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your back straight and your arms extended slightly behind you.
Step:3 Raise the handles up and together in a wide arc, bringing them to meet above your head, while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Low Resistance band lying bicep curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach the middle of the resistance band to a low anchor point in front of you. Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms extended straight by your sides.
Step:2 Curl the handles towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Low Resistance band lying bicep curl half repetition
instructions: Step:1 Attach the middle of the resistance band to a low anchor point in front of you. Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a handle in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms extended straight by your sides.
Step:2 Curl the handles halfway towards your shoulders by bending your elbows until your forearms are parallel to the floor, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge front kick
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Lift your right leg to perform a front kick, extending your leg straight out in front of you.
Step:3 As you bring your right leg back down, step it behind you into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to stand back up, returning to the starting position. Repeat the movement on the same side or alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge pulses bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart. Step your right foot forward into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:2 From the lunge position, perform small pulses by slightly raising and lowering your hips in a controlled manner.
Step:3 Continue pulsing for the desired number of repetitions or duration, keeping your core engaged and maintaining balance.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by pushing through your right heel and repeat the exercise on the opposite leg.

name: Lunge reverse with Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the middle of the resistance band under your left foot. Hold the handles of the resistance band at shoulder height with your elbows bent and facing the floor.
Step:2 Step your right leg back into a reverse lunge, bending both knees to lower your right knee towards the floor while keeping your left knee aligned with your ankle.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, bringing your right leg forward.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to work the other leg.

name: Lunge rotation left and right bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms bent at your sides, hands close to your torso.
