Step:2 Step your right foot forward into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, bringing your arms to the right side, then rotate your torso to the left, bringing your arms to the left side.

Step:4 Return your torso to the center and push through your right heel to return to the starting position. Repeat the movement on the opposite leg. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge to knee drive left bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Step your left foot back into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to stand back up, simultaneously driving your left knee up towards your chest.
Step:4 Return your left leg to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Switch sides and repeat the movement with your right leg stepping back.

name: Lunge to knee drive right bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Step your right foot back into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee nearly touches the floor.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to stand back up, simultaneously driving your right knee up towards your chest.
Step:4 Return your right leg to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Switch sides and repeat the movement with your left leg stepping back.

name: lunges alternate leg with pause bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.

Step:2 Step your right foot forward into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor. Pause for a moment in this position.

Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, then step your left foot forward into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee nearly touches the floor. Pause for a moment in this position.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunges same leg side view bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.

Step:2 Step your right foot forward into a lunge position, lowering your hips until your right thigh is parallel to the floor and your left knee nearly touches the floor. Pause for a moment in this position.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the lunge with your right leg for the desired number of repetitions before switching to your left leg.

name: Lunging straight leg calf stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Step your right foot back into a lunge position, keeping your right leg straight and your heel on the floor. Bend your left knee slightly, keeping your left foot flat on the floor.
Step:3 Lean forward slightly, pressing your hips downward and feeling the stretch in your right calf. Hold this position for 15-30 seconds.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and switch legs, stepping your left foot back and repeating the stretch.

name: lying (prone) abdominal stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor with your legs extended straight behind you and your hands placed under your shoulders, palms flat on the floor.
Step:2 Slowly press your hands into the floor to lift your chest upward, extending your spine. Keep your hips and legs relaxed on the floor.
Step:3 Continue to lift your chest until you feel a comfortable stretch in your abdomen and lower back. Hold this position for 15-30 seconds, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:4 Slowly lower your chest back down to the floor and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying abs Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Attach the resistance band to a low anchor point behind your head and hold the handles with both hands, keeping your arms bent and handles close to your head.
Step:2 Curl your upper body, bringing your elbows towards your knees while lifting your back off the floor.
Step:3 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying back extension
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor with your legs extended straight behind you and your hands placed behind your head, elbows out to the sides.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes, then lift your upper torso off the floor, keeping your neck in a neutral position and your lower body relaxed on the floor.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, squeezing your lower back muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper torso back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying bench external shoulder rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a bench with your arms extended out to the sides, your elbows bent at 90 degrees, and your forearms hanging off the sides of the bench, perpendicular to the floor in line with your head.
Step:2 Rotate your shoulders to lift your forearms upward until they are vertical to the floor, maintaining the 90-degree angle at your elbows throughout the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower your forearms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying bench internal rotation stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back on a bench with your arms extended out to the sides, your elbows bent at 90 degrees, and your forearms hanging off the sides of the bench, perpendicular to the floor in line with your torso.
Step:2 Rotate your shoulders to lift your forearms upward until they are vertical to the floor, maintaining the 90-degree angle at your elbows throughout the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower your forearms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying crossover stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight and your arms out to the sides to form a T shape.
Step:2 Bend and lift your right leg and cross it over your body, aiming to touch the floor on the left side, and extend your left arm to hold your right knee down.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your lower back and hips.

Step:4 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position. Repeat the stretch with your left leg, crossing it over your body to the right side. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying glute stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Step:2 Cross your right ankle over your left knee, forming a figure-four position.
Step:3 Grasp the back of your left thigh with both hands and gently pull your left leg towards your chest. Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your right glute and hip.
Step:4 Slowly release your left leg and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch with your left ankle crossed over your right knee. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying hip flexor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight on the floor.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards your chest, holding it with both hands to keep it close while extending your left leg straight off floor, keeping it in line with your right foot.

Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release your right knee and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch with your left knee lifted towards your chest and your right leg extended. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying lateral raises bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your legs extended straight and your arms extended out to your sides, palms facing down.
Step:2 Lift both arms straight upwards, keeping them in line with your shoulders. Maintain a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a second, feeling the contraction in your shoulder and upper back muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying leg curl machine
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the lying leg curl machine, positioning your legs under the padded lever, just above your ankles. Adjust the machine so that your knees are just off the edge of the bench.
Step:2 Grasp the handles on the sides of the machine for stability and keep your back flat against the bench.
Step:3 Curl your legs up towards your glutes by bending your knees, squeezing your hamstrings at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the padded lever back to the starting position with control, fully extending your legs. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying leg raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms at your sides, palms facing down firm on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles and press your lower back into the floor.
Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, lift them up towards the ceiling until they are perpendicular to the floor.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position with control, stopping just before they touch the floor. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying On Side Arm Circle Warm Up
Lying On Side Arm Circle Warm Up_Female
Lying pull over with Resistance band cable
instructions: Step:1 Attach the middle of the resistance band to a low anchor point behind you. Lie on your back on the floor, knees bent and feet flat on the floor, holding a handle in each hand with your arms extended straight above your head, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Keeping your arms straight, pull the handles over your head and towards the floor until your arms are in line with your body.
Step:3 Slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, keeping your arms straight.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying quadriceps stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your legs extended straight and your arms resting by your sides.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and reach back with your right hand to grasp your right ankle or foot.
Step:3 Gently pull your right foot towards your glutes, feeling the stretch in your right quadriceps. Keep your hips pressed into the floor.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release your right foot and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch on your left leg. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying side quadriceps stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended straight and your head resting on your lower hand. Extend your top arm and reach back to grasp your top ankle or foot.
Step:2 Bend your top knee and gently pull your foot towards your glutes with your hand, feeling the stretch in your quadriceps. Keep your hips stacked and your body in a straight line.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, breathing deeply and steadily.
Step:4 Slowly release your foot and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch on the other side. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Single Leg Extended On Wall Hamstrings Stretch
Lying Single Leg Extended On Wall Hamstrings Stretch_Female
Machine chest press decline
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the decline chest press machine with your feet flat on the floor. Grasp the handles with both hands at chest level, palms facing down.
Step:2 Press the handles forward by extending your arms, keeping your elbows slightly bent at the end of the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the bottom of the movement and slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, bringing them back to chest level.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine chest press incline
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the incline chest press machine with your feet flat on the floor. Grasp the handles with both hands, elbows facing the floor, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the handles upward by extending your arms, keeping your elbows slightly bent at the end of the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement and slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, bringing them back to chest level.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine fly
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the chest fly machine with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the backrest. Grasp the handles, arms parallel to the floor, with both hands at chest level and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and your arms extended out to your sides.
Step:3 Bring the handles together in front of your chest by squeezing your chest muscles, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:4 Slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, bringing them back to your sides. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine lateral raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the lateral raise machine with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the backrest. Adjust the seat height so that the pads rest against the outside of your upper arms.
Step:2 Grasp the handles with both hands, keeping your elbows bent.
Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor and slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: MAJOR GROUPS Muscle body male
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your back straight, arms by your side, and feet shoulder-width apart.

name: Middle back rotation stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands placed on your hips.
Step:2 Slowly rotate your torso to the right, keeping your hips facing forward. Twist as far as is comfortable, feeling the stretch in your middle back.
Step:3 Return to the center and repeat the rotation to the right once more.
Step:4 Rotate your torso to the left side twice in the same manner, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Middle crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended straight on the floor and your arms straight by your sides, palms facing the floor.
Step:2 Curl your abdomen, raising your upper back off the floor, while simultaneously lifting your legs straight up towards the ceiling and raise your arms towards your feet.
Step:3 Just before your hands and feet touch, lower your upper back, legs and arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Military press bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms bent at the elbows, hands positioned at shoulder height with palms facing forward.
Step:2 Engage your shoulders and press your hands upward until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, feeling the contraction in your shoulder muscles.
Step:4 Slowly lower your hands back to shoulder height with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Modified hindu push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight.
Step:3 Push through your hands to raise your hips up and back into a downward-facing dog position, forming an inverted V-shape with your body.
Step:4 Lower your hips and return to the plank position by moving your body forward. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Mountain climbers
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position on your toes and hands, with your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your right elbow and stop when your knee is close to the elbow.
Step:3 Return to the starting plank position, then repeat the movement on the opposite side.
Step:4 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: MTS ISO-LATERAL KNEELING LEG CURL
equipments: MTS Iso-Lateral Kneeling Leg Curl Machine
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the MTS Iso-Lateral Kneeling Leg Curl machine to fit your height. Kneel on the machine with your left knee on the knee pad and the right leg extended, securing your ankle under the padded lever. Rest your chest against the chest pad.
Step:2 Hold onto the handles for stability and keep your back straight.
Step:3 Curl your leg by bending your knee and pulling your heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your leg back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: MTS ISO-LATERAL KNEELING LEG CURL_Female
equipments: MTS Iso-Lateral Kneeling Leg Curl Machine
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the MTS Iso-Lateral Kneeling Leg Curl machine to fit your height. Kneel on the machine with your left knee on the knee pad and the right leg extended, securing your ankle under the padded lever. Rest your chest against the chest pad.
Step:2 Hold onto the handles for stability and keep your back straight.
Step:3 Curl your leg by bending your knee and pulling your heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your leg back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Multi Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the multi-hip machine and position the padded lever against the outside of your thigh. Grip the handles firmly and maintain an upright posture with a slight bend in your standing leg.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and push the working leg laterally against the resistance, lifting it to the side as far as possible.
Step:3 Slowly return your leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Multi Hip Abduction_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the multi-hip machine and position the padded lever against the outside of your thigh. Grip the handles firmly and maintain an upright posture with a slight bend in your standing leg.
Step:2 Engage your glutes and push the working leg laterally against the resistance, lifting it to the side as far as possible.
Step:3 Slowly return your leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Multi Hip Glute Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the multi-hip machine, turn to one side, and position the padded lever behind your thigh. Hold the handles firmly in front of you and lean slightly forward at the hips while keeping your spine straight.
Step:2 Extend your leg backward in a controlled motion until your leg is in line with your torso.
Step:3 Slowly return your leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Multi Hip Glute Extension_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the platform of the multi-hip machine, turn to one side, and position the padded lever behind your thigh. Hold the handles firmly in front of you and lean slightly forward at the hips while keeping your spine straight.
Step:2 Extend your leg backward in a controlled motion until your leg is in line with your torso.
Step:3 Slowly return your leg to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, switch legs, and repeat.

name: Normal Push-up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Engage your chest and lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Lower your chest until it is just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Oblique crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your hands behind your head, keeping your elbows wide.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles and lift your upper back off the floor, rotating your abdomen to raise your right elbow towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Squeeze your obliques at the top of the movement and slowly lower your upper back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides to work the opposite oblique.

name: One arm reverse dumbbell fly
instructions: Step:1 Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip. Bend at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight and almost parallel to the floor, and extend your free hand to hold on a bench.
Step:2 Allow the dumbbell to hang straight down from your shoulder, with your arm fully extended towards the floor.
Step:3 Raise the dumbbell out to the side until your arm is parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: over head weight sit up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying flat on your back with your legs slightly bent and your feet together. Hold a weight plate with both hands, extending your arms straight above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles and lift your upper body off the floor into a sitting position while keeping the weight extended straight up.
Step:3 As you sit up, ensure your back remains straight and your chest is lifted, bringing your torso to an upright position.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Over head weight sit up
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your knees bent and your feet on the floor. Hold a weight plate with both hands, extending your arms straight above your chest.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles and sit up by lifting your upper body towards your knees, keeping the weight extended upwards and your arms straight.
Step:3 Continue to sit up until your torso is upright, maintaining the weight above your head throughout the movement.
Step:4 Lower to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Over weight ab crunch
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on your back with your legs straight on the floor close together. Hold a dumbbell with both hands, keeping your arms bent and behind your head, close to the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core muscles and lift your torso off the floor while bending your knees and raising them to your chest, and bringing the dumbbell close to your knees.
Step:3 Lower your body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Overhand clap
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended down to your sides, palms facing your torso.
Step:2 Lift your arms overhead, bringing your palms together in a clapping motion.
Step:3 Lower your arms back to the starting position with control, keeping them straight and at shoulder height.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a smooth and controlled motion.

name: Overhand tricep stretching single arm
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Raise your right arm overhead and bend your elbow, reaching your right hand down towards your upper back.
Step:3 Bring your left arm overhead and hold your right elbow with your left hand, gently pulling your right elbow to the left side to deepen the stretch. Hold this position for 15-30 seconds.

Step:4 Release the stretch and return to the starting position. Repeat on the left side by raising your left arm overhead and bending your elbow, using your right hand to assist with the stretch. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Overhead extension Resistance band both arms
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing the middle of the resistance band under both feet. Hold the handles of the resistance band with both hands and extend your arms overhead, keeping your elbows close to your ears and your palms facing each other.
Step:2 Lower the handles behind your head by bending your elbows until your forearms are about parallel to the floor, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Extend your arms back to the starting position by straightening your elbows.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Overhead triceps stretch side angle
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Raise your right arm overhead and bend your elbow, reaching your right hand down towards your upper back.
Step:3 Bring your left arm overhead and hold your right elbow with your left hand, gently pulling your right elbow to the left side to deepen the stretch. Hold this position for 15-30 seconds.

Step:4 Release the stretch and return to the starting position. Repeat on the left side by raising your left arm overhead and bending your elbow, using your right hand to assist with the stretch. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Palm up palm down rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight at your sides at shoulder height.
Step:2 Slowly rotate your forearms in the opposite direction so that your palms face up while slightly lowering your arms.
Step:3 Slowly raise your arms back to the starting position while rotating your forearms so that both palms face down.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Pec deck fly machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the Pec Deck machine with your feet flat on the floor and your back pressed firmly against the backrest. Bend your arms at 90 degrees and rest your elbows on the elbow pads and grasp the handles, upper arms parallel to the floor and palms facing forward.
Step:2 Squeeze your chest muscles to bring the handles together in front of your chest.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, bringing your elbows back to your sides.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pike push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Walk your feet towards your hands, lifting your hips up towards the ceiling to form an inverted V-shape. Keep your arms and legs straight, and your head between your arms.
Step:3 Lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them pointed outwards.
Step:4 Push through your hands to return to the starting inverted V position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plank cross knee drive
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core.
Step:2 Lift your right knee and drive it towards your left elbow and straighten your leg, twisting your torso slightly to the left as you do so.
Step:3 Return your right leg to the starting plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left knee, driving it towards your right elbow. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plank jack
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core.
Step:2 Jump your feet out to the sides, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, while keeping your upper body stable.
Step:3 Quickly jump your feet back together to return to the starting plank position.
Step:4 Continue jumping your feet in and out for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Plank Knee Tucks
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Quickly jump both knees towards your chest, landing with both feet flat on the floor beneath you.
Step:3 Immediately jump your feet back to the starting plank position.
Step:4 Continue jumping your feet in and out for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plank lunges
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Bring your right knee forward and place your right foot outside your right hand, keeping your left leg extended straight back.
Step:3 Return your right foot to the plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left knee, bringing your left foot forward to place it outside your left hand. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plank on elbows
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying face down on the floor. Place your elbows directly under your shoulders and your forearms flat on the floor, parallel to each other.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your body off the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your heels. Your elbows and toes should support your body weight.
Step:3 Hold this position, keeping your core tight and your body straight. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise too high.
Step:4 Maintain the plank position for the desired amount of time, focusing on your form and breathing steadily.

name: Plank reach through
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a side plank position on your right side with your right elbow supporting your body, your left arm raised vertically towards the ceiling, and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your left arm, reaching it under and across your torso while slightly lowering your hips.
Step:3 Return your left arm to the starting position, lifting your hips back to the straight line.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left side and repeat the movement with your right arm.

name: Plank reverse fly with bottle
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands placed directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Hold a water bottle in your right hand, and keep your feet slightly wider than hip-width apart for stability.
Step:2 Lift the water bottle out to the side while keeping your arm straight, raising it until it is parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly lower the bottle back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plank shoulder taps
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lift your right hand off the floor and tap your left shoulder, keeping your hips stable and minimizing rotation.
Step:3 Return your right hand to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left hand, lifting it off the floor and tapping your right shoulder. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plate front raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight plate with both hands. Keep your arms extended straight down in front of your hips.
Step:2 Raise the plate in front of you with straight arms until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the plate back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining good form throughout.

name: Plate loaded chest press incline
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the plate-loaded incline chest press machine with your feet flat on the floor. Grasp the handles with both hands, elbows facing the floor, palms facing forward.
Step:2 Press the handles upward by extending your arms, keeping your elbows slightly bent at the end of the movement.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement and slowly return the handles to the starting position with control, bringing them back to chest level.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plyo side lunge stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and both arms extended straight out to your sides.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and lower into a side lunge while simultaneously rotating your torso to the right and bringing your left hand to touch your right leg. Keeping your left leg straight.
Step:3 Push off your right foot to return to the starting wide stance position, straightening your right leg and rotating your torso back to the center.

Step:4 Repeat the movement on the left side, bending your left knee into a side lunge and rotating your torso to bring your right hand to touch your left leg. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher curl barbell
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), shoulder-width wide, and your arms resting on the preacher pad.
Step:2 Curl the barbell towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms pressed against the pad.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher curl dumbbells simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up), and your arms extended over the preacher bench pad.
Step:2 Engage your core and curl both dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms pressed against the pad.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher curl ez bar
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding an EZ bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), shoulder-width wide, and your arms resting on the preacher pad.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms pressed against the pad.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher curl ez bar close grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding an EZ bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), just closer than shoulder-width wide, and your arms resting on the preacher pad.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms pressed against the pad.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher curl ez bar wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your feet flat on the floor, holding an EZ bar with an underhand grip (palms facing up), just wider than shoulder-width wide, and your arms resting on the preacher pad.
Step:2 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms pressed against the pad.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the bar reaches shoulder height.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pretzel stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you.
Step:2 Bend your right knee, placing your right foot flat on the floor inside your left thigh.
Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right and place your left elbow on the outside of your right knee, using your right hand on the floor behind you for support.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release and return to the starting position. Repeat on the other side by switching the positions of your legs and rotating your torso to the left.

name: Prone bench row barbell pronate grip
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a barbell with a pronate grip (palms facing down) and your hands placed shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the barbell towards your upper abdomen by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches reaches close to the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone bench row barbell reverse grip
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing up) and your hands placed shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the barbell towards your abdomen by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell reaches close to the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone bench row dumbbells
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other), and your arms extended straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your abdomen by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach the sides of your torso.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone bench row dumbbells pronated grip
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a reverse grip (palms facing down), and your arms extended straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your abdomen by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach the sides of your torso.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone bench row dumbbells supinated grip
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a supinate grip (palms facing up), and your arms extended straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Pull the dumbbells towards your abdomen by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement, ensuring the dumbbells reach the sides of your torso.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone front raises barbell on bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incline bench, holding a barbell with both hands using a pronated grip (palms facing down) and a shoulder-width hand placement. Your arms should be extended straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Lift the barbell straight up in front of you until your arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone front raises dumbbell on bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie chest-first on an incine bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down). Your arms should be extended straight down towards the floor.
Step:2 Raise the dumbbells straight up in front of you until your arms are in line with your torso.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Pull apart cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a resistance band with both hands, arms extended straight in front of you at shoulder height. Your palms should be facing the floor.
Step:2 Pull the resistance band apart by moving your arms out to your sides.
Step:3 Slowly return your arms to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull up normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand beneath a pull-up bar and grasp it with an overhand grip (palms facing away from you), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your back muscles and pull yourself up towards the bar by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, focusing on contracting your back muscles.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position in a controlled manner, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull up wide grip
instructions: Step:1 Stand beneath a pull-up bar and grasp it with an overhand grip (palms facing away from you), hands wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your back muscles to pull yourself up towards the bar by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, focusing on contracting your back muscles.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position in a controlled manner, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull up wide grip front view
instructions: Step:1 Stand beneath a pull-up bar and grasp it with an overhand grip (palms facing away from you), hands wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your back muscles to pull yourself up towards the bar by bending your elbows.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, focusing on contracting your back muscles.
Step:4 Lower yourself back to the starting position in a controlled manner, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push Pull Chair Over Head Pull
Push Pull Chair Over Head Pull_Female
Push up and rotation
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed shoulder-width apart and your feet together. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Perform a push-up.
Step:3 As you push back up, shift your weight onto your left hand and rotate your torso to the right, raising your right arm towards the ceiling. Your body should form a T-shape.

Step:4 Return your right hand to the floor and lower your body into another push-up. Repeat the movement, this time rotating to the left and raising your left arm towards the ceiling. Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push up plus
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Push through your hands to protract your shoulder blades, rounding your upper back slightly.
Step:3 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body to perform a push-up.
Step:4 Return to the plank position. Repeat the sequence for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push ups bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Lower your chest until it is just above the floor, maintaining a straight body line and keeping your neck neutral.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Raised leg crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight, vertical to the floor. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your shoulders off the floor, bringing your chest towards your knees.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, squeezing your abdominal muscles.
Step:4 Lower your shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reaching up shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Bend your right elbow and bring your right arm behind your back, raising your hand upward with your palm facing out.

Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release and return to the starting position. Repeat on the other side by bending your left elbow and using your right hand to assist with the stretch.

name: Rear deltoid fly cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a shoulder height anchor point in front of you. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the handles with both hands, arms extended straight in front of you at shoulder height, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Pull the handles out to your sides by extending your arms and squeezing your shoulder blades together, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Slowly return your arms to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rear deltoid stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your right arm, slightly bent, across your body at shoulder height.
Step:3 Use your left hand to gently pull your right arm towards your chest, feeling the stretch in the rear deltoid.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release and return to the starting position. Repeat on the other side by extending your left arm and using your right hand to assist with the stretch.

name: Resistance band - cable row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. Kneel on one knee with the opposite leg forward, foot flat on the ground.
Step:2 Hold the band handles with both hands, arms extended forward, and palms facing down.
Step:3 Pull the band handles towards your chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement.
Step:4 Return to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Assisted Front Rack Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a weight cage with a horizontal bar at chest level. Place the resistance band under your left foot and hold the other end of the band with your left hand.
Step:2 Bring your left elbow up and rest it on the horizontal bar, allowing your forearm to lean backward. The band should extend down by your shoulder, creating tension.
Step:3 Slowly allow your forearm to lean back to increase the stretch in your shoulder, keeping your hand close to your shoulder.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then slowly release the tension and switch to the other arm.

name: Resistance Band Assisted Front Rack Stretch_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a weight cage with a horizontal bar at chest level. Place the resistance band under your left foot and hold the other end of the band with your left hand.
Step:2 Bring your left elbow up and rest it on the horizontal bar, allowing your forearm to lean backward. The band should extend down by your shoulder, creating tension.
Step:3 Slowly allow your forearm to lean back to increase the stretch in your shoulder, keeping your hand close to your shoulder.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then slowly release the tension and switch to the other arm.

name: Resistance Band Assisted Push-up
instructions: Step:1 Secure two loop elastic bands on a straight bar, ensuring they are securely anchored. Position each band over your shoulders.

Step:2 Set yourself in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. The resistance bands should provide support as you perform the push-ups.
Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body. Allow the resistance bands to assist you as you descend.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Step:2 Set yourself in a plank position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. The resistance bands should provide support as you perform the push-ups.
Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 45-degree angle to your body. Allow the resistance bands to assist you as you descend.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Bent Leg Kickback (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Place a loop resistance band around both thighs, just above your knees. Start in a kneeling position on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and knees under your hips.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back flat. Begin with your left knee bent at a 90-degree angle and your foot flexed.
Step:3 Push your left foot upward towards the ceiling while keeping your knee bent, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return your leg to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Resistance Band Calf Press Sitting on Chair
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair with your back straight, knees bent at 90 degrees and feet flat hovering just above the floor. Loop a resistance band around your forefeet, holding the ends of the band with your hands.
Step:2 Extend your forefeet downward to point your toes to the floor, pressing against the resistance of the band to engage your calf muscles.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, flexing your forefeet back towards you.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Calf Press Sitting on Chair_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair with your back straight, knees bent at 90 degrees and feet flat hovering just above the floor. Loop a resistance band around your forefeet, holding the ends of the band with your hands.
Step:2 Extend your forefeet downward to point your toes to the floor, pressing against the resistance of the band to engage your calf muscles.
Step:3 Slowly return to the starting position with control, flexing your forefeet back towards you.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Clam
instructions: Step:1 Place a loop resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. Lie on your side with your legs bent at a 90-degree angle and your feet stacked together.
Step:2 Rest your head on your bottom arm and place your top hand on the floor for stability.
Step:3 Keeping your feet together, lift your top knee as high as you can without moving your pelvis or back, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return your knee to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side.

name: Resistance Band Cross Body Single Straight Arm Supinated Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the resistance band to a high anchor point in front of you, on your left side. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handle with your right hand, palm facing up.
Step:2 Extend your right arm straight opposite the left side of your head, keeping your arm straight.
Step:3 Pull the handle down across your body towards your right hip until fully extended by your side and slowly return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side.

name: Resistance Band Cross Body Single Straight Arm Supinated Pulldown_Female

name: Resistance band face pull
instructions: Step:1 Attach a resistance band to an anchor point at face height. Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands, palms facing down.
Step:2 Step back to create tension in the band and extend your arms straight in front of you at shoulder height.
Step:3 Pull the handles towards your face by bending your elbows and spreading them out to the sides, keeping your upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance band face pull
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at head height. Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended straight in front of you, palms facing down.
Step:2 Pull the handles towards your face, bending your elbows and flaring them out to the sides until your hands are at your face sides.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement, keeping your upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control, maintaining tension in the band. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Floor Hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with a loop resistance band over your ankles and another loop resistance band over your forearms. Extend your arms forward and keep your legs straight.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes, and lift your chest and legs off the floor simultaneously, spreading your legs apart against the resistance of the band.
Step:3 Squeeze your lower back muscles at the top of the movement, keeping your arms and legs straight.
Step:4 Slowly lower your chest and legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Glute Bridge Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place a loop resistance band just above your knees. Keep your hands extended by your sides with hands firm on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and glutes, and lift your hips towards the ceiling, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Step:3 While holding the bridge position, press your knees outward against the resistance band to stretch them as far as possible.
Step:4 Slowly bring your knees back together, then lower your hips back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Step:4 Slowly lower your hips back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Kneeling Leg Half Circle
instructions: Step:1 Start on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and knees under your hips. Attach a loop resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees.
Step:2 Lift your right leg a few inches off the floor and extend it straight back.
Step:3 Move your right leg in a half-circle motion inward over your left leg until it lightly touches the floor, keeping the resistance band taut.
Step:4 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Resistance Band Kneeling Leg Half Circle on bench
instructions: Step:1 Start in a tabletop position on a bench, with your hands holding the edges for support and your knees under your hips. Attach a loop resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees.
Step:2 Lift your right leg off the bench and extend it straight back, keeping it under bench level.
Step:3 Move your right leg in a half-circle motion inward over your left leg until it comes in level with the bench, keeping the resistance band taut.
Step:4 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

instructions: Step:1 Place a loop resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. Begin by lying on your left side with your legs bent at 90 degrees and stacked on top of each other.

Step:4 Slowly lower your leg and hips back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side.

name: Resistance Band Upper Body Dead Bug
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent at a 90-degree angle, knees right above your hips. Attach two loop resistance bands at a low point, extending behind you.
Step:2 Hold the end of each band in each hand, keeping your arms extended straight up towards the ceiling.
Step:3 Lower your right leg towards the floor while keeping your left leg and arms in the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent at a 90-degree angle, knees right above your hips. Attach two loop resistance bands at a low point, extending behind you.

name: Resistance bands facepull
instructions: Step:1 Secure the middle of the resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at head height. Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding one handle of the band in each hand with your arms extended straight in front of you, palms facing down.
Step:2 Pull the handles towards your face, bending your elbows and flaring them out to the sides until your hands are at your face sides.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement, keeping your upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control, maintaining tension in the band. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Ab Wheel Rollout
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands on the floor, arms straight, and the ab roller set under your feet. Your legs should be straight back, forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the ab roller towards your hands, keeping your legs straight. Continue rolling until your thighs are vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Hold the position briefly, ensuring your core is tight and your back is straight.
Step:4 Roll the ab roller back to the starting position with control, maintaining a straight line with your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Ab Wheel Rollout_Female
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands on the floor, arms straight, and the ab roller set under your feet. Your legs should be straight back, forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the ab roller towards your hands, keeping your legs straight. Continue rolling until your thighs are vertical to the floor.
Step:3 Hold the position briefly, ensuring your core is tight and your back is straight.
Step:4 Roll the ab roller back to the starting position with control, maintaining a straight line with your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse cable fly on crossover
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a cable crossover machine with the pulleys set at shoulder height. Grasp the left handle with your right hand and the right handle with your left hand, crossing the cables in front of you and palms facing the floor.
Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and keep your back straight. Extend your arms straight in front of you at chest height, palms facing down.
Step:3 Pull the handles outwards and backward in a reverse fly motion, keeping your arms straight, until both arms are fully extended to your sides.
Step:4 Slowly return your arms to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your arms by your sides with palms facing down for stability.
Step:2 Lift your legs off the floor, bending your knees at a 90-degree angle so that your thighs are perpendicular to the floor and your calves are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, curling your knees towards your chest. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to lift your hips.
Step:4 Slowly lower your hips back to the starting position, keeping your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse crunch with kick out
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your arms by your sides with palms facing down for stability.
Step:2 Lift your legs off the floor, bending your knees at a 90-degree angle so that your thighs are perpendicular to the floor and your calves are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Extend your legs straight out in front of you, keeping them off the floor to perform a kick-out.

Step:4 Bend your knees back to the starting position and engage your core to lift your hips off the floor, curling your knees towards your chest. Lower your hips back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse grip lat pull down
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the bar with an underhand grip (palms facing you) at shoulder-width apart, arms fully extended above you.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. Lean back slightly to create a natural arch in your lower back.
Step:3 Pull the bar towards your upper chest, bringing your elbows down to your sides while squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse grip Resistance band simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the middle of a resistance band under both feet. Hold one handle in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down), arms fully extended by your sides.
Step:2 Simultaneously curl both handles upward towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and squeezing your biceps at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse lunge left Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the middle of a resistance band under your right foot. Hold one handle in each hand with your arms bent and hands close to your face sides.
Step:2 Step your left foot back into a lunge position, lowering your left knee towards the floor while keeping your right knee over your ankle.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position, bringing your foot forward to stand up straight.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Reverse machine fly
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stool with your back straight, knees bent, and feet on the floor.
Step:2 Extend your arms forward and grab the handles of the machine with your palms facing down.
Step:3 Pull the handles by opening your arms wide to your sides.
Step:4 As your arms are aligned with the shoulders, return to the initial position and repeat.

name: Reverse shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing away from a hip-level box or surface.
Step:2 Place your hands on the box behind you with your arms straight, palms down.
Step:3 Slowly bend your knees to lower your body, keeping your arms straight and allowing your shoulders to stretch as you lower yourself.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your shoulders and chest. Slowly straighten your legs to return to the starting position.

name: Runner stretch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standing position with your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Step your right foot slightly forward, keeping it straight. Lightly bend your left knee.
Step:3 Lower your torso and arms towards your right foot, reaching down with your hands while keeping your back straight.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your right hamstring. Slowly return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

name: Running
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, your arms relaxed by your sides, and your core engaged. Maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Begin running by taking quick, powerful strides, lifting your knees higher than jogging.
Step:3 Swing your arms naturally with each step, keeping them bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:4 Maintain a steady, comfortable pace and continue running for the desired duration or distance.

name: Running_female
