name: Russian twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Lean back slightly so that your torso forms a V-shape with your thighs.
Step:2 Clasp your hands together in front of your chest.
Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, bringing your hands opposite your right hip.
Step:4 Rotate back through the center and to the left, bringing your hands opposite your left hip. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Russian twist weighted ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat. Hold a weighted ball with both hands, keeping it opposite to your chest with straight arms.
Step:2 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight.
Step:3 Rotate your torso to the right, bringing the weighted ball towards the floor beside your hip.
Step:4 Rotate your torso to the left, moving the weighted ball towards the floor beside your left hip. Repeat the twisting motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapula push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Keep your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Without bending your elbows, squeeze your shoulder blades together, allowing your chest to lower slightly towards the floor.
Step:3 Push your shoulder blades apart, rounding your upper back slightly and lifting your chest away from the floor.
Step:4 Continue to alternate between the retraction and protraction phases for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining a steady and controlled movement.

name: Scissors kick
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides, palms facing down.
Step:2 Lift both legs off the floor a few inches, keeping them straight.
Step:3 Alternately cross your legs over each other in a scissor-like motion. Move your right leg over your left leg and then switch, bringing your left leg over your right leg.
Step:4 Continue alternating legs in a controlled manner for the desired number of repetitions or duration.

name: Seated cable row V bar machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet secure on the foot platform. Grasp the V bar with both hands.
Step:2 Sit upright with your back straight, extending your arms fully in front of you.
Step:3 Pull the V bar towards your abdomen by bringing your elbows back and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Seated calf machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the calf raise machine with your forefeet positioned on the foot platform and your knees secured under the padded lever.
Step:2 Hold the handles with both hands and allow your heels to lower as far as possible, fully stretching your calves.
Step:3 Press through your forefeet to lift your heels as high as possible, then slowly lower your heels back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Seated calf raises dumbbell on knee
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your forefeet on the edge of a plate, close together, allowing your heels to hang off. Place a dumbbell on both knees, holding them securely with your hands.
Step:2 Raise your heels as high as possible, pushing through your forefeet and lifting the dumbbells.
Step:3 Lower your heels back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg and repeat.

name: Seated calf stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you. Keep your back straight and your core engaged.
Step:2 Extend your right foot while lightly bending the left knee, reaching forward to grasp your toes with both hands.
Step:3 Gently pull your toes towards you, feeling the stretch in your calf muscle.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release. Repeat on the left leg.

name: Seated cross leg glute stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and cross your right leg over your left thigh and lightly bend your left knee placing your left foot flat on the floor.
Step:3 Keeping your back straight, lower your chest towards your crossed leg, reaching your hands stright to the floor to deepen the stretch.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your right glute. Slowly release and return to the starting position. Repeat on the left side.

name: Seated dumbbell one arm shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in your right hand at shoulder height, palm facing forward. Keep your back straight and feet flat on the floor.
Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead, keeping your wrist straight.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left arm and repeat.

name: Seated dumbbell rear delt fly
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your feet flat on the floor and a dumbbell in each hand. Lean forward at your hips until your chest is close to your thighs, letting your arms hang down towards the floor with palms facing each other.
Step:2 With a slight bend in your elbows, raise the dumbbells out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: seated elbow in alternating dumbbell overhead pres
Seated Figure Four With Twist Glute Stretch
Seated Figure Four With Twist Glute Stretch_Female
Seated floor crunches
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight out in front of you, forming an L-shape with your torso.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head without pulling on your neck, elbows facing outwards.
Step:3 Engage your core and bend your torso towards your thighs, performing a crunch while keeping your legs straight.
Step:4 Bring your torso back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated flutter kicks
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. Lean back slightly, supporting yourself by gripping the sides of the bench.
Step:2 Lift both legs off the bench a few inches, keeping them straight.
Step:3 Begin the flutter kicks by alternately raising and lowering your legs in a scissor-like motion, moving your right leg up while your left leg moves down and vice versa.
Step:4 Continue the flutter kicks for the desired number of repetitions or duration, keeping your core engaged and your movements controlled.

name: Seated hip abductor machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the hip abduction machine and place your feet flat on the footrests while positioning your outer thighs against the padded levers.
Step:2 Grip the side handles to stabilize your upper body and press your legs outward against the resistance, pushing the pads apart in a controlled motion.
Step:3 Pause for a second at the peak of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Seated leg curl machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your legs fully extended. Adjust the backrest and leg pads so the pad rests just above your heels.
Step:2 Pull your heels down by bending your knees until the pad reaches down as far as possible.
Step:3 Pause for a second, then slowly return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension single leg
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position both feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your right leg by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knee, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension single leg_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position both feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your right leg by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knee, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension_alternate legs
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position both feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your right leg by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knee, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Immediately repeat the movement with your left leg. Alternate between right and left legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension_alternate legs_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position both feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your right leg by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knee, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Immediately repeat the movement with your left leg. Alternate between right and left legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension_both legs
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position your feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your legs by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knees, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated leg extension_both legs_Female
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leg extension machine. Position your feet under the padded lever, with the lever resting just above your ankles.
Step:2 Grip the handles on the sides of the machine for support. Engage your core and keep your back pressed firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Extend your legs by pushing the padded lever upward, straightening your knees, then slowly lower the lever to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated machine hip adductor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a hip abductor machine with your back straight, knees open wide and bent, and feet on the footrests.
Step:2 Set the padded bars against the inner sides of your knees.
Step:3 Close your knees to bring the bars together.
Step:4 As the bars come together, return to the initial position and repeat.

name: Seated normal grip row machiNe
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing a row machine with a straight back and your feet placed on the footrests.
Step:2 Hold the rod above your knees with an overhand grip of your hands while keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Pull the cable towards your chest by bending your arms and taking your elbows past your back.
Step:4 Return to the initial position and repeat.

name: Seated Resistance band - cable rows
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs fully extended and feet together, anchoring the resistance band around the soles of your feet. Hold the handles with both hands, arms extended forward, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Keep your back straight, chest up, and core engaged to stabilize your body.
Step:3 Pull the handles towards your torso by bending your elbows, keeping your arms close to your body. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together at the peak of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position, maintaining control over the resistance band. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated shoulder flexor depressor retractor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you and your back straight.
Step:2 Extend both arms down to your sides, then lean back slightly.
Step:3 Bring both arms about a foot behind you, keeping them straight, and place your hands on the floor with your fingers pointing forward.
Step:4 Hold this position for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your shoulders. Slowly return to the starting position.

name: Seated shoulder press barbell
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a backrest, feet flat on the floor. Hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing forward), hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Rest the barbell on your upper chest.
Step:2 Press the barbell overhead by extending your elbows, keeping your back firmly against the backrest.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms at the top of the movement, ensuring the barbell is directly above your head.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back down to your upper chest with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated side stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back straight.
Step:2 Extend your right arm overhead, keeping your left hand holding on the bench for support.
Step:3 Lean your torso to the left, reaching your right arm over your head and to the left side, feeling the stretch along the right side of your body.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. Repeat on the other side by extending your left arm overhead and leaning to the right.

name: Seated single leg hamstring stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you.
Step:2 Bend your left knee and place the sole of your left foot against your right inner thigh. Keep your right leg extended and straight.
Step:3 Reach forward with both hands towards your right foot, keeping your back straight. Aim to grasp your toes or reach as far as comfortable.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your right hamstring. Slowly release and return to the starting position. Repeat on the other side by extending your left leg and bending your right knee.

name: Seated Single Leg Toe Touch Hamstring Stretch
Seated Single Leg Toe Touch Hamstring Stretch_Female
Seated straight leg calf stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you.
Step:2 Lightly bend both knees and extend your right foot, reaching forward to grasp your toes with your right hand.
Step:3 Gently pull your toes towards you, feeling the stretch in your calf muscle.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release. Repeat on the left leg.

name: Seated v up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you and your arms placed on the floor slightly behind you for support.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your torso off the floor, bringing your knees towards your chest to form a V shape with your body.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, squeezing your abdominal muscles.
Step:4 Lower your legs and torso back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shadow boxing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, one foot slightly in front of the other, and your knees slightly bent. Position your hands in front of your face in a guard position, with your elbows close to your body.
Step:2 Begin throwing punches in the air, alternating between jabs, crosses, hooks, and uppercuts. Use a full range of motion and rotate your hips and shoulders to generate power.
Step:3 Move around as you throw your punches, incorporating footwork to simulate a real boxing match. Step forward, backward, and side to side, keeping light on your feet.
Step:4 Continue shadow boxing for the desired duration, maintaining a steady pace and controlled movements.

name: Shoulder abduction
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms at your sides.
Step:2 Slowly raise your arms out to the sides until they reach shoulder height, forming a T shape with your body. Keep your palms facing down and your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Hold the position for a moment, feeling the activation in your shoulders.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder circle
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms relaxed, hanging straight down by your sides.
Step:2 Begin by making small circular motions with your shoulders, moving them backward in a controlled manner.
Step:3 Gradually increase the size of the circles, maintaining a steady pace.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms straight by your sides.
Step:2 Slowly extend your arms straight forward, and up overhead, keeping them straight and parallel to each other .
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment. Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side lateral raise Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the middle of a resistance band under both feet. Hold one handle in each hand, arms down by your sides, and palms facing inward.
Step:2 Lift your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a "T" shape with your body. Focusing on lifting with your shoulders and keeping your palms facing down.
Step:3 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side lunges bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your hands clasped in front of you for balance.
Step:2 Take a big step to the right with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your right knee should be bent and your left leg should remain straight.
Step:3 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat on the other side by stepping out to the left with your left foot, lowering into a lunge, and then returning to the starting position.

name: Side lying floor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your left side with your legs stacked on top of each other and your body in a straight line. Rest your head on your left arm.
Step:2 Extend your right arm straight over your head.
Step:3 Slowly lower your right hand towards your left hand to stretch your back.

Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling the stretch in your back and shoulders. Slowly return to the starting position and repeat on the other side by lying on your right side and following the same steps.

name: Side lying leg lift left
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your right side with your legs extended straight and stacked on top of each other. Rest your head on your right arm and place your left hand on your hips.
Step:2 Slowly lift your left leg straight up towards the ceiling, keeping it straight and in line with your body.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, feeling the contraction in your outer thigh and hip.
Step:4 Slowly lower your leg back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left side and perform the exercise with your right leg.

name: side lying leg lift right
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your left side with your legs extended straight and stacked on top of each other. Rest your head on your left arm and place your right hand on your hips.
Step:2 Slowly lift your right leg straight up towards the ceiling, keeping it straight and in line with your body.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, feeling the contraction in your outer thigh and hip.
Step:4 Slowly lower your leg back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your right side and perform the exercise with your left leg.

name: Side plank
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your right side with your legs extended straight and stacked on top of each other. Prop yourself up on your right elbow, keeping your elbow directly under your shoulder.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your feet.
Step:3 Hold the position for the desired duration, keeping your body straight and your core tight.
Step:4 Slowly lower your hips back to the starting position with control. Repeat on the other side by lying on your left side and following the same steps.

name: side plank oblique crunch
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a side plank position on your right side, with your legs extended straight and stacked on top of each other. Prop yourself up on your right elbow, keeping your elbow directly under your shoulder. Place your left hand on your hip.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your feet.
Step:3 Lower your hips towards the floor without touching it, then raise them back up to the starting position, squeezing your obliques at the top.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side and perform the exercise on your left side.

name: Side Plank with hip lift
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a side plank position on your right side, with your legs extended straight and stacked on top of each other. Prop yourself up on your right elbow, keeping your elbow directly under your shoulder. Raise your left arm straight toward the ceiling.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your head to your feet.
Step:3 Once in the top position, perform two small controlled bounces with your hips, lifting them slightly higher each time.
Step:4 Lower your hips back to the floor without touching it and repeat the steps for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other side and perform the exercise on your left side.

name: Side push up
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your right side with your legs bent and stacked on top of each other. Place your right arm across your chest and your left hand on the floor in front of you for support.
Step:2 Engage your core and press your left hand into the floor, lifting your upper body off the floor.
Step:3 Hold the top position for a moment, feeling the contraction in your chest and triceps.

Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left side and perform the exercise with your right hand for support.

name: Side to side punch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Hold your fists up in front of your face in a guard position.
Step:2 Rotate your torso to the left as you punch across your body with your right hand, extending your arm fully. Keep your legs and hips stationary.
Step:3 Quickly return to the starting position, then rotate your torso to the right as you punch across your body with your left hand.
Step:4 Continue alternating punches from side to side for the desired duration or number of repetitions, maintaining a steady rhythm and controlled movements.

name: Side to side push up
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standard push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Lower your body into a push-up, bending both arms but leaning more to the right side, bringing your chest closer to your right hand.
Step:3 Push through both hands to return to the starting position.

Step:4 Lower your body into a push-up again, this time leaning more to the left side, bringing your chest closer to your left hand. Continue alternating sides with each push-up for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side wrist pull stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Extend your right arm across your torso at chest height, keeping it bent and your forearm parallel to the floor.
Step:3 Bend your left arm and use your left hand to grasp your right hand, gently pulling your right wrist backward to feel a stretch in your right wrist and forearm.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then slowly release. Repeat on the other side.

name: Single arm cable row left
instructions: Step:1 Set the cable pulley to a mid position and attach a single handle. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the handle with your left hand, arm extended towards the machine.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, push your hips backward, and lean forward slightly for balance.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your torso, bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blade back. Keeping your elbow close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the right arm.

name: Single arm cable row right
instructions: Step:1 Set the cable pulley to a mid position and attach a single handle. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the handle with your right hand, arm extended towards the machine.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, push your hips backward, and lean forward slightly for balance.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your torso, bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blade back. Keeping your elbow close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the right arm.

Single Arm On Wall Side Biceps Stretch
Single Arm On Wall Side Biceps Stretch_Female
Single arm overhead extension Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and secure one end of the resistance band under your left foot. Hold the other end of the band with your right hand, raising your right arm overhead, keeping your elbow close to your head and your palm facing forward.
Step:2 Start with your right elbow bent and your hand behind your head.
Step:3 Extend your right arm upward, fully straightening your elbow. Then, slowly lower your hand back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left arm.

Single Arm Palm Down On Wall Biceps Stretch_Female
Single arm standing low cable row
instructions: Step:1 Set the cable pulley to a low position and attach a single handle. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the handle with your left hand, arm extended towards the machine.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, push your hips backward, and lean forward slightly for balance.
Step:3 Pull the handle towards your torso, bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blade back. Keeping your elbow close to your body.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired repetitions, then switch to the right arm.

name: Single Dumbbell Biceps Curls
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands using an underhand grip (palm facing up), holding it from under the plates. Let the dumbbell hang down in front of your hips.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbell upward towards your chest by bending your elbow, focusing on engaging your biceps.
Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single kettlebell deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand in front of your body. Keep your back straight and shoulders back.
Step:2 Bend at your hips and knees to lower the kettlebell towards the floor, keeping your back flat.
Step:3 Push through your heels to return to the standing position, extending your hips and knees.

Step:4 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, then lower the kettlebell back down in a controlled manner. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand and repeat.

name: Single leg calf raise leg press machine
instructions: Step:1 Lie on the leg press machine and straighten your left leg, placing your forefoot on the platform, while your heel hangs off the edge. Your right foot should be resting on the floor.
Step:2 Press through your forefoot to lift the platform upward by extending your ankle and squeezing your calf at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position with control, ensuring you achieve a full range of motion.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Single leg incline 45 degree leg press machine
instructions: Step:1 Lie on the leg press machine and place your left foot flat on the platform while your right foot rests on the floor.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back pressed against the seat. Release the safety handles of the leg press machine.
Step:3 Press through your left foot to extend your leg fully, pushing the platform upward.
Step:4 Slowly lower the platform back down to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Single leg romanian deadlift dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. Shift your weight onto the right leg and keep it straight.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips, extending your left leg straight back while lowering the dumbbell towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue lowering until your upper body and extended leg are parallel to the floor and level from ankle to shoulders.
Step:4 Return to the starting position by driving through your standing heel. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Single leg romanian deadlifts right cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Attach one end of the resistance band to a low anchor point and hold the other end in your right hand. Stand on your left leg with your right leg slightly bent and your left foot firmly on the floor.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and lower your torso until it's parallel to the floor while extending your right leg straight back, keeping your left knee slightly bent.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by driving your hips forward and bringing your right leg back down.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Situps
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place your hands behind your head.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the floor, curling your chest towards your knees.
Step:3 Continue to lift your torso until you are in a sitting position with your chest close to your knees.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-ups
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place your hands behind your head.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your upper body off the floor, curling your chest towards your knees.
Step:3 Continue to lift your torso until you are in a sitting position with your chest close to your knees.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Alternating Arm Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles above you with both hands.
Step:2 Begin by pulling one handle down towards your hip by extending your elbow downward.
Step:3 Alternate the movement by pulling the opposite handle down towards your hip while bending the other arm upward, mimicking a skiing motion.
Step:4 Continue alternating the arm pull movements at a steady pace. Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Alternating Arm Pulls_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles above you with both hands.
Step:2 Begin by pulling one handle down towards your hip by extending your elbow downward.
Step:3 Alternate the movement by pulling the opposite handle down towards your hip while bending the other arm upward, mimicking a skiing motion.
Step:4 Continue alternating the arm pull movements at a steady pace. Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Basic Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down towards your thighs simultaneously, extending your elbows while pushing your hips back, bending your knees, and leaning your torso forward.
Step:3 Bring your arms back up to the starting position in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Continue pulling the handles down at a consistent pace for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Basic Pull_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down towards your thighs simultaneously, extending your elbows while pushing your hips back, bending your knees, and leaning your torso forward.
Step:3 Bring your arms back up to the starting position in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Continue pulling the handles down at a consistent pace for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Face Biceps Curl Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands, palms facing each other. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles towards your face in a curl motion, bending your elbows, and keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, ensuring the handles reach close to your face.
Step:4 Extend your arms back to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm. Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Flyes
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back facing the ski ergometer machine, feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the handles with both hands. Arms extended out to the sides at shoulder height.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles inward towards each other in a fly motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and squeezing your chest muscles as your hands come together.
Step:3 Pause briefly when the handles are close together in front of your chest, ensuring a strong contraction.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm. Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Jump Squat pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down towards your hips while simultaneously lowering into a squat position, bending your knees, and pushing your hips back.
Step:3 Explosively jump up from the squat position, extending your legs fully while pulling the handles back up in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Land softly back into the squat position with control, immediately transitioning into the next repetition. Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Kneeling Reverse Fly Pull
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor facing the ski ergometer machine, holding opposite handles with cables crossing, arms extended forward at head height. Engage your core and keep your back straight.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles outward in a reverse fly motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together as your arms move out to your sides.
Step:3 Pause for a second when your arms are fully extended to the sides and slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski pullover pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands and arms straight. Slightly bend your knees, push your hips back, and lean slightly forward.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down and back in a pullover motion, keeping your arms straight.
Step:3 Pull the handles down until they are at hip level, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

Step:3 Pull the handles down until they are at hip level, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Reverse Fly Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding opposite handles with cables crossing. Extend your arms forward at head height.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles outward in a reverse fly motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together as your arms move out to your sides.
Step:3 Pause for a second when your arms are fully extended to the sides and slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Reverse Fly Pull_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding opposite handles with cables crossing. Extend your arms forward at head height.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles outward in a reverse fly motion, keeping a slight bend in your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together as your arms move out to your sides.
Step:3 Pause for a second when your arms are fully extended to the sides and slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Reverse Lunge pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.

Step:2 Begin by stepping your right foot back into a reverse lunge position, lowering your body until your right knee is close to the floor and your left thigh is parallel to the floor. Simultaneously, pull both handles down towards your hips.

Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the lunge, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position, extending your left leg and bringing your right foot forward. Extend your arms back up in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Reverse Lunge pull_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.

Step:2 Begin by stepping your right foot back into a reverse lunge position, lowering your body until your right knee is close to the floor and your left thigh is parallel to the floor. Simultaneously, pull both handles down towards your hips.

Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the lunge, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position, extending your left leg and bringing your right foot forward. Extend your arms back up in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the left leg.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski reverse triceps extension pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back facing the ski ergometer machine, with the right foot a step forward and the other a step back for support. Hold the handles with both hands, palms facing each other, and upper arms parallel to the floor.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles forward, extending your elbows, and engaging your triceps.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your arms are fully extended in front of you, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back facing the ski ergometer machine, with the right foot a step forward and the other a step back for support. Hold the handles with both hands, palms facing each other, and upper arms parallel to the floor.

Step:3 Continue pulling until your arms are fully extended in front of you, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Squat pull half circles
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands.

Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles downwards with your arms bent to 90 degrees until both elbows are close to your sides, while simultaneously lowering into a squat position, bending your knees and pushing your hips back.
Step:3 Bring the handles back in a half-circle motion in a controlled manner as you stand back up from the squat.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Squat wide lat pull

Step:3 Continue pulling the handles down towards your sides until they are at hip level, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, and stand back up from the squat.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Triceps extension pull

Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down towards your hips, extending your elbows, and engaging your triceps.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your arms are fully extended down, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer Cross Country Ski Triceps extension pull_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the ski ergometer machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the handles with both hands, palms facing each other. Arms bent at 90 degrees with elbows pointing down.
Step:2 Begin by pulling both handles down towards your hips, extending your elbows, and engaging your triceps.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your arms are fully extended down, then slowly return your arms to the starting position with control, maintaining a steady rhythm.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Skipping
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and arms by your sides as if holding the handles of a skipping rope, one in each hand. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Swing your hands in a circular motion as if turning a skipping rope, and jump lightly off the floor, keeping your knees slightly bent and landing softly on your forefeet.
Step:3 Keep your jumps low and quick, simulating skipping with a rope. Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Smith machine bulgarian split squat
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under the bar of a smith machine, resting it across your shoulders, and hold it firmly with both hands. Place your right foot back on a bench or box behind you, ensuring your left foot is firmly planted on the floor in front.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your left knee, keeping your torso upright and your right knee pointing towards the floor.
Step:3 Continue lowering until your left thigh is parallel to the floor and your right knee is close to, but not touching the floor.
Step:4 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, extending your left leg fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your right leg.

name: Smith machine calf raise
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under the bar of a smith machine, resting it across your shoulders, and hold it firmly with both hands. Place your feet shoulder-width apart with your toes pointing forward.
Step:2 Lift your heels off the floor by pushing through your forefeet, raising your body upwards.
Step:3 Continue lifting until you are standing on your forefeet, then slowly lower your heels back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith machine press decline
instructions: Step:1 Position a decline bench under the smith machine. Adjust the bench so that the barbell is at chest height when lying on the bench.
Step:2 Lie on the decline bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest until it slightly touches it.
Step:4 Press the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith machine press flat
instructions: Step:1 Position a flat bench under the smith machine. Adjust the bench so that the barbell is at chest height when lying on the bench.
Step:2 Lie on the flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest until it slightly touches it.
Step:4 Press the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith machine press incline
instructions: Step:1 Position an incline bench under the smith machine. Adjust the bench so that the barbell is at chest height when lying on the bench.
Step:2 Lie on the incline bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest until it slightly touches it.
Step:4 Press the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith machine shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Position an adjustable bench under the Smith machine and set it to a vertical position. Adjust the barbell to your shoulder height.
Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Step:3 Unrack the barbell and press it upward until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider curl barbell
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and lie face down, ensuring your chest is supported and your feet are firm on the floor. Hold a barbell with an underhand grip and hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Let your arms hang straight down towards the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Curl the barbell towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary, and focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider curl dumbbells simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and lie face down, ensuring your chest is supported and your feet are firm on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Let your arms hang straight down towards the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary, and focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider curl ez bar
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and lie face down, ensuring your chest is supported and your feet are firm on the floor. Hold an EZ bar with an underhand grip and hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Let your arms hang straight down towards the floor, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Curl the EZ bar towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary, and focusing on contracting your biceps.
Step:4 Slowly lower the EZ bar back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider plank
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a standard plank position with your forearms on the floor, elbows directly under your shoulders, and your body forming a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and keep your feet hip-width apart.
Step:2 Lift your right foot off the floor and bring your right knee towards your right elbow, keeping your hips level and your core tight.
Step:3 Return your right foot to the starting position, maintaining a stable plank position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left leg, bringing your left knee towards your left elbow. Continue alternating legs for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Standing Ab Wheel Rollout
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an ab wheel with both hands. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Bend at your hips and knees to lower the ab wheel to the floor in front of your feet. Keep your arms extended and your back straight.
Step:3 Slowly roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body into a plank position. Ensure your core remains tight and your back stays straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Roll the ab wheel back towards your feet, bending at your hips and knees to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Ab Wheel Rollout_Female
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an ab wheel with both hands. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Bend at your hips and knees to lower the ab wheel to the floor in front of your feet. Keep your arms extended and your back straight.
Step:3 Slowly roll the ab wheel forward, extending your body into a plank position. Ensure your core remains tight and your back stays straight throughout the movement.
Step:4 Roll the ab wheel back towards your feet, bending at your hips and knees to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: standing adductor stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Keep your hands to your hips.
Step:2 Shift your weight to your right leg, bending your right knee while keeping your left leg straight. Lean your torso slightly forward.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, feeling a stretch along the inner thigh of your left leg.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the stretch on the other side by shifting your weight to your left leg and bending your left knee.

name: Standing arnold press dumbbell
secondaryMuscles: Upper Chest (Clavicular Head of Pectoralis Major)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Your palms should be facing backward, and your elbows should be bent.
Step:2 Begin to press the dumbbells overhead. As you press, rotate your palms so they face forward at the top of the movement.
Step:3 Fully extend your arms at the top, ensuring your biceps are near your ears.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position by rotating your palms back towards your shoulders. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing bow hamstring stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your arms by your sides. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Hinge at your hips and lower your torso towards your legs, reaching your hands towards the back of your feet. Keep your back straight and avoid rounding your shoulders.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, feeling a stretch along the back of your legs.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the stretch as needed.

name: Standing cable oblique twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand sideways to a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Attach a handle to a mid-pulley and grasp it with both hands. Bend your arms at 90 degrees and keep your elbows close to your torso sides.
Step:2 Engage your core and keep your arms stationary as you twist your torso away from the machine, pulling the handle across your body.
Step:3 Twist until your shoulders are turned 90 degrees from the machine, feeling the stretch in your oblique muscles.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position with control, keeping your arms straight. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Standing calf raise Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a resistance band under your forefeet. Hold the handles of the band by your sides.
Step:2 Slowly lift your heels off the floor by pushing through your forefeet, raising your body upwards.
Step:3 Continue lifting until you are standing on your forefeet, feeling a strong contraction in your calves.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing calf raises smith machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the Smith machine bar and place both hands on the bar keeping your arms straight. Place your forefeet shoulder-width apart on a low platform, heels extended to the floor.
Step:2 Slowly lift your heels off the floor by pushing through your forefeet, raising your body upwards.
Step:3 Continue lifting until you are standing on your forefeet, feeling a strong contraction in your calves.
Step:4 Slowly lower your heels back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing dumbbell alternate shoulder press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing forward and elbows pointing to the floor.
Step:2 Press the right dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended, keeping the left dumbbell at shoulder height.
Step:3 Lower the right dumbbell back to shoulder height with control and then press the left dumbbell overhead until your arm is fully extended.
Step:4 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing front raise dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended in front of your hips and palms facing your thighs.
Step:2 Raise both arms straight in front of you until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:3 Lower your arms back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing gastrocnemius stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a bench with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench, keeping your heel on the bench and your toes pointing up. Your left foot should remain flat on the floor.
Step:3 Lean forward slightly, grab your right heel with your right hand, and straighten your leg while lightly pulling your forefoot.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch legs and repeat. Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions on each side.

name: Standing hamstring calf stretch with Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a resistance band in both hands. Place the center of the band under your right forefoot.
Step:2 Extend your right leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the floor and your toes pointing upward. Hold the ends of the resistance band to create tension.
Step:3 Gently pull on the resistance band, leaning your torso forward to increase the stretch in your right hamstring. Keep your back straight and avoid rounding your shoulders.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch to your left leg and repeat. Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions on each side.

name: Standing lat cable pull over
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Attach a straight bar to the high pulley and hold it with both hands, arms extended and palms facing down.
Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, hinge at your hips, and lean forward slightly. Keep your arms straight and pull the bar down in an arc motion towards your thighs.
Step:3 Keep pulling the bar down until it reaches your thighs, feeling a strong contraction in your lats.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, maintaining tension in your lats. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing lateral stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms relaxed by your sides. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Place your right hand behind your head. Keep your left hand extended down the side of your leg.
Step:3 Gently bend your torso to the left as far as possible and hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, feeling a stretch along the right side of your torso.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the stretch on the other side.

name: Standing leg elevated hamstring stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing an incline bench with your feet shoulder-width apart. Place your right heel on the edge of the bench headrest, keeping your leg straight and toes pointing upward.
Step:2 Engage your core and hinge at your hips, leaning your torso towards your right leg.
Step:3 Reach towards your right foot with both hands, feeling a stretch along the back of your right leg (hamstring). Hold this position for 20-30 seconds.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and switch legs. Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions on each side.

name: Standing oblique crunch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, placing your hands behind your head with your elbows flared out to the sides. Engage your core and maintain an upright posture.
Step:2 Lift your right knee towards your right elbow while simultaneously bending your torso to the right to bring your elbow and knee closer together.
Step:3 Return to the starting position by lowering your right leg and straightening your torso.
Step:4 Repeat the movement on the left side, lifting your left knee towards your left elbow. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing one arm chest stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your right side facing near a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. Extend your right arm to the side at shoulder height and place your palm flat against the wall.
Step:2 Slowly turn your body away from the wall, keeping your arm extended and feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulder.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, maintaining a gentle pressure.
Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the stretch on the left side. Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions on each side.

name: Standing overhand shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms extended straight out in front of you at shoulder level, palms facing down.
Step:2 Swiftly raise your right arm overhead while simultaneously lowering your left arm down towards your thigh to your side. Keeping both arms straight.
Step:3 Swiftly return to the starting position and repeat the stretch by raising your left arm overhead and lowering your right arm.
Step:4 Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing quadriceps stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and find a stable surface to hold onto for balance if needed.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring your heel towards your glutes. Grasp your right ankle with your right hand.
Step:3 Keep your knees close together and lightly pull your right ankle upward, feeling a stretch along the front of your right thigh.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release your right ankle and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch on the left leg.

name: Standing quadriceps stretch side angle
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and find a stable surface to hold onto for balance if needed.
Step:2 Bend your right knee and bring your heel towards your glutes. Grasp your right ankle with your right hand.
Step:3 Keep your knees close together and lightly pull your right ankle upward, feeling a stretch along the front of your right thigh.
Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release your right ankle and return to the starting position. Repeat the stretch on the left leg.

name: Standing reverse shoulder stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your posture upright. Clasp your hands behind your back, interlocking your fingers.
Step:2 Straighten your arms and slowly lift your hands upwards, feeling a stretch in your shoulders.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, and return to the starting position by lowering your hands and releasing the clasp.
Step:4 Repeat the stretch for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing shoulder press dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing forward and elbows pointing to the floor.
Step:2 Press both dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended, keeping your elbows slightly bent at the top.
Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height with control, maintaining tension in your shoulders.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing side leg raises
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips for balance.
Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and slowly lift your right leg out to the side as high as you comfortably can, keeping it straight.
Step:3 Hold the raised leg for a second, and slowly lower your right leg back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left leg.

name: Standing side slope stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your posture upright. Raise your right arm overhead and allow your left hand to hang by your side.
Step:2 Gently lean your torso to the left, reaching your right arm over your head and feeling a stretch along the right side of your torso.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, and slowly return to the starting position.
Step:4 Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions on each side.

name: Standing swimmer
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, your left arm extended up, your right arm extended down, and your palms facing forward.
Step:2 Simultaneously move your right arm up while moving your left arm down and lightly rotating your core, mimicking a swimming motion. Keep your arms straight throughout the movement.
Step:3 Continue alternating arms in a smooth, controlled motion for the desired repetitions.

name: Standing toe touch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your posture upright and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your right leg straight up to hip height while raising your left arm to touch your right toes.
Step:3 Return your right leg and left arm to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Y raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with your arms extended forward, parallel to each other.
Step:2 With slightly bent elbows, raise both arms diagonally overhead to form a "Y" shape.
Step:3 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired repetitions

name: Star crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms and legs extended out to form an "X" shape. Keep your core engaged and your lower back pressed into the floor.
Step:2 Crunch your abdominal muscles to lift your shoulders and legs off the floor and lift your arms and legs towards each other, reaching your hands towards your ankles.
Step:3 Lower your arms and legs back to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Star jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your arms by your sides, maintaining an upright posture.
Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and lower into a half-squat position to prepare for the jump.
Step:3 Explosively jump upwards, spreading your legs out to the sides and extending your arms overhead to form a star shape in mid-air.
Step:4 Land softly with your feet together and your arms by your sides, immediately bending your knees to absorb the impact. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stationary Exercise Bike
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that when you sit on the bike, your feet can comfortably reach the pedals with a slight bend in your knees at the bottom of the pedal stroke.
Step:2 Sit on the bike with your back straight, and grip the handlebars lightly. Place your feet securely on the pedals, ensuring they are aligned properly.
Step:3 Begin pedaling by pushing down on one pedal while pulling up on the opposite pedal, creating a smooth, circular motion.
Step:4 Adjust the resistance level using the bike's control knob or digital settings to match your desired intensity. Continue pedaling for the duration of your workout.

name: Step up on chair bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a sturdy chair with your feet shoulder-width apart, keeping your posture upright.
Step:2 Place your left foot firmly on the chair, ensuring your entire foot is supported.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to lift your body onto the chair, bringing your right foot up to stand on the chair with both feet.
Step:4 Step down carefully with your right foot first, followed by your left foot. Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Straight bar cable pull down
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley. Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, palms facing down.

Step:2 Slightly bend your knees, push your hips back, and lean your torso forward slightly. Pull the bar down towards your thighs in a straight line, keeping your arms straight and your elbows slightly bent.
Step:3 Pull the bar down until it reaches your thighs, feeling a strong contraction in your lats.
Step:4 Slowly return the bar to the starting position with control, maintaining tension in your lats. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straight bar cable row close grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a cable row machine with your feet placed on the footrests and knees slightly bent. Grasp the straight bar with a close grip, palms facing down.
Step:2 Engage your core and maintain a straight back. Pull the bar towards your abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a moment, feeling the muscles in your back activating.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms to return the bar to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straight bar cable row normal grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a cable row machine with your feet placed on the footrests and knees slightly bent. Grasp the straight bar with hands just wider than shoulder-width, palms facing down.
Step:2 Engage your core and maintain a straight back. Pull the bar towards your abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your elbows close to your body.
Step:3 Hold the contraction for a moment, feeling the muscles in your back activating.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms to return the bar to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sumo squat in between legs Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Place a resistance band under your feet.
Step:2 Hold the ends of the resistance band with both hands in between your legs, keeping your hands at hip level.
Step:3 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. Keep your chest up and your back straight.
Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sumo squat over shoulder Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. Place a resistance band under your feet.
Step:2 Hold the ends of the resistance band with both hands near your shoulders, palms facing forward and elbows pointing down.
Step:3 Lower your body into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. Keep your chest up and your back straight.
Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended straight out in front of you and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor as high as you comfortably can, engaging your lower back and glutes.
Step:3 Hold the lifted position for a second, feeling the contraction in your lower back and glutes.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms, chest, and legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman holds
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended straight out in front of you and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor as high as you comfortably can, engaging your lower back and glutes.
Step:3 Hold the lifted position for 5-10 seconds, feeling the contraction in your lower back and glutes.
Step:4 Slowly lower your arms, chest, and legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman pulls
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with a resistance band secured to a low anchor point in front of you. Hold one end of the resistance band in each hand with your arms extended straight out in front of you and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor as high as you comfortably can, engaging your lower back and glutes.
Step:3 While holding the lifted position, bend your elbows and pull the resistance band towards your shoulders, squeezing your shoulder blades together.

Step:4 Extend your arms back out in front of you, keeping tension on the resistance band, and then slowly lower your arms, chest, and legs back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman pulls Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended straight out in front of you and your legs extended straight behind you.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your arms and chest off the floor as high as you comfortably can, engaging your lower back and glutes.
Step:3 While holding the lifted position, bend your elbows and pull your arms back towards your shoulders, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:4 Extend your arms back out in front of you and slowly lower your chest back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: Supine push up
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Position your elbows to your sides with your forearms perpendicular to the floor and hands kept closed.
Step:2 Engage your core and press your elbows into the floor, lifting your upper back and shoulders off the floor.
Step:3 Hold the lifted position for a second, feeling the contraction in your upper back.
Step:4 Slowly lower your upper back and shoulders back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about waist height. Stand in front of the hanging handles with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the handles with your palms facing down.

Step:3 Lower your body until your arms are fully extended above your head, feeling the tension in your core.
Step:4 Pull your body back to the starting position by pulling your arms back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Reverse Ab Rollout
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about knee height. Place your feet in the handles and assume a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width, placed directly under your shoulders, arms slightly bent, and body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Engage your core and bend your knees to bring them towards your chest while lifting your hips upwards, creating a V position.
Step:3 Continue bringing your knees towards your chest until your hips are fully bent and your knees are close to your chest.
Step:4 Slowly extend your legs back to the starting plank position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Reverse Push-up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles close to the floor. Grasp the handles with an underhand grip (palms facing forward) and position your body in a straight line, feet together and arms fully extended.
Step:2 Engage your core and maintain a straight line from your head to your heels.
Step:3 Lower your chest towards the handles by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight and elbows close to your sides.
Step:4 Press through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Reverse Push-up_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles close to the floor. Grasp the handles with an underhand grip (palms facing forward) and position your body in a straight line, feet together and arms fully extended.

Step:3 Lower your chest towards the handles by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight and elbows close to your sides.
Step:4 Press through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Side Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handle close to the floor. Stand to the side of the suspension trainer, placing your right foot in the handle and keeping your left foot firmly on the floor. Keep both hands to your sides.

Step:2 Bend your left knee and push your hips back to lower into a squat while reaching with both hands to touch the floor with your fingertips.  Keep your right leg straight through the squat and allow it to extend to the side.
Step:3 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position, keeping your right leg extended.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Single Arm Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handle to about chest height. Stand facing the handle, holding one handle with an overhand grip (palm facing down), and lean back slightly with your arm extended and feet shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Engage your arm and pull your chest towards the handle by bending your elbow and driving it out to the side, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your upper arm is parallel to the floor and your elbow is bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Split Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about chest height. Stand facing the handles with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a handle in each hand with an overhand grip (palm facing down) with the left hand and an underhand with the right (palm facing up).
Step:2 Engage your core and lean back slightly with your arm extended, keeping your body straight from head to heels and your arms extended in front of you at shoulder height.
Step:3 Spread your arms in front of you, bringing your left arm overhead and the right arm by your hip, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly bring your arms back together to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Split Fly_female
