Step:3 Spread your arms in front of you, bringing your left arm overhead and the right arm by your hip, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Step:4 Slowly bring your arms back together to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about knee height. Stand facing away from the handles, placing one foot in a handle, and step forward with the other foot to assume a split stance.
Step:2 Lower your body by bending your front knee until your thigh is parallel to the floor, keeping your back leg slightly bent and your front knee tracking over your toes.
Step:3 Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, keeping your back leg bent throughout the movement.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Straight Hip Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about knee height. Lie on your back with your heels in the handles, legs extended, and arms by your sides for support.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your heels.
Step:3 Bend your knees to pull with your heels towards your glutes and stop just before they touch together.
Step:4 Slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Supine Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about knee height. Sit on your hips with your heels in the handles and legs extended straight, and place your arms by your sides for support.
Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips off the floor while keeping your legs straight.
Step:3 Curl your knees towards your chest, and stop just before your knees touch your chest.
Step:4 Slowly bring your legs back to starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips triceps extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about waist height. Stand facing the handles, holding the handles with an overhand grip (palms facing down), and lean forward slightly with your upper arms perpendicular to your torso.
Step:2 Keep your arms bent at 90 degrees. Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Step:3 Extend your arms by pressing through your hands until your elbows are fully straight.
Step:4 Slowly bend your elbows to return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Wide Grip Inverted Row on floor
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about waist height. Stand facing the handles, holding the handles with an overhand grip (palms facing down) just wider than shoulder width. Lean back with your body straight, heels on the floor, and arms extended.
Step:2 Engage your back and pull your chest towards the handles by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Step:3 Continue pulling until your chest is close to the handles and your elbows are almost fully bent.
Step:4 Slowly extend your arms back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspension Trainer with Grips Wide Grip Inverted Row on floor_female
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the suspension trainer handles to about waist height. Stand facing the handles, holding the handles with an overhand grip (palms facing down) just wider than shoulder width. Lean back with your body straight, heels on the floor, and arms extended.

name: Svend press decline bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured under the foot pads and your back firmly against the bench. Hold a weight plate with both hands, pressing your palms against the flat sides of the plate at chest level with your fingers pointing up.
Step:2 Engage your chest and press the weight plate straight out in front of you by extending your arms.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles as you press the plate outward until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly bring the plate back to your chest with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Svend press flat bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back firmly against the bench. Hold a weight plate with both hands, pressing your palms against the flat sides of the plate at chest level with your fingers pointing up.
Step:2 Engage your chest and press the weight plate straight out in front of you by extending your arms.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles as you press the plate outward until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly bring the plate back to your chest with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Svend press incline bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back firmly against the bench. Hold a weight plate with both hands, pressing your palms against the flat sides of the plate at chest level with your fingers pointing up.
Step:2 Engage your chest and press the weight plate straight out in front of you by extending your arms.
Step:3 Squeeze your chest muscles as you press the plate outward until your arms are fully extended.
Step:4 Slowly bring the plate back to your chest with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Trap bar deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a trap bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees and hips to lower your body, and grasp the trap bar handles with a neutral grip (palms facing in).
Step:2 Engage your core; keep your chest up and your back straight. Push through your heels to lift the trap bar off the floor, extending your hips and knees simultaneously.
Step:3 Stand up straight, pulling your shoulders back at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the bar back to the floor by bending your hips and knees, maintaining a straight back. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Trap bar shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the center of a trap bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees and hips to lower your body, and grasp the handles of the trap bar with a neutral grip (palms facing in).
Step:2 Stand up straight with the trap bar at arm's length by your sides, keeping your core engaged and back straight.
Step:3 Lift your shoulders towards your ears, squeezing your traps at the top of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower your shoulders back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Treadmill Jogging
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the treadmill with your feet on the side rails and attach the safety clip to your clothing. Start the treadmill at a low speed to safely step onto the belt.
Step:2 Once you are on the moving belt, gradually increase the speed to a comfortable jogging pace, maintaining an upright posture with your core engaged.
Step:3 Keep your arms bent at a 90-degree angle, swinging them naturally at your sides to match your jogging rhythm.
Step:4 Maintain a steady pace, landing mid-foot with each stride and keeping your breathing steady. Jog for the desired duration or distance.

name: Tricep cable kickback on crossover machine
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, and set the cable at a low position. Hold the cable end in one hand and bend slightly forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent.
Step:2 Position your upper arm parallel to the floor with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle, keeping your elbow close to your side.
Step:3 Extend your arm backward by straightening your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary, and only moving your forearm.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbow. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Tricep extension machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the tricep extension machine, adjusting the seat height so that your upper arms comfortably rest on the arm pad, with your elbows bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:2 Grasp the handles with a neutral grip, ensuring your elbows are below the pivot point.
Step:3 Push the handles forward by straightening your elbows and fully extending your arms while keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: tricep rope extension on crossover machine
Triceps dip machine
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the triceps dip machine and place your feet flat on the floor. Adjust the seat height so that your upper arms are parallel to the floor when you grasp the handles.
Step:2 Grip the handles firmly, keeping your elbows bent and close to your sides. Slightly lean your torso forward.
Step:3 Push the handles downward by straightening your elbows and extending your arms fully while keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps light stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and raise your right arm at chest height across your chest, bending your elbow.
Step:2 Use your left hand to gently grab your right elbow, pulling it across your chest to deepen the stretch in your triceps.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, feeling a gentle stretch in your triceps.
Step:4 Release the stretch and repeat with your left arm. Perform the stretch for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps rope extension on crossover machine
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to the high pulley of a crossover machine. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, and grasp the ends of the rope with both hands, palms facing each other.
Step:2 Step back slightly to create tension in the cable and position your body so your upper arms are close to your sides, and your elbows are bent at a 90-degree angle.
Step:3 Push the rope down by straightening your elbows, separating the rope ends, and extending your arms fully while keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:4 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upper back stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height, rounding your upper back and pushing your hands forward.
Step:2 Lower both arms backward, bringing them to your sides just past behind your hips.
Step:3 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, feeling a gentle squeeze in your upper back and shoulder blades.
Step:4 Release and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upright row barbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Allow the barbell to rest against your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Pull the barbell upward along the front of your body by bending your elbows and lifting your upper arms.
Step:3 Continue lifting the barbell until it reaches chest height, keeping your elbows higher than your wrists throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upright row cable Resistance band
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart in the middle of a resistance band, holding a handle in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing back). Ensure the band is taut when your arms are extended downwards.
Step:2 Lift the handles straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows and keeping the band close to your body.
Step:3 Raise the handles until your elbows are slightly higher than your shoulders and pointing to your sides.
Step:4 Slowly lower the handles back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upright row dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing your thighs). Let the dumbbells rest against your thighs.
Step:2 Lift the dumbbells straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows and keeping the weights close to your body.
Step:3 Raise the dumbbells until your elbows are level with your shoulders, ensuring your upper arms are parallel to the floor.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upright row ez bar
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding an EZ Bar with an overhand grip (palms facing down), hands placed shoulder-width apart. Allow the barbell to rest against your thighs with your arms fully extended.
Step:2 Pull the EZ Bar upward along the front of your body by bending your elbows and lifting your upper arms.
Step:3 Continue lifting the EZ Bar until it reaches chest height, keeping your elbows higher than your wrists throughout the movement.
Step:4 Slowly lower the EZ Bar back to the starting position by extending your arms fully. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Upward rotation Bent arms
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, arms bent at 90 degrees with your upper arms parallel to the floor, and your forearms pointing down to the floor.
Step:2 Rotate your forearms upwards until your fingers point towards the ceiling, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 Slowly rotate them back to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired repetitions

name: V bar lat pull down
instructions: Step:1 Sit at a lat pulldown machine with your feet flat on the floor and knees secured under the pads. Grasp the V-bar attached to the machine, arms fully extended above you, and hands shoulder-width apart.
Step:2 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest and bring your elbows downwards.
Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the bottom of the movement.
Step:4 Slowly return the V-bar to the starting position. Repeat for the desired repetitions.

name: V crunches
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your legs extended and your arms extended on the floor overhead.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your legs and torso off the floor, reaching your hands towards your feet to form a 'V' shape with your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your abdominal muscles at the top of the movement, ensuring your hands reach towards your feet.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs and torso back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: V up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your legs and arms extended so that your body forms a straight line.
Step:2 Simultaneously lift your legs and torso off the floor, reaching your hands towards your feet to form a 'V' shape with your body.
Step:3 Squeeze your abdominal muscles at the top of the movement, ensuring your hands reach towards your feet.
Step:4 Slowly lower your legs and torso back to the starting position with control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, rolling through the heel to the ball of your foot while swinging your left arm forward and right arm back.
Step:3 Push off with your right foot, bringing your left foot forward to step, swinging your right arm forward and left arm back.
Step:4 Continue this alternating pattern, maintaining a natural stride and rhythm. Repeat for the desired distance or time.

name: Walking Fast
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, rolling through the heel to the ball of your foot while swinging your left arm forward and right arm back.
Step:3 Push off with your right foot, quickly bringing your left foot forward to step, swinging your right arm forward and left arm back. Increase your pace while maintaining control.
Step:4 Continue this alternating pattern, maintaining a brisk and consistent stride. Repeat for the desired distance or time.

Step:3 Push off with your right foot, bringing your left foot forward to step, swinging your right arm forward and left arm back.

name: Walkout
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms relaxed by your sides.
Step:2 Bend your hips and knees to place your hands on the floor before you.
Step:3 Walk your hands forward, keeping your legs straight, until you are in a plank position with your hands under your shoulders and your body forming a straight line from head to heels.
Step:4 Walk your hands back towards your feet, lifting your hips and forming an inverted V shape with your body. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wall sit bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and your feet shoulder-width apart, about 2 feet away from the wall.
Step:2 Slide your back down the wall until your thighs are parallel to the floor, and your knees are directly above your ankles.
Step:3 Hold this position, keeping your back flat against the wall and your hands relaxed by your sides or on your thighs.
Step:4 Maintain the position for the desired duration, then slowly stand back up.

name: Wall squat bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and your feet shoulder-width apart, about 2 feet away from the wall.
Step:2 Slide your back down the wall until your thighs are parallel to the floor and your knees are at a 90-degree angle, ensuring your knees are directly above your ankles.
Step:3 Push through your heels to stand back up, sliding your back up the wall until you return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wall squat with pause bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and your feet shoulder-width apart, about 2 feet away from the wall.
Step:2 Slide your back down the wall until your thighs are parallel to the floor and your knees are at a 90-degree angle, ensuring your knees are directly above your ankles.
Step:3 Pause for 5-10 seconds and then push through your heels to stand back up, sliding your back up the wall until you return to the starting position.
Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: weighted standing shoulder press with plate
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight plate with both hands at chest level, elbows bent and pointing down.
Step:2 Press the plate upward by extending your arms fully above your head, keeping your core tight and your back straight.
Step:3 Lower the plate back down to chest level in a controlled manner.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wheels To Heaven
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight together, and your arms resting by your sides. Position an ab roller between your heels.
Step:2 Lift your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them slightly bent, holding the ab roller securely between your heels.
Step:3 Engage your core and push your legs upward, raising your hips high off the floor.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down slowly keeping your legs up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wheels To Heaven_Female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight together, and your arms resting by your sides. Position an ab roller between your heels.
Step:2 Lift your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them slightly bent, holding the ab roller securely between your heels.
Step:3 Engage your core and push your legs upward, raising your hips high off the floor.
Step:4 Lower your hips back down slowly keeping your legs up. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wheels To Toes
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight together and your arms extended diagonally overhead, holding an ab roller.
Step:2 Lift your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight, and simultaneously raise the ab roller towards your toes, lifting your upper back off the floor.
Step:3 Slowly lower your legs and the ab roller back down to the starting position, stopping just before they touch the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wheels To Toes_Female
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight together and your arms extended diagonally overhead, holding an ab roller.
Step:2 Lift your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight, and simultaneously raise the ab roller towards your toes, lifting your upper back off the floor.
Step:3 Slowly lower your legs and the ab roller back down to the starting position, stopping just before they touch the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide push ups bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin in a plank position with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. Your body should form a straight line from head to heels.
Step:2 Engage your chest and lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them at a 90-degree angle to your body.
Step:3 Lower your chest until it is just above the floor.
Step:4 Push through your hands to raise your body back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wind wipers
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your arms extended out to the sides for stability, lift your legs up towards the ceiling, and keep them bent at 90 degrees.
Step:2 Lower your knees to the right side, keeping them bent together until they are just above the floor.
Step:3 Raise your knees back to the center position, and then lower them to the left side until they are just above the floor.
Step:4 Repeat the movement, alternating sides, for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wrist curl barbell
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up).
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the barbell to hang downward.
Step:3 Curl the barbell upward by flexing your wrists, lifting it as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wrist curl dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a dumbbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up) in each hand.
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the dumbbells to hang downward.
Step:3 Curl the dumbbells upward by flexing your wrists, lifting the weights as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully extending your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wrist extension barbell
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the barbell to hang downward.
Step:3 Extend the barbell upward by flexing your wrists, lifting it as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully curling your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wrist extension dumbbell
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor in front of a bench, placing both forearms over the bench while holding a dumbbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down) in each hand.
Step:2 Rest your wrists just off the edge of the bench, allowing the dumbbells to hang downward.
Step:3 Extend the dumbbells upward by flexing your wrists and lifting the weights as high as possible while keeping your forearms flat on the bench.
Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, fully curling your wrists. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Zotman curl dumbbell simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing forward) and arms hanging by your sides.
Step:2 Curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward (overhand grip), and then lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the underhand grip once you reach the bottom of the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Zotman curls Resistance band simultaneous
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, in the middle of a resistance band, holding the handles with an underhand grip (palms facing forward), arms hanging by your sides.
Step:2 Curl the handles towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and keeping your upper arms stationary.
Step:3 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward (overhand grip), and then lower the handles back down to the starting position with control.
Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the underhand grip once you reach the bottom of the movement. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline bench oblique crunches bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Begin by lying on a decline bench with your feet secured under the footpads. Position yourself so that your hips are at the edge of the bench.
Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or crossed on your chest with your elbows pointing out to the sides.
Step:3 Engage your core and lift your upper body towards your right knee, twisting your torso to engage your oblique muscles.
Step:4 Lower your upper body back to the starting position with control and then lift your upper body towards your left knee. Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.
